lic_profile: A 7 Numbers Danforth  welcome is like a familiar embrace. The fun and lively neighbourhood restaurant specializes in fresh, unpretentious and authentic Southern Italian food. The space is eclectic, warm and comfortable, a theme repeated by the staff and owners alike. Let Mama Rosa and her team wine and dine you in comfort, just like family.

reviews.text: Love this local eatery - it's our go to whenever we want to have a great meal, and unwind after a work day. Always consistent with the quality of food and...
I had heard of this place via BlogTO as one of the best Italian restaurants in Toronto and had been eager to try it. I live near the Danforth, but never...
When I first moved to Toronto, almost twenty years ago, I lived near the Danforth and I look forward to any opportunity to return to the east end. Where the...
Love the food!! Nice vegetarian offerings. Very comfortable.  Generally the staff are good.

Seven Numbers in Greek Town is a popular place if you are in turmoil for Italian food. You have the option to choose from a menu of 'small plates' as well as full-size servings. Service is friendly yet professional, a very popular place for 'Italian' food in Greek Town. Novel and delicious combinations of traditional Italian foods!

A really great restaurant, service, food, and drinks. You will eventually meet every one of your neighbors in this family friendly Italian oasis on the Danforth. Bring your friends, get the good wine, and order family style.
Had dinner with my wife and another couple. The lasagna was excellent, but the lemon veal (vitello limone) I had was just average.

The service was excellent but I think the menu didn't have too much variety to choose from and I went there mainly to try the lasagna after seeing good reviews but I definitely think it was nothing special. It was bland, and the tomato sauce was kind of bitter tasting. I've had better lasagna at plenty of other spots in the city

A La Carte is such an underrated amongst the participating Summerlicious restaurants. It's located upstairs to the Gardiner...
I think this place needed more than 1 server on a Sunday afternoon. Overall this place is not bad, the view is nice and the presentation of the food was...

Chef Michael Da Silva prepares a variety of traditional and contemporary dishes with primarily Portuguese and Spanish influences. White tablecloths, rustic bronze walls and cozy booths provide a fine yet casual ambience. Adega's pastry kitchen and port wine selections offer the perfect finish to the Adega experience.

reviews.text: Excellent service and food! I had the prix fixe salad, squid, then biscotti. For each course the presentation was cute and creative. Also, the squid was...
I was here for summerlicious with a bunch of coworkers months ago and had a great experience. So when I was part of the committee to plan our work winter...

The essence: A warm inviting atmosphere and interesting Portuguese cuisine options.

The food: While the food was pleasant, it wasn't special.  

The...

Want great Portuguese??

Look no further. Best grilled octopus in Toronto. Cozy, classy, great service, great food, this place has been in business for a very long time. I've been coming here for a decade and it's been so consistent. Same menus since then. There's a wine cellar downstairs for private parties. 

Amazing olive oil for dipping bread, just so good. 

Ask for the booth for special occasions.

We randomly chose this venue looking for a non meat centric restaurant and what a surprise! Fernando was such a great host and server. He helped us choose a fantastic Portuguese wine based on our taste and we had a good laugh when the cork didn’t want to come out. We ordered the two specials, seafood stew and octopus which where both large portions and really well prepared. Highly recommend this place for seafood lovers.

My friends and I decided to come here for a birthday dinner. The moment we walked in, we were greeted very kindly and were asked if we wanted to hang our jackets. Every single thing about this restaurant was amazing! From the moment we walked in, to our service, to our food, etc. The ambiance is very romantic or is a perfect place to have dinner with very close friends. With the two bottles of wine, the food and the tip, our bill came up to $300 and change for the four of us. Every dollar was worth it! Thank you so much to the chef and the servers for making this a very special birthday for our friend.

My wife and I went in Dec and from the moment we came through the door until the moment we left through that same door...... To us was a 5 star experience.......service, food, drinks and service.... Nothing missed the mark if I'm scoring.
Great food and wonderful service.  Their squid is first rate.  They also have a fixed price dinner which is excellently priced.  I go there almost every time I am in Toronto.  Highly recommend it.

lic_profile: Enjoy a bold urban tavern experience at the new Against The Grain, located in the Corus Quay building, at Cherry Beach, with a breathtaking view of Centre Island and the waterfront. The menu balances traditional tavern offerings with bold, unexpected flavours complemented with a true craft experience of rotating craft pours and hand-crafted cocktails. Cozy up in the lounge and enjoy a social with friends or pull up to "the wood" to watch the game. Either way, stop in and experience the new Against The Grain - change is good.

reviews.text: If it wasn't for a festival in the area, I would never wander into this restaurant that is way out of the downtown core. It is attached to the CORUS...

Love the food not the service, first time here we had a reservation, place was half empty, we had a friend with a broken leg and they made us wait.
Got our...

Only shared an appetizer and one main. They were good and the service was adequate. Nothing special.

The view from the deck is great and we enjoyed the...

My friends and I spent the day on your beautiful patio yesterday for my friends birthday. I just wanted to say that we had an AMAZING time! Our server, Mark (I believe - Irish guy from Cork), was absolutely outstanding! When I told him about my friends birthday, and her being vegan, he was able to bring out a surprise birthday treat, vegan friendly, for her and she was delighted. Judging on this experience, I'll definitely be back! Great service, great food, and wonderful atmosphere!

I have been to eat here few times and always enjoyed myself. Recently we hosted a party here and had a great time. Nice atmosphere, excellent patio in the summer and great parking if you are doing an event.

Friendly staff and great spot to be at. Right beside sugar beach and right on the water. A huge a patio waterside that is great. Quick service and cool looking place in the bottom of the corus building. The location also makes the environment better as it's mostly professionals here.

Food is great. I tipped well. Service was good. Then all I got was a parking ticket when the waitress told me that the place where I parked my car was theirs. So yeah, unforgettable experience. I reported it to the manager but can't do anything anyways.

Wish I could give this place zero stars. One of the worst restaurants I've ever been to. Our server didn't even come up to us after being sat for 15 minutes, and the manager stood right there and didn't help us either. We got our drinks and appetizer and never saw the server again. We actually had to get up and go find someone to pay our bill. He never came and asked us how things were, if we wanted to order meals or get more drinks when ours were done. Then after asking to speak to the manager they told me no because he was busy with a problem in the back. LOL WHAT?!  can safely say I will never go back or recommend this horrible restaurant to anyone.

lic_profile: AGO Bistro, the Art Gallery of Ontario’s award-winning restaurant, is a distinct Frank Gehry-designed space. Casual and chic with modern Danish furnishings paired with acrylic tabletops in a multitude of vibrant colours and a contemporary installation of Frank Stella's work. AGO Bistro's contemporary global bistro cuisine showcases seasonal flavours featuring local seasonal fare and quality fresh ingredients.

reviews.text: First rate in ever sense of the word. The menu ranges wide enough to satisfy most tastes, the food is fantastic, the space is beautiful, the service is...
Bae and I visited for a quiet brunch after enjoying a private viewing of the Guillermo Del Toro exhibit (side note, if you can catch the exhibition I would...
We had the Guillermo Del Toro prix fixe, and the food was good but not exceptional for the price - although the salad with grilled cheese was amazing....

We had the fixed price dinner menu after seeing the del Toro show. It was wonderful and themed to fit the show.  For example, chili chocolate cake with avocado ice cream...inventive and engaging.  

The space is lovely and the service was excellent.

This place used to be great until our last visit. I was so disappointed in Frank. The food and the service. My duck was way too salty and my friend's dish came out cool (it should have been hot). When we complained, nothing was done about it. I believe this place needs to focus more on customer satisfaction and better food or it will go under very fast. I will never return again.

We went for drinks and dessert before a special event at the gallery. The drinks were amazing, although pricey, but the desert was just alright. I had the Monet's Garden cocktail, which was very visually impactful and delightfully astringent and floral. My partner had Foraging with Emily which was very much like drinking a camp fire, but in a good way. The trifle was tasty, but the cake was dense. The caramelized apple cake was also nothing special. 

The atmosphere is cozy and relaxed, even in such a giant space. The staff were knowledgeable and friendly. I would go back for cocktails and tapas and maybe try dinner, but I would not consider it a desert destination.

Pricey, but a beautifully designed space. Food was surprisingly great on my most recent visit. They serve tasty sloane tea. 

Good spot if you're in the area or if you're with an older crowd but I wouldn't seek it out.

The ambiance is amazing. Great place to have a cocktail after visiting the AGO. The food is good but not good enough to match the prices. The presentation is solid, but again there is nothing special about the food, it's just good. Does not match the price range.

lic_profile: A quaint, neighbourhood restaurant, Aioli Bistro is located in the heart of Cliffside Village not far from the Scarborough Bluffs. The menu features dishes from the South of France including classics such as confit de canard and cassoulet paired with a selection of primarily French wines handpicked to enhance your dining experience. The decor, candle lit dining room and sounds of Piaf, Brel & Aznavour make one feel as if they are in a small village bistro in France. The experience is further enhanced by the chef and friendly staff as they greet guests, explain the dishes and ensure a wonderful meal.

reviews.text: Terrific! Food is delicious and wine is fantastic. Chef Henry makes the experience. The place won't disappoint. The food and music evenings are wonderful...
Came here for summerlicious. Love the ambience and customer service. Food was a little over seasoned and salty. The lavender and honey Creme brûlée was a...
Great food and service. Feels like you are in a Paris bistro.

This was a nice little French restaurant. The portion sizes were great, the food was good, and the staff were very nice! It was an experience, but not somewhere I would eat all the time. The summer special menu, is what I ordered from, and it was a 3 course meal. Definitely something to try if your just looking for something new!
A delicious $30 Prix Fixe three-course French cuisine fine dining. Truly a hidden gem in Scarborough!

A little gem here! If you enjoy classic country French cuisine, this cozy little Bistro is the spot! Chef and owner, Henri  is a wonderful host. Just 50 seats, reservations are recommended. Nice wines at reasonable prices too.Henri and Celeste prepare fresh local food with such love in every bite.
The bread and aioli we got was really good. Chilled cauliflower puree was nice too. The salmon and duck dishes were good but a bit overcooked. The service was the best part. Very friendly staff.
My boyfriend and I came here for dinner and the food and service were excellent! Will definitely be returning soon!

lic_profile: Most appropriately named, music lovers and food enthusiasts have made Alleycatz a popular dining and party destination. A menu with Mediterranean flair, a varied martini line-up and after dinner entertainment in the form of salsa, bachata, and live bands playing blues & top 40's dance music. Warm and convivial in red oak and exposed brick, Alleycatz sets a comfortable and fun environment for their guests.

reviews.text: Overall we had a good experience at Alleycatz but it's a bit of an unusual spot. We decided to take advantage of their summerlicious menu and enjoy the live...
So we came in with groupon. and it happened to be a black event.. which we had zero clue about when we were making reservations. so we felt completely out...

Came here for dinner (Summerlicious menu) and dancing on a Friday night.

Was expecting service to be slow, based on previous reviews, but I guess choosing...

Was there last Saturday for dinner and stayed to hear a band called Sound Parade. Dinner was decent. My Paella was so so. My sister liked her pasta w Vodka sauce.
The band played good songs but the 2 singers were awful. It sounded more like screaming than singing. Couldn't hit the high notes. The rest of the band however were pretty good. My advice to them: replace your vocalists. 
The saving grace was the DJ who played music during the band's break. He was fantastic. Had the crowd going w different music mixes. Played something for everyone.

Do not expect a King Street Entertainment District experience. Be prepare to have a good Friday or Saturday night out for dancing and libations! Crowd tends to be mature.  Weekend bands are proper. Lady Kane and Solar band are the main hitters!! Treat the bartenders well and they will take care of you!   No review on food.  Enjoy!

Went as a work Christmas party, asked for a vegan option. Got a basic tomato sauce pasta with no dessert and hardly any vegetables in the dish (did not even offer fruit as dessert)... The order was collected in advance, so not accommodating at all. If you're vegan don't come here for alternative options.

My wife and I were introduced to Alleycatz via Groupon, we got there early with about 6 couples seated, once we settled  in at the bar our bar keep  Bobby made us feel amazingly comfortable.
The 3 courses were delicious, try the salmon, my wife ate my sticky toffee desert (not good)and left me with her ice cream, mmm.

In about an hour of being there the venue started to fill, great crowd  between 20 - 50.  Live music, DJ and great drinks (Old Fashion).

Can't say enough, great night out. We'll be back, highly recommend.

Second time there. First time was just for drinks and dancing. This time we went for food.

They were getting ready for Halloween night so things were a little bit hectic and kind of all over the place. But that's to be expected.

Food was great. Service slightly slow but friendly. Only complaint I have is that the appetizers were cold, tasteless & a very small portion.

I do love this place though!

lic_profile: Antler Kitchen and Bar is a celebration of regional ingredients. Chef Michael Hunter's menu aims to define Canadian cuisine highlighting local seasonal and wild foods.

reviews.text:
Brunch like whoa.
Had the pork belly breakfast sandwich ($8) and absolutely loved it.
The homefries ($5) were well cooked and even the crispy dried up bits...

Locked coming here. The game and meat options are first class and perfectly  prepared. 
I was blown away by the deer main and the mushroom app. 

Wine...
Came here on Saturday afternoon for brunch with 3 friends. It's a small space with a cozy, warm atmosphere. I really liked some of the wall decorations...

Enjoyed a great NYE dinner here with friends.  I was shocked that we were able to get a reservation for 6 when I booked a couple weeks ago.  Overall, the night was awesome. 
The Service: Fantastic.  I regret not remembering our servers name, but she was great.  She kept the laughs coming along with everything else.  It seemed that everyone working that night was having fun. 
The Food and Drinks:  Interesting and exciting options.   I started with the barrel aged cocktail and duck heart yakitori, both of which were delicious.   For my main,  I had the Deer, which was prepared Rare Plus, just the way I like my lean red meats.  The spice ash was complex and complimented the gaminess of meat.  Dessert included the Cedar Sour and sticky toffee pudding.  Again, both were fantastic.  My friends got the smoked chocolate dessert, which I have to admit was a bit of a let down.  The presentation was great, but the smoke overtook all other flavours in the dish.  

I would definitely recommend this place.

Food was spectacular. Never did I imagine eating cow tongue and duck hearts would be so good. Venison was cooked to perfection and well presented with complimenting flavours. Service was on point and Bobby, the head honcho bar guy (not his technical title) is the stuff of legends when it come to delicious creative cocktails. The place is a game meat lovers dream. Vegetarians also welcome. You should go.

This was a last minute brunch decision that proves that I am amazingly smart when hungover. Everything was so simple, but extremely well done. You get some classic options on the menu that should satisfy most people.  The service was incredible and made us feel very welcome to just hang out and have drinks after our meal was done. One nice little twist on a classic was the Caesar. It was made with sake. Crazy and very good!  I definitely look forward to my next visit here.

Simple food,  fresh and wild ingredients,  chef tends to bring out the food's flavor heavily using cream,  salt,  smoked ingredients and sauce.   Sligtly salty but tasty.  This place should attract lots of game meat lovers.  Home made hearty style dishes.   Very very nice service.

Just wow, top notch!! Incredible food, fantastic cocktails and great service. Everything we ate and drank left us speechless; we didn’t want to leave without trying everything on the menu! Without a doubt, we will be back.

reviews.text: Archeo is easy to miss when you are visiting the Distillery District and not specifically looking for it - even though it is right at the main gate entrance...

Most Memorable Feature: Honest servers

Came here on a double date for summerlicious dinner.  We had very friendly and honest servers who weren't afraid to...
After walking awhile in the Christmas market it was already 8, so we just randomly chose Arheo for dinner since it is just located in the Distillery...

We had our wedding reception at Archeo in October. Chantal, our wedding coordinator at the venue, was very organized and a pleasure to work with. When we got to Archeo after our wedding ceremony, we were so happy with the way the venue looked! The venue is already so beautiful so we only needed flowers and candles. The room is perfect for a candlelit dinner. The food was fantastic! We received so many compliments from our guests about how wonderful the food was. The vegetarians were also very happy with the curry! Everything came out very hot and the timing was perfect. The manager greeted us at the door when we came in and made sure we were well taken care of. The room is perfect for 100 people without being too tight. The bartender was also really great! I would highly recommend this venue!

We had our holiday party here and being a vegetarian I found it was good but not up to the mark. They served Thai coconut curry with rice which was okay but the butternut squash soup was amazing and rich in texture. Salad had too much of vinegar in that which made it quite sour. Dessert was great. Overall it’s a good place to visit specially during Christmas festivities and the four course meal was very fulfilling.

My husband and I had our wedding here in late October 2017. Throughout the wedding planning process (took about 1.5 years), Distillery Events always kept us informed. I was extremely happy with the wedding coordination. We had Chantal as our Coordinator and she was amazing.

The main reason we chose Archeo as our wedding venue was the interior decor. There was no need to add our own decoration so we only added centrepieces, and photographs as our table runners. Archeo was already gorgeous so we were lucky we didn't need to add more.

Our wedding was during the day so we used the Brunch menu with the added food station that had Asian food. Our guests loved the variety and it was very delicious. They all went home with full bellies.

Overall I'm so glad we chose Archeo as our wedding venue.

Everything was fantastic until the heat became an issue.  I tried tirelessly to convince the banquet manager be he would not budge on having the doors open with the AC on.  it was actually very cool outside I felt that since we paid 20k to have the place for the evening that we could at least make a decision on what we wanted for doors being open and AC on at the same time.  We had a lot of people complain that it was far too hot.  Other than that the venue, servers, bar staff and food was amazing.  I would just recommend talking to the staff beforehand and negotiation having control over the doors being open while the AC is on.
Priced well for a fancy restaurant. Service is excellent as they explained ingredients in the dishes. Very few vegetarian options but those taste great.

lic_profile: Aria offers genuine Italian fine dining in a contemporary urban setting. Aria is owned by Guido Saldini and Elena Morelli the proprietors of Noce Restaurant which has helped set the standard for Italian cuisine in Toronto for almost 20 years.  "Aria" means "air" in Italian but also references the most Italian of art forms - opera.  Both themes are evident inside Aria which boasts a dramatic 35 foot ceiling and is situated adjacent to the Air Canada Centre and Maple Leaf Square. Aria has dining capacity for 130 people and can accommodate private parties in a variety of formats.

reviews.text: Decent Italian eats steps from the ACC. Busy during lunch as it's located in the same building as MMC, PwC and Telus. Good pick for a business lunch....

Was here for a corporate Christmas party and saw the Yelp reviews before we left and was already kind of knowing I was not going to love this.

We had...
I am really surprised that this place has such negative reviews for what it actually serves and represents...people, really need to stop being so harsh on...

I love going here! It is a beautiful restaurant that never seems busy or loud. It is actually very tranquil. The decor is absolutely stunning. The food is amazing as well. Everything I have had there has been delicious. Service is good, wine selection is good. During the day it is very bright and you can people-watch everyone running to union station.

Myself and several of my friends came here this past evening and a friend ordered the 'Spaghetti' with the clams, and it was beyond bland. Basically flour and the black pepper is all you will taste if you choose the spaghetti pasta or gnocchi, or anything else on their menu. The risotto is completely average and not worth the $25-$30. The 'Spaghetti Pasta' was bland and a friend asked to return it, and the waitress, 'Nadja', said "I offered you 3 other options" and was extremely argumentative and rude about it all. The "manager" Martina, was not any more professional and proceeded to defend the rudeness of her waitress staff. It took them well over an hour for them to clear our table and offer the bill. Overall, the food was terrible, bland, and overpriced for tasteless food, and the staff was extremely rude. If you want overpriced tasteless food and pretentious service please come here. Enjoy.

Absolutely incredible service and food. Mark not only knew his wines but customized them to our personal tastes and blended them seamlessly with our food. Not back in Toronto often but this will be a required stop when we are.
Food was good. Had the rabbit and it was delicious. Service is excellent. It is pricey. Not a quiet restaurant. Highly recommend.

Great ambience, simple and sparse menu with seasonal options! Give the specials a try, I had the risotto with a generous portion of truffle shavings which was delicious. Desert was also exceptional with the Nutella cheese cake!

reviews.text: Really cute Korean and Japanese restaurant by Bathurst and Bloor. My friend and I came for summerlicious and it was so great that we are definitely looking...

Wanted to just update plus 1 star! 

I still haven't tried the regular menu but as I said before, I think it's much better than the summerlicious menu...

I came here for dinner for one of my friends birthday. It was packed when we arrived so we had to wait about 15mins before a table was cleared up. 

It was...
Amazing restaurant! Definitely recommend for big parties or small, very clean and great service with a smile. Food was so delicious and filling as well. Would go back here in a heart beat!!

Service was not that good, it is very overpriced and it is not all you can eat. Quality of the meat is good but the portion could be better. However, the worst thing was the “mistake” in our bill, they tried charging us $10.00 over the price quoted and we were NOT the only people with problems with our bill (we overheard at least two other tables who complained)
Everything was decent and edible, not exceptionally delicious. Beer prices are really good if they have promos. The baby octopus was overcooked and had too much batter.

I've been to this place couple of times. Interior is nice although the lighting can be greatly improved. There are seats one can only stare to his plate to avoid the ceiling lamp. The food is good offered at a higher price compared to neighboring restaurants with comparable food quality (and slightly bigger portion). They're also courteous in taking the empty plates as soon as you're done and bringing you the bill to the point that one feels they're asking you to leave the premises once the food is over, even though we had still our drinks going on.
Loved this experience. We cooked at the table. Excellent service and quality food. Will go again!

reviews.text: I came here on a Friday during Summerlicious. I must say, even during Summerlicious, this restaurant is empty. I'm not sure if it's prior reviews, or if...

Grilled chicken club was a great lunch. Got the "yam fries" (I asked for "no salt", but they came salted anyway).

Good choice of beers in the small on-tap...
Solid place for a meal with a unique view. Came for breakfast/brunch on a Friday -- the restaurant was fairly empty. The stadium was being converted from...

It's a really good value and experience when there's a game.  Otherwise, it's a hotel restaurant.  There is no audio of the game in the restaurant but the window seating is worth it.  Make reservations and call for a window seat.  The food was standard hotel restaurant but better than what you'd find in a ballpark.  The service is basically bar service and are busy during game days.

I tried to find attracted place for dinner in solo mode at one November’s day after long nice walking through Toronto Waterfront. 

Arriba restaurant was right choose. Service was great, thank a lot to Mr.Monoj ). 

Well-done beefstake, two cup of dark Canadian beer, Cesar salat and for finish tune, one awesome cake (not remember it name, but it second one from upper left side of cakes menu). 

Guys, I will return to this place and I sure I would have amazing experience if I will see Blue Jays game via big window to Rogers Center.

Awesome restaurant to seat, eat and watch the blue jays play!! the food was surprisingly very delicious.. the staff was very friendly too.. its more of a bar with good food and not a upscale sit down restaurant..   Great hang out place with friends
Wonderful place, with DELICIOUS food, with an awesome view! Our server Sunil was awesome as well.  I'd fly from Texas again to eat here...love it!

Used to be a hidden gem for Blue Jay games, but that's in the past.  Great place to eat food, have drinks, spend time with friends and watch the Jays game. The recommendations for food would be their calamari, nachos and burgers.

reviews.text: Came for a business dinner and the food and atmosphere was lovely. The staff was extremely attentive, there is coat check, and our wine and water glasses...
Miss my days in France, sat down for a food excursion in an attempt to relive la vie. The service was on point. Had wonderful and friendly service that...
The service was bad, the atmosphere was chaotic, lighting is a bit off, there was no vibe, my seat was awkward, was not what I expected from a restaurant at...

Amazing service! The waiters were super friendly and helpful. The food was delicious and flavourful but a bit on the smaller side. The Earl Grey Tea was an amazing finish. Probably the best earl grey I had!

Beware of the parking outside however as they are waiting to ticket. Not the restaurants fault but I think the parking should be complementary for lunch and not just dinner.

Great service, location, decor, service, ambiance, food. (Almost) Nothing to complain about. All staff have a great smile and are very helpful! Food is definitely worth the price paid. We dined at the private room...originally we were placed in the center of the main dining area, because when we made the booking, the private rooms were supposedly not available (it seems that the room is available but reservations did not call us back to inform) - this meant we had to wait (only about) five minutes for them to set up the whole private dining room area for a seating of 10 people. Very impressive speed and service. Also, all staff were able to explain the dishes, which is a very rare thing nowadays (come on, there are servers in this world that still don't know what soup of the day is).
Quaint cozy dining atmosphere. Elevated French cuisine. Great service. Well worth the hefty price tag.

One of the nicest restaurants in the city. For those downtown it's worth the commute. Everything about it is great. Service and food are top notch and the atmosphere and decor are spectacular.  Perfect for a di her with your significant other

Our first trip to the restaurant was amazing (from food to level of service to the amazing atmosphere). However, the last visit was awful and we had one of the worst experience in the level of service for our wedding anniversary.

The waiter simply never even bothered to fill our waters, check in on the food, completely ignored us. Even at the very end, when we tried to pay, the server took a good 30 minutes just going back-and-forth for the bill and bringing the credit card machine. It was a weeknight and the restaurant was not busy at all, there were only maybe 2-3 other tables.

Let's just say, we will never return to this restaurant again. For a restaurant of this price range, the level of service was simply, pathetic.

On Dupont. Who could imagine a
place like this one?
I love this small restaurant. Decoration is really interesting and unique. Most importantly, They offer the best pizza in town. It is as good as those one i...

Wow. This is the stuff.  This is the hidden gem of an area that is rather lack luster.  

Aviv is hidden away in a somewhat regrettably run-down area near...
We had our team dinner here. The restaurant was very accommodating to our needs. The food was amazing as well! Recommended for a group or romantic night out

Had a great experience.   The atmosphere was great and the food awesome.  The beet salad was great as was there traditional breakfast that my friend had.  And to cap it off, the Ontario Blueberry gelato - home made was a great ending to a wonderful afternoon meal.

Great atmosphere and staff. Amazing food! I got the lamb and beef flatbread and the triple decker gill cheese, both were amazing and that grilled cheese was just something else! And the price for everything great and actually affordable! I definitely recommend this place if your in the area.

So tasty!! We had calamari, risotto balls and the pizza with ribs on top and loved every bite. Very friendly staff and a great atmosphere for lunch, dinner or just a drink. Very fair prices.  A must try restaurant!
The pizzas are great. Owner is very friendly, kind and prompt ; as are the staff. Good to go with big groups.

reviews.text: Excellent service from staff!  Mohammed was amazing - professional and polite. Ran the hostess who helped organized did an amazing job and was so accommodating.
Nice place in the intercontinental hotel. Food is very good, but very pricey. Good serving staff.

Came to Azure during Summerlicious for dinner with my girlfriend, and had a great experience.

We ordered the Old Fashioned and Maple Manhattan to start,...

Food was okay. Ordered crab parfait and the crab was a little fishy - wouldn’t recommend. Also had beef tenderloin which was over-cooked and did not have any blue cheese. Don’t think I’d come back but it was decent enough. had a very attentive server.

The best restaurant services in town.  The smile starts from the host and the fine services and hospitality from the waiter.  They are not only knowledgeable about their profession, but also show their passion to help people like me new to the city.  Thanks Ran and Mesfin !!

The food was great!  Especially the dessert!  The portion size was perfect for me (I don't eat too much), so I didn't have to feel guilty for being unable to finish a meal.  The service was also on point.  My partner and I arrived at the restaurant an hour early and wanted to have a stroll down the street but didn't want to lug our stuff our with us.  The restaurant staff were gracious enough to allow us to put our stuff in the back and pick it up after dinner.
Food was excellent and they were very attentive on the service.
Service and ambiance were amazing. The food (at least from the Summerlicious menu) was good but, nothing stands out screaming amazing.

lic_profile: Housed in a historical building, Bangkok Garden is one of the first restaurants to introduce traditional Thai cuisine and culture to Toronto over 30 years ago, and is acclaimed as one of North America's premier Thai restaurants. One of only four Toronto restaurants to be awarded the Thai Select Premium designation from the Thai government, recognizing authenticity of food and outstanding service, Bangkok Garden serves food based on the Thai principle of balancing the five tastes: sweet, hot, sour, salty and bitter, including fiery stir fry and flavourful curries. The bar offers a large selection of exotic cocktails, international beers and an extensive wine list.

reviews.text:
I was not sure by the 3 star rating, but I am glad I tried this place. 

The food was amazing. I started with the Tom Kha Gai soup and it was delicious....
We came here for lunch Buffet. They have one section for cold dishes: glass noodle salad, mango Jicama salad, fresh roll, chicken wings, Thai spring rolls....

Had such high expectations for this spot based on how much I drooled just looking at the summerlicious menu. 
Listen. I love Thai food but this did not do...

I went to this restaurant with friends on December 31, 2017. It was my first time there and I loved it. The staff were very friendly and the service was about the best I have experienced. Once seated I took a good look around. Simply beautiful. Clearly a great deal of thought and work went into creating such a wonderful space. As I sat there I began to notice the wonderful aromas of the different dishes which served to tease and excite. It is a great space to sit and enjoy with great friends. I ordered the Chicken Coconut Soup, Cashew Chicken with Rice and for dessert a Chocolate Mousse. The various courses were served to all guests at the same time (something that I feel is important and sadly often lacking in many restaurants these days). We all got to enjoy and share each course together. The food was fantastic. In fact I can say it was the best Thai food I have ever had.  What a pleasant dining experience and night out. What a great find in downtown Toronto. I highly recommend this restaurant and will definitely return again and again.

I am right here having food and I ordered Red curry with vegetables and Tofu. Food arrived but high on salt. I requested for it to be replaced and chef added more coconut milk to it to balance and when it arrived back, it tasted like milk and not curry. I was so disappointed. I requested them to make it again and not just add mil to balance, I was told that it will come out again the same way, high salt because of the proportions they use. Wow....finally I had to change my order to spicy fish which was average and by that time I had lost my appetite. Overall a sad evening. You come to a good place for food and all you get is disappointment on a Friday night. I will not go back again. Sonia
Awesome food. Had the dinner for 2 fixed meal and it was great.  Spring rolls were awesome, soup had great spice levels, pad thai was the bomb. Oh ya, and the service was good too

We ate at this restaurant for the first time on August 21, 2017 with our 10 and 8 year old. We would go back again the next time we visit Toronto. If your a parent who encourages your child to discover different types of foods, there kids menu is awesome!  My son ordered their pad Thai and my daughter their yellow curry, and both were adjusted for their more sensitive palettes in terms of heat. It's the best Thai restaurant I've ever went to in terms of catering to families.   The atmosphere is cool too.

I had the every day wet noodles and they were amazing. The service was very friendly and the atmosphere was nice. The plate was full and I had to pack up half the meal tip take home. They had a full range of spiciness from none to extremely hot, and the food was very flavorful. The dessert was wonderful (we split the chocolate & chili mousse and the coconut creme brulle). I'd recommend this place to anyone, and I'm sure I'll be back.

lic_profile: Bannock's menu is reflected in its eclectic and approachably Canadian architecture, featuring antique pine and hemlock reclaimed from one of the Queen's wharfs that sat under the waters of Lake Ontario at York Street for over a hundred years.  Bannock's honest approach to food is rooted in familiar, wholesome ingredients that represent Canada's rich regional and cultural diversity, delivered in an innovative and playful way.  Everyday classics are revitalized as the chefs pay homage to traditional Canadian comfort foods, putting our cultural favourites front and centre.

reviews.text:
We came for an earlier dinner on a Monday night and had our pick of the tables. Our server was friendly and had plenty of recommendations on the menu. 

We...
Bannock is really busy so the service can be hit or miss depending on the night.  It was a hit for us tonight.  There was a definite buzz in the dining room...
I went to Bannock for dinner on Thursday evening with a group of 3 people. I ordered the margherita pizza (pretty good, cheese was good quality and flavour...

Bannock is really busy so the service can be hit or miss depending on the night.  It was a hit for us tonight.  There was a definite buzz in the dining room and people seemed in the holiday spirit.  We had made a reservation for 6 and arrived on time but it took another 10-15 minutes for them to have the table ready for us.  We were kept warm and toasty by the roar of the kitchen heat that was streaming from the open kitchen.

I started with the Throwback Thursday drink specials of the night and the Manhattan hit the spot.  The O&B cream of mushroom soup was warming and tasty.  Moved onto my entree of the wood-fired oven pizza special of the day. It was done just fine and the pizza crust was thin and crispy.

Our server was really nice and chatted us up during the meal.

I think you can have a good time here although my expectations and experience of the place don’t really match with the menu prices.
Love this place! I have come here a few times and the food is always excellent. Really cool twists on Canadian classics. Servers are helpful and friendly. I will continue to visit here :)

Dec 9 2017, Eating with siblings I got to sample all the dishes.  Before anything about them, I should say the service was really superb and the big room is nicely appointed.  On to the food: Caesar salad - good- healthy, mostly kale, and dressing-free: be careful if want you want is the usual gunky resto version.  Arctic Char- a disappointment.  I didn't particularly care for the fish - seemed a little 'fishy' and otherwise flavourless, and I was turned off by the very, VERY, earthy-flavoured beets.  These are the beets of my youth and I still hate that taste, though in counterpoint my sister said she really liked them.  The broth it all lay in seemed flavourless and just made me ask, 'why?'. Mushroom shepherd's pie - this pie seemed to be entirely made of whipped potatoes, with the mushroom being the crust (?), or lost in the potato, or entirely absent. Anyway, not good.  The winner by all acclaim was the pork chop, very tastily-breaded and large, with decent scalloped potato and mushrooms.

Bannock has great comfort foods and an enjoyable environment. The location is great as well if you have after dinner plans, you can basically get anywhere in the city from it. The wine was slightly overpriced, for both a full bottle and by the glass, but that would be the only downside.

The service at Bannock is amazing. The waiter would check in frequently to make sure we were satisfied and was very friendly. The food was satisfactory, nothing amazing. The quality of the specific dishes I had were not the best, including the margherita pizza and squash pasta.

reviews.text:
Based of the reviews I can see a lot of inconsistency in this restaurant. Luckily for me I had a good experience. 

The food is pricey. But let's face it,...

Tried this place last month with my husband. 
We are both Persian, so decided to try a new restaurant and we were so unhappy. 

With my meal I did not get a...
We walked by the other day and decided to give it a try :) my boyfriend is Persian and his mother is a decent cook, so we are a little spoiled when it comes...

Vodka drinks a must try in this place - unique, original combination and smooth. I had my B-day celebration here with my best friend - food was amazing. First time I tried their food I was impressed, came back in this restaurant several times - Brought in friends visiting from the States they enjoyed and loved the food. Service was excellent warm and welcoming. Its a beautiful day in Toronto! thanks Banu

It does not get any better than this. Top quality ingredients. Can't believe people can put down such good quality food because of price. YOU GET WHAT YOU PAY FOR PEOPLE!!! Great ambiance. Amazing service. If you want $10 kebab go to Yonge St made by some guy smoking a cigarette. Get real and realize what a gem this place is.
Best Persian food in Toronto. Everything is super gas. The owner is the head chef and a beauty. Highest quality meat in the city. Don’t sleep.

Food was amazing. The meat was like marshmallows it was so tender. My friend had the vegan stew and although I am a meat lover, I really enjoyed it also. I don't generally like eggplants and when I told the server that she insisted I try theirs and brought me some on the house - it was so smoky and rich. I loved the vibe in here too, it seemed like all the tables knew each other or something and you felt like you were in somebody's house rather than a restaurant. Their drinks were really really good also. Would highly recommend this place.
Very chic restaurant with great service. Food tasted amazing, they had beautiful presentation, and the portions were perfect. I definitely recommend this place.

lic_profile: Bar Buca is an Italian-style eatery where one can begin their day over house made pastries and perfectly prepared specialty coffee. Throughout the day, guests can enjoy Executive Chef Rob Gentile's creative menu of small dishes which changes seasonally to reflect Bar Buca's commitment to sourcing fresh, authentic ingredients. A unique, carefully crafted cocktail list of Italian classics, alongside a thorough wine list including 21 selections by the glass, complete every meal.

Whether seated on Bar Buca's intimate front patio or inside the dining room with a view into the electric energy of the open kitchen, guests will appreciate its mix of industrial aesthetics with classic materials. The combination of inspired design and a finely curated drinks list and menu makes Bar Buca a Toronto favourite with patrons and critics alike.

I've been here twice now, and both times: post-gym + almost walked past it + went through the awkward exchange of "sitting wherever there's a space but...

Fantastic hidden gem. Unfortunately, I live right across the street. So.. its my best friend. From the espresso early in the morning to the late night comfort food, there is a lot of attention to detail with anything they make. I also like the atmosphere. Its quiet, friendly, and the perfect size. The staff is pretty cool as well. They close really late, so good if you need a late night drink. Busiest times would be late morning or late evening. They make a mean Manhattan, with some smooth bourbon.

We called when we were 5 minutes away to see if any tables were available, not really expecting much. To our chagrin "Josh" said that many tables were about to open up. 10 minutes later we waltz in the door and we're told there is a substantial wait. Fine. But "Josh" said, "It's gonna be a long wait. That's the game. But you can hang out if you want." I'll never go back. I don't expect to get a table immediately, but I do expect to treated with respect. No thanks.

One of the best bangs for your buck. Incredible food for a reasonable price. It's a small plates type place, but the quality overwhelmingly makes up for it. Split 3 plates between the 2 of us and were plenty full!

Fantastic brunch! Everything we ate tasted phenomenal - loved the truffle eggs and porchetta sandwich. The steak was good but not out of this world like the other two dishes. Staff was friendly! Will come again and I can’t wait!

Great staff, atmosphere, eats and drinks. Was seated right away for dinner and drinks. Hung out in the bar for a long time without feeling like the staff wanted us to leave. Server was very considerate and patient of my allergies and gave great suggestions in drinks and food. Totally loved the experience.

The manager (owner?) of the restaurant ruined the place for me - too demanding of staff and customers(!)...the place would be much better if she stayed hidden in the back.

reviews.text:
Came for brunch with a large party. Service had a lot more to he desired but food was delicious.

Staff: We had made a reservation but they only had one...
I passed by this place so many times, then decided to go in on a very cold snowy day looking to warm up on some good Latin food! Well, I wasn't warmed very...
I ordered 3 vegetarian tacos needing them to be as described on menu, ie-- with salsa verde, esquites and fried mushrooms. Instead I was given deep fried...

First, and most importantly, the food was incredible. Authentic hispanic cuisine, very flavourful, just enough spice, portions sizes were perfect! Service was great, our server was very attentive, came by the table at very appropriate times, we never felt rushed or bombarded. The ambience was perfect. Whether you're just enjoying cocktails, celebrating a birthday party or just having an intimate date/meeting, this place is perfectly cozy yet trendy. Highly recommended!

Great Place for Brunch! Friendly wait staff and awesome food. Coming from Texas this place reminded us of home. The guacamole dip and freshly made chips hit the spot. The breakfast burrito was extremely good. The Rancheros were also very tasty. Definitely a great Mexican food spot on Queen Street.

First time for myself and a friend, heard good things so we gave it a shot. Bad move. Got there and wan't busy so thought it would be a good night. Was seated by one person, another brought us water and both claimed they would be taking care of us, confusing as to who to place an order with. (no alcohol menu online either) Beers were brought to the table without pint glasses (had to go to the bar and ask for some) Staff was attentive at first but went downhill from there. The male server seemed more concerned about sitting at the bar and playing with his phone. After finally getting his attention and wanting to order our meals, we were told they were now on the late night menu. Luckily tacos were part of the late night menu. We were ten told they were closing at ten when website says open late, I hardly think 10pm on a Thursday is late. Food was about the only bright spot, although they had to double check our order to make sure. Once and never again.

Fantastic place that goes for that 'down south' fibe.  I love to hit the patio here late at night during the summer.  Great lighting provided by hundreds of incandescent bulbs and space heaters galore means this place is perfect.  I love the margaritas and recommend the cheaper of the two, the only difference being the tequila quality.  Make sure you get the guacamole!

The food, ambiance and service were all excellent when we dropped in on a random Wednesday night. It was a bit quieter because of the cold (generally I have always seen this restaurant well-packed), but the music and mood were both great. The octopus and chorizo dish was particularly noteworthy, well conceived and well executed, with a wonderful blend of flavours. I will be coming back.

I feel mixed about Batch. We showed up on a Saturday night for drinks only. The ambiance and decor were lovely. It wasn't too full or noisy.  

I tried a...

The place looks great from the outside and in, upstairs is really sharp looking with a beautiful bar and nicely set up tables set for brunch. Downstairs was dim and looking a little messy, maybe from a busy Friday night. Bathrooms were clean and well maintained. Food and drinks were well overpriced for what they were, my salad had a generous thick spread of yogurt on the bottom with beats, nuts mixed lettuces for $16, I added salmon for $6 (chicken was$8) I had a Caesar $10, it was pretty bland and came garnished with a lime and lemon wedge, even the salt on the rim was lackluster, I don't need a bean or a pickle but can a brother get a celery stalk? Service was excellent, always keeping our water full even after our meal when we chatted for a bit. I don't think I'll be back to eat but they do have table tennis downstairs so there's always a chance

Nice atmosphere and interior.  Good selection of beers, and you can grab a bottle with you. The food is 3/5. Service is just ok. They do have a ping long table downstairs but it's Way too dark to play, unless you have a night vision device. Generally pretty decent.

Good choice in the Yonge and Richmond area for lunch or dinner. Good menu with a nice treatment of pub classics like fried chicken and fish and chips. Nice satisfying of craft beers brewed on site. 

It has a convenient room in the basement that will fit up to 60 people for a team meeting and they serve an excellent buffet for lunch meetings for a very reasonable price.

Went here recently for a dinner party.  Our group was about 30 people.  The restaurant was dead otherwise.  It took +3h for our meal.  Service was incredibly slow.  Food was just ok, and because it took so long to come out, it was warm not hot.  Then to top it all off on large groups they add 18.5% gratuity.   I wouldn't go back.

The beers were good while the mixed drinks were ok. Didn't get to try the food though. Staff were nice but took a really long time time before checking on us and when we wanted our bill. Past that, no issues. Would go again.

3.5 stars for now. 

I've been coming here since opening week and this place has it's ups and downs. My first time here (3 days after opening) was fabulous,...

Time: Saturday night
Ambiance: Poor 
Food: Good quality and portion size
Service: very good, server was really attentive, did not have good food knowledge...

Honestly, I didn't think I would like it. I though it'd be a pretentious place since it's at Saks but in honesty the wait staff was very friendly and welcoming. They always asked if anything was needed and had a warm smile on their faces.

My wife order the burger as did I while my mother-in-law ordered the roasted beet appetizer and baby spinach salad. Everything was delicious and we were all pleased with our orders.

The burger that I order was small compared to some other places but it was thick and very juicy. Yes, it can be considered "pricey" but considering where you are it's not too bad. The burger was simple but tasty and perhaps one of the top ones I've ever had. It was moist and flavourful with a little pink in the middle... give it a try, you won't regret it.

Our waitress, Madison, was extremely nice and we never felt rushed to leave even though our meal was over and our billed paid. She even gave my mother-in-law a free dessert for her birthday even though she didn't want to order one because she was stuff. It even had Happy Birthday written in chocolate. Seriously, Madison was awesome. Thanks for a great night!
Scallops were perfectly cooked. Best I've had. Cocktails were great as well.
We has a great lunchtime. Everyone enjoyed food and service.

The food has good flavour and texture, but is about 15% too salty. I had the Avocado Scotch Egg with Mushroom Soup. The egg was really good. Lightly battered with slices of bacon surrounding the avocado, perfect egg. My wife had the burger with fries. Can't speak for the burger, but the fries are very good, perfectly crunchy. The only negative is that all of the food is slightly over salted.
Had their Sunday Brunch. Delicious and their PBJ French Toast thing was AMAZING. A bit pricey. Spent 40.00 a person. But what do you expect...

It felt like they served us food that was old and just trying to clear inventory before they close the doors.

lic_profile: A Japanese steakhouse experience in the heart of Toronto, Benihana lets you enjoy the excitement of teppan cooking right at your table.  Instead of using conventional kitchens, Benihana's highly skilled chefs present and prepare the freshest beef, seafood and produce at a 'hibachi' table (a flat 4'x 3' grill), around which, up to eight guests are seated. A fast-paced performance of chopping and juggling creates an exciting teppanyaki-style dining experience for guests of all ages.

reviews.text:
I gave 5 stars because everything was tasty and perfect. 
We had Toto as a chef and he made cooking fun and super interesting.
Sushi is very good
My...
Great place to celebrate your birthday, anniversary and any special day in your life! Although it's a little bit expensive for students, but once in a while...
We visited Benihana for summerlicious, and i was disappointed.  At first entry, the decor reminds me of 80's restaurant with amber wood and fabric chairs....

Great teppanaki experience to be seated in front of the chef as we were entertained as the food was being cooked.  Be prepared to share the "table" with strangers if your party is not large enough to fill the "table" - the willingness of the other guests to be engaged with the chef can influence how entertained you'll be.  Food quality was good and quantity was ample but, unfortunately, not unique.  What does set this place apart is it's ambience and the service.

Great place to celebrate your birthday, anniversary and any special day in your life! Although it's a little bit expensive for students, but once in a while doesn't hurt much and it's totally worth it! The atmosphere is great, the chef makes great effort to entertain customers while cooking the food in front of everyone. It's a very unique experience to have in Toronto! Also if you go on your birthday/anniversary, the restaurant will prepare a free dessert (either chocolate cake or cheese cake) for you, very good service! I had their cheese cake, I'd say I made the right choice! Will come back for sure! 👍🏼

The wait was long for our main course and our chef didn't really perform anything impressive. Beef was excellent and everything else was mediocre. I would rae this higher but the wait for a food was long. Definitely overpriced for the experience.

Decent food, but terribly overpriced. Sure its a chain - but there are so many GOOD and GREAT teppanyaki spots downtown, why would you spend all this for cookie cutter experience?? head up to Dundas west to Don Don Izakaya or the like for a much better dining / atmosphere experience.

Overpriced and very bland food,our friends tenderloin was ridiculously undercooked as well. I would not recommend this restaurant for how expensive it is. Extremely disappointing experience ,if I'm going to spend that kind of money at a place I would expect much better.

Great Italian. Fresh made pasta was served al Dante  and the porcini cream sauce, delicious.  Filet beef was well cooked, juicy and had a wonderful sauce....

Really nice old school feel to the place. The original owner combs the dining room and is very engaged in the service. The waiters we had were so friendly. We had our three year old with us and they made every effort to make her as happy as possible. The food  was delicious and the wine list is extensive. Though it was our first time there it seemed the majority of the customers were regulars which added to the charm. Overall a great experience and we will return for the ice cream at the very least.

Summary: SLOW, bad appetizers, but good steak and kind employees.

For a corporate holiday party, we arrived at 5 pm for drinks. In the beginning they only had one type of drink, but eventually we were able to order different kinds of drinks. 

Dinner was scheduled to start at 7 pm, but we weren't served until 7:30 pm. The pasta looked and tasted like it was made by children ... just penne and plain sauce. Eventually at 9 pm, we got steak, and it was great. 

The employees were very kind.
The food is amazing. Service is excellent. And the wine cellar is beautiful. Definitely check this place out if you haven't been

Big Crow offers one of the most unique dining experiences in the city. Tucked behind the Rose and Sons diner, Big Crow is nestled in a small shed at the end...
Big Crow is tucked behind Rose and Sons restaurant. Just follow the big sign FOOD and walk around the side of the building to the back. Use your nose and...

Went here for a surprise birthday party my friends organized for me. Let me just say having a big group was a good idea here. We paid for a set menu and oh boy did they deliver! We couldn't move after the meal. We got a huge assortment of meats and dishes. The rotating taps were pretty good as well. I loved the gourmet backyard bbq style of the food and even the decor. We loved the fact that they played classic rock too, totally fit the vibe. Only recommendation would be to dress warm; the heaters weren't strong enough to heat the entire place. Great place, highly recommended!

We went on a Saturday night with a reservation. The food was great and our server recommended some great dishes. The place itself is behind Rose and Sons and is supposed to feel like a cabin. Its a wonderful concept, just a tad chilly in -20 degree weather. There were space heaters and blankets and it really wasnt that bad. The smoked meat dishes were to die for. Its best to go in medium sized groups as all the plates are meant to share and it can get pretty pricey as a twosome.

Amazing place. Hard to find, but well worth the search. The hunt for the place is part of the experience. Food was to die for. They source their drinks (most) locally. Great staff. Ambiance was spectacular. Far exceeds expectations of the first time visitor. Washrooms are in another building. Might get cold some times.

Had an offsite work meeting in their enclosed back patio Friday afternoon. Their Special Events and Catering Manager, Desiree was an absolute pleasure to work with. She was prompt in responding to emails and outlined all costs in detail. When we arrived, Desiree and Vanessa, set up our Projector (I had no idea what I was doing) and stuck around to help hand out Welcome Cocktails (Kentucky Mule) to the attendees and ensure everything was in order. Desiree checked in to make sure everything was to our satisfaction before her night ended and left us in the competent hands of her servers. Staff were friendly and attentive throughout. This place knocked the food out of the park! I wish I took pictures. The staff raved about everything from the ribs to the cornbread and to my surprise, continued to order the Kentucky Mules well into the evening. I highly recommend this establishment, especially for large groups. This team runs like a well oiled machine. You will not be disappointed!

Big crow is a hidden gem in Toronto! Immediately after sitting down it feels like I've been transported to a cottage with the sweet smell of barbeque in the air. Impeccably served in an upscale dining room with warmly lit stone walls, grand mirrors, and cozy leather seating, and enhanced by soothing live music Friday and Saturday, dinner is a truly memorable experience.

Their brunch!

If you’re looking for a brunch place AND can take reservation, this is not a bad restaurant to check out. The menu is very simple and offers some good options for brunch/lunch. If you have a big party or if you have kids, this is also a good restaurant to consider. Especially when you want more space, this venue can offer you a lot of space for your party.

I came out satisfied with their brunch but I wouldn’t go here if you’re looking for something unique for brunch. It’s just a good gathering place for your friends and family for lunch/brunch though!

We have been to so many restaurants in Toronto, and didn't think there was one that could impress us with food (besides Au Berge, etc) - but Bymark was a delightful surprise. We loved the quiet atmosphere, elegant, slow but great service, and meals that were finally a notch above the rest. This is a restaurant we have now tried twice, and loved every dish we have been served. And we are hard to please! PS. the first night we went, the waiter was not great, but food was so good, we tried it again. Had a great waitress, and an overall terrific night. We will return again!

reviews.text: Visited Cactus Club and had a great experience! I only gave a 4 star due to it being so busy that our server was MIA for a little bit. Otherwise, the food...

It's amazing how consistent Cactus Club is with their food. I would go to Cactus almost every week in Vancouver, especially during the summer.

My...

Let me start by stating "CACTUS CLUB in Toronto is HORRIBLE HORRIBLE PLACE!!!

We booked a reservation for tonight - Dec 16, 2017 dinner for a party of 10...

Probably the best service I've ever had at any place I've been to. They struggled to get my steak just right, came out a little too well done around the outside and I unfortunately had to send it back and wait for another one. It took a little while, but they made sure I wasn't hungry and gave me a plate of food - for free, mind you - whilst I waited. When we had finished our meal, and the bill came, they did not charge me and apologized profusely for the steak. Didn't NOT want to pay - as the food was delicious! - so offered to tip instead. Will definitely be returning, with many people on many more occasions and recommending this to everyone I can. The staff was so, so lovely! Vibe is amazing, too. Only negative is the wait time but honestly, it was worth waiting an hour and half for the customer service and quality of food.

A modern eclectic dining experience that serves great cocktails and food options.

Lovely atmosphere with a decent sound system.  The food here was terrifically balanced.  We had the happy hour apps (loved the truffle fries, sliders and fish tacos).

We had slightly iffy service at first but then switched servers and it got much better.  So, I seems that if you luck out and get a good server, you can have a good experience.

The atmosphere is the main reason as to why I gave this place the full 5 stars. The music is better than that at any bar I've been to (doesn't suit the theme of the restaurant though) and the movie reel playing in the background was very tasteful (Bruce lee's game of death). 
The drinks are very pricey considering that 90% of it was just ice but the wine selection was adequate. 
The duck confit was nothing special but the braised lentils were definitely good enough for me to revisit the dish. 
Waitresses and staff were also super friendly. Overall, I'd recommend this place for a date, certainly a place you need to try at least once.

I had actually gone here with a large group +7, and it was great. Delicious food, arrived at timely manner, very posh. However, this would have been a 5 star review if the music was slightly quieter, I felt I had lost my voice the next day trying to yell to be heard. I also found the servings weren't that filling, even with amount we ordered. I'm a petite person and found even I wanted at least another side, but for the price we paid no one should have felt wanting more. The thing that left everything on a slightly sour note was when it came to ordering dessert. We were celebrating a birthday and not only did we order ALOT of food but we each also ordered dessert, and most places I've been the birthday persons dessert is on the house, but even if it wasn't I wouldn't be too bothered (hey every place is different). However our waitress on MULTIPLE occasions kept saying 'that dessert isn't free, we have a complimentary birthday dessert which is a small chocolate treat of some kind (I've attached a picture)' which we said was fine but we also wanted the desserts regardless if they're complimentary or not. To which she kept saying 'but we won't be paying for that.' Perhaps there have been issues before with people assuming the desserts would be free, but after we've agreed, you need to take our order and just give us the food. Instead it was a 10 minute back and forth on explaining we just want to satisfy our sweet tooth regardless of the cost. The food was definitely 5 stars, atmosphere and staff could use some work, and maybe a smidge more of the sides.

Came here for a fun night out with a friend. Drinks and lettuce wrap were great. However the staff was very aggressive in making us finish out drinks, our food and kicking us out at 1:30 am. At one point, the lights went on we were given a 2 minute warning at 1:40  to chug our drinks and was told we would be forced to exit soon. This was right after our server asking if we wanted another drink. Why ask for last call if you are going to kick people out right after.
Definitely do not recommend or coming back ever. Will make sure to tell all my coworkers and friends ds to avoid the area. Horrible experience here at cactus club. Looking forward to seeing what you have to say.

reviews.text:
I have been 5 times to café boulud this year. I spent my bachelorette party, my birthday, my mother's birthday here. 
It is definitely my top go to fine...

This is a sister restaurant from NYC cafe bouloud which I regularly go to . 

Pros : location is great . Ambiance is ok . Servers are ok 

Food : ok nothing...
I was fortunate enough to be able to attend a special event at Cafe Boulud on Oct 27, where Daniel Boulud was joined by executive chefs from various other...

A top notch brunch experience in every respect: from convenient online booking, though to service, food, and ambience. We were here for midweek breakfast and thoroughly enjoyed ourselves. My hubby’s omelet was not very inspired, but neither was there anything wrong with it- and seeing as that’s the most critical thing we can say about the whole experience that’s saying something. Lemon ricotta pancakes were superb and coffee was very well made (plus the beans are a very nice non-acidic blend). A wonderful place for a date or special occasion.

Beautiful ambiance; decor set a beautiful tone. Greeting us by our reservation name was a lovely touch!

However, service was rushed and drinks were very poor. 

We all work hard for our money and at 15$ per glass, I feel anyone is deserving of a well chilled, properly presented beverage from all means and walks of life. My drink was served in the wrong glass - not necessarily a big deal, but then it was simply poured into another glass with the ice removed rather than a chilled glass. These days, if you're a mixologist and charge me like I owe you child support, I figured to expect some knowledge and care. Also, I saw film floating  around in the drink due to the warmth of the beverage. It was simply a bit gross. At that point I didn't say anything because I was already disheartened and felt as an inconvenience to the staff. 

Our server seemed rushed and spent no time to ask us about the drink after asking for it to be changed - not really throughout our meal, now that I think about it, either.

Pickup staff, those who delivered our food or brought garnishes and sides, were absolutely fantastic and friendly!

Unfortunately, would not visit again.

We went to Cafe Boulud for a work event. They made very nice cocktails here and had a nice selection of fine. I had the lamb shank which was very tender. Most people went with the steaks and they were all cooked to their liking. Dessert blew us away. One had a grapefruit with cotton candy and I had a chocolate lava cake to die for.

Came here for my birthday dinner with family in the summer under recommendation from my brother. Served us, a party of 12 with allergies and all impeccably, food was outstanding and definitely worth the price which is great for the area. Will definitely be back.

Good quality riffs on classic French bistro dishes.  High prices make this place  poor value but the upscale setting suits many special events very well.  Professional service marred by relentless up selling.

Cafe California was suggested by a friend to go to for a Summerlicious lunch.  Am glad i got to experience it.
For apprtizer, i got the Cafr California...

Came here for Winterlicious on a Friday and this place was pretty busy but you can still find a spot without reserving.

Quality of food: 4/5 

I think the...
Just stopped in for a glass of wine and they brought us a lovely complimentary antipasto plate. Staff are always so nice here.

The quality of the food isn't the same as before.The service sucks, you always have to keep asking for basic things like salt & pepper, ketchup, more coffee or water. etc. The kitchen always mess up what you ordered and just can't maintain a consistency in the food they serve. Also, before drinking your coffee make sure to check if there's no lipstick mark on the edge of your cup because they don't wash it properly.
The waiters seem to not even bother with the bad service anymore .. if you complain about something they ironically apologize. I decided not to come back to this place anymore. I really miss the old Café California. It's a shame because they have a great location and a nice patio.

Food and service is amazing. Bob P. The manager has done an absolutely amazing job is making CC much better. We were a group attending for late afternoon cocktails and snacks. All was very good. We will be back soon

Went for lunch as part of the Summerlicious promotion.  Lunch for 2 plus tip plus 1/2 litre of wine was $80. Cafe California is in the heart of Toronto's Gay Village - it's a pleasant place but nothing stood out for me.  Food was good (although my companion's medium-rare steak was close well done), service was spotty (they needed more staff).  If I lived in the neighborhood I'd visit occasionally but I'd never make a special trip to eat there.

This restaurant has been nothing but mediocre and cheap looking both inside and out for years. How they survive is a complete mystery to almost everyone. There's nothing especially great about the food, the service is off and on and it's empty most of the week.

reviews.text:
Absolute gem of a restaurant! Food was amazing and the view was beautiful. 
Food portions were a little small but other than that, they tasted great and had...
Made a reservation but still had to wait maybe 10 to 15 minutes for a table, despite being after the lunch rush. A bit pricey for lunch, but it's expected...

Note that I didn't actually eat at Canoe but this is my experience making a reservation for Winterlicious 2018. 

Canoe may be the one restaurant that I...

We had an amazing first experience together from start to finish. Service was impeccable and friendly. We brought our own bottle of wine and did the tasting menu. Each dish was unique and presentation artistic to go along with our amazing window seat. The only dish that wasn't as balanced as the others was the dessert which was a unique tarragon sorbet. In hindsight we should have mixed this and it would have been perfect also.

We had an excellent evening at the Canoe bar (first) and restaurant (second). Great drinks, very good food, impeccable service and of course a breathtaking view. We thought the food a really excellent mixture of finesse and down-to-earth Canadian eating. Something that came out very well in each dish and the combined tastes. We recommend the mushroom soup (with a strong taste of truffles) and the heritage pork, rounded of with a Niagra peninsula Riesling.
Contrary to some of the more negative reviews here, our courses arrived very quickly (although the restaurant was full) and were certainly not too small.

The food was just amazing! Probably here I had the tastiest steak in my life. The view from the 54th floor is amazing. The staff so knowledgeable and pleasant. Since I visited Canoe it is my favourite restaurant in Toronto.

Was so excited to finally experience Canoe. I took my husband to celebrate his birthday. The service was impeccable, but the food was disappointing. For a "fine dining" experience, sure did not feel like it to my taste buds. For the price you are paying, you would think that this food would blow your mind, did not happen for us. Ended up paying a lot for the view and experience overall.

Atmosphere, food, service and view are all amazing.

This post is more tips for people that want to try canoe and not blow their budget and have an amazing experience.

Tip #1 make a reservation and pick a good time. This restaurant is busy, don't expect to get a window table for 4 at 6 pm on Friday night.  Find a time when the restaurant is more calm.

Tip #2 skip dinner go for lunch. It is almost the same menu and the prices are $15-20 less a plate.  The view is better during the day. My girlfriend and I went at 1:15 on a Thursday and got a window seat no problem.  The business crowd is just leaving at the time and from 1-230 it's get nice and quiet.

Tip #3: look for pictures and speak to your waiter about dishes and what you are looking for. We shared a large steak tartare for an appetizer. My gf had beef strips and I had Arctic char for main, we both tried each other's dishes and split a dessert and we were stuffed. 

Tip #4: wine and alcohol can be expensive. So if you are really looking to save skip the wine. If you still want to have a glass each order 9 ounce of wine, it will be about $27 and u can split that and each have a good size glass.

Tip #5: this is a true dining experience. Take your time, enjoy it. Don't be a critique while you are eating. Go in with an open mind and enjoy.

Hope this helped!

reviews.text: We had reservations for dinner at 6pm on a Friday. I was seeing a 7pm show at tiff and hubby and niece were seeing a show at nearby Royal Alexander...
This is a good spot for brunch and dinner. The food is solid and the decor leans toward clean lines and minimal sophistication. I'm bumping the rating to 4...
Where to begin. I'll start with the positive: the waitress was nice enough and the wine we ordered was good. On to the negative: everything else. Upon...

I really enjoy O&B restaurants and Canteen is no exception! We went with a large party and service was quick and the staff was very friendly. I made a ridiculous request for a drink and the server went up to three Luma bar to see if it could be accommodated (unfortunately it could not...). 

We ordered a pizza and babaganouj to share. They were delicious but we immediately regretting our decision when we saw how good the burger looked!

It is a lovely spot for a decently priced meal!

We came on thanksgiving eve. We had no reservations but were seated right away. Our server was great and took some time to explain menu options. The food came at a reasonable time. It was not fast but I really wouldn't like it if it was fast. Everything tasted very good and best of all they have lots of gluten free options.
Lovely chilled atmosphere and nice staff. Good brunch options and nice coffee. Oatmeal was delicious. Chia pudding was a nice healthy breakfast option but was quite sweet. Otherwise very nice!

Very nice staff who let me wait for my peers for over 30 minutes. I had the a peppermint tea and an eggplant pizza. Missing a star because the waitress rushed to deliver the bill to us and asked how we were going to pay when we had not asked for the bill yet. We were in the middle of our conversation.
While a little bit pricey (10 for some appetizers and up) its still a good place with decent service and close to public transit.
