Service: As always Canyon...
Went to the Canyon Creek restaurant on Front St for dinner. The restaurant is nicely decorated, but the dining area is very dark. It was difficult to see...

I was there with a friend on June 29.  We had made reservations and the 'check in' was smooth.
I found the location a bit dungeon-like, lol, but it was...

Pretty nice place. Usually go when it isn't busy or with reservations, so don't have much experience with wait times. 

Service is normally quite good with friendly staff willing to crack a joke or two. wait times for food aren't unreasonable, never waited over half an hour even for a large, medium well steak

Food itself is good quality, prices are 20-40 bucks for most meals. Steaks are probably a tad overpriced, but they at least have good flavour options compared to many other places. Not too good for the gluten sensitive though, most of their sauces contain some amount.

Came here for my birthday, service was absolutely incredible some of the most friendly and helpful wait staff I've ever. My waiter, I think his name was Jeff, was very knowledgeable of the menu and his recommendations were spot on. I had the pot roast (12oz aged 40 days) with a loaded baked potato on the side. I'm a pretty big guy in this completely filled me up, very good portion sizes. The cream of mushroom soup that I had as an appetizer was also delicious, I'd recommend that as well. For dessert I had the seasonal creme brulee which was very good. I personally hope to come back here, and I suggest you would as well.

I was really impressed with the food. The quality was great and there was a large selection to choose from. Atmosphere was also very nice! But I'm  a little concerned with the waitresses and their ability to listen. My girlfriend explained to our waitress that it was my birthday, and she responded with "congratulations!" - still trying to figure that one out

We had a lovely time at Canyon Creek. The place has a cozy feel to it, even though it was quite busy, we didn’t feel cramped. The food was absolutely superb. Both of our meals were incredible and the desert was great. The service was attentive and professional and the recommendations were spot on. We are extremely pleased with our experience and we look forward to coming back again.

Great service and staff. We were given excellent recommendations. All of our dishes were prepared with fresh ingredients.  Our group tried the Classic Fillet and the Ribeyes and we were very pleased with our choices.  The Peruvian Chicken Nachos are a must do. We loved them so much we ended up getting another plate. We ended the night with the brownie and ice cream as well as the rum and eggnog creme brulee. The waiter saw our request for a birthday celebration and brought a dessert with a candle without us even asking... that was a great touch. Will definitely come back when we visit Toronto.

lic_profile: With comfort at its heart, Capocaccia is a lighthearted and fresh take on trendy dining where guests can enjoy the very best of Italian cuisine. Towering ceilings and a multi-story wine rack puts a spotlight on every wine bottle. Deep-grained wood tables set up close together are lit softly to create an intimate bistro-style environment. Many regulars prefer sitting at our long bar or our high communal table, but you may choose the cozy tables or outside covered patio during the summer months. The chef puts Italian heart into every dish, from pizzas, pastas, antipasto and salads to the specials of the day.

reviews.text: Went out for a dinner meeting with a bunch of colleagues and found this place to be nice and cosy. The service was stellar! Tons of personal touch points,...
Went to this restaurant on a very cold Saturday night in January 2018.  When we entered I noticed we were the only people, other than servers, in the place....
Wow! This menu was incredible. Although I couldn't pronounce anything on it, I knew whatever I chose, I'd be happy with. I went during lunch hour and it...

Excellent food! We were party of 6, we chose some appetizers to share and each one had a main course. The food was high quality, tasty and fresh. The cocktails clean and the service impeccable. Will definitely be back.

Went here for a friend's birthday with a group of about 12. Good was delicious, portions were good sizes and the prices were fair. I found our server to be a bit annoyed with us since we took are time to choose our drinks but other than that no complaints.

The food was very tasty. We came here for our anniversary lunch with a gift card. The calamari was perfectly cooked - melt in your mouth. Servers were attentive except when it came to paying the bill (hence it lost 1 star in my review). Salmon was cooked perfectly - moist, not dry and paired well with a light cream sauce. Lavender panna cotta was deliciously paired with a berry compote. Nicely decorated and a good ambiance.

Outstanding Italian neighbourhood restaurant. Modern and bright interior and delicious food. Usually quite busy, which is always a good sign. Had the gnocchi and some other pasta dishes, was fantastic.
Located on a quiet section of Yonge Street, south of St. Clair.
I had a pasta dish that was on special and my bf had the pizza. We were both very happy with our choices. It's a little pricey but a nice place to go for a special occasion.

lic_profile: With stunning Tiffany lamps, stained glass windows, and wood-burning fireplaces, this 19th century Victorian Cottage known as Carmen's Steak House is that special combination of classic and comfort. The modernized menu is a compilation of locally sourced ingredients and features market fresh seafood and the best of Canadian and USDA prime steaks. With its notable wine list, unparalleled service and hospitality, Carmen’s truly is a neighbourhood gem.

reviews.text:
I'm absolutely in love with this great steakhouse in the city! What a great find.
I was here for summerlicious 2017 and will certainly be returning to try...

Most Memorable Feature: Intimate atmosphere

Steak and Tartare were a hit but the salmon was a very big miss.  It was blander than cardboard even with the...
Carmen's has a unique Victorian interior that can be a romantic place for dinner. Came here for summerlicious and ordered the French onion soup, steak, and...

It Is probably one of the best steak house in Toronto, the fireplace in the dinning room is just amazing ,the smell of burning wood and the food was just perfect. 
Definitely is the first place that i will go to dine in my next trip to Toronto.
Good ambiance.   Great steak... overpowering seasoning though

I got the steak from the fixed price menu (10oz New York strip). Came with choice of Salad or French Onion Soup and a dessert of Cheesecake or Creme Brulee. The french onion soup was average at best and I got tired of it half way through. The steak seemed like it was pan fried in vegetable oil and over salted. It was not appetising at all and I left a good portion of it on my plate. I got a baked potato as a side and again, just average. The cheesecake was good though and the only thing I finished. The service was pretty awful which was surprising considering the fact that the place was almost empty with the exception of 1 other table of 2 (we were a table of 6). The waiter forgot about drink orders and was generally not checking in. Finally, we got separate bills and only 1 of us paid with cash but yet somehow the restaurant wasn't able to give any change for $100 for a $65 bill. The waiter was gone forever and some of us wanted to leave but were still waiting to pay. Luckily someone from our party had change. Will never go back here. Not a quality steakhouse at all. Your better off going to the Keg.

Not a good experience in here. Ordered medium for the steak, but it was definitely over cook! When I paid the bill with my credit card, that waiter drop my card rudely!! I gave 12% tips, and all I got just basic service! I would never come again.

Fantastic meal.  Caeser salad was great, beautiful sauce, loved the bread and olives as well.  Steak cooked absolutely to perfection.  Baked potato was divine.  Dessert nearly beat me, but too good to leave anything, huge meal.  Great ambience as well.  An absolute 5 star experience.  Will definitely return.

lic_profile: Locally and internationally acclaimed as one of the best Filipino restaurants in Toronto, Casa Manila is the place to enjoy classical Filipino cuisine. Casa Manila's philosophy "Nature to Nurture" ensures authentic Filipino dishes are given a 21st century update to offer wholesome, healthy and fresh tasting food while honouring traditional home cooking. The menu reflects regional authentic cuisine - a blend of Indo, Malay, Spanish, Mexican, Chinese, Polynesian and indigenous Filipino flavours served in a charming, cultural atmosphere depicting the facets of the 7100 Philippine Islands.

reviews.text: The ambiance is nice plus the music is awesome. Feels like you're in the Philippines. Ordered the dinner combo, crispy pata, daing na bangus (milk fish) and...
Horrible place.  From the get go through out, the service was terrible.   Was seated and took forever to get acknowledged and when we did, we were asked for...

TERRIBLE. DO NOT COME TO THIS PLACE. 
We came at 7:20 and the food came out at 8:20. They served to people that came after us first. We asked if our foods...

Kayayan - a unique dining experience. Reserve ahead of time and order 24 hours before your arrival.  Food comes on a long platter covered in banana leaves.  Eat with your hands or with the wooden (instead of plastic) utensils. Flavours are different, a bit over-powered by the raw red onions but interesting.  Service is attentive, and all dishes are explained to diners.  Very unique decor. No need to fight for parking out front as their is plenty of parking around the back and in the under-ground parking.

Had one of the set meals ($40).  Know that you're basically paying to eat (at best) food court food on a banana leaf.

Was a fun experience.  Service was friendly, but slow.  Food was a pile of rice with a few scraps of mediocre meat and seafood.

Dishes that were not part of the set menu looked great though.  Table was also charged 20% grat automatically.

I've been here twice. The first time with a group, and that experience was horrible. Took forever to catch someone's eye to be seated (and it was not busy) and the food took more than an hour to arrive. 

My second visit was much better. Food came promptly and service was attentive. If you like fried Filipino cuisine - this is your haven!
Great food and atmosphere. The kamayan was good and filling. Staff is friendly and helpful and provided instructions clearly before we started. Would recommend.

First time writing a review. Although I don’t like to write bad reviews, since I normally just avoid the place after a bad experience, I dislike the fact that they get so many stars for their food quality and services. I ate there during late lunch hours, notably my husband and I the only customer, but still the food took forever to arrive. We both order the same drink (with alcohol) and my husband required a soda, drink arrive with no alcohol just a Virgin and no soda at all. Food was bland, no salt and pepper for taste. Pork chewy and more layers of fat than meat. Ox tails in peanut was just heat up in microwave, peanut sauce is bland. Rice is lukewarm at best, not streaming hot. Again, why not salt and pepper the chicken wings before batter and fried. That’s the basic. I’m Vietnamese so I regards street food often cheap and filling, although this is not Vietnamese food most Asian country run the same concept. But this restaurant over charge 2x more for worst quality than a take out Chinese food. Anyway I apologize if it’s too harsh but it’s just annoying that we had to seat through the whole dining experience.

reviews.text:
Well I've been here before years ago but I don't recall much except that the food was good.
very fresh seafood is on the menu.  I had a mastercard special...

From the summerlicous menu: 

Cod fish cakes (can't remember the exact name of the dish): they were unimpressive and tasted like a mix between a potato...
If you are looking for a sophisticated Portuguese restaurant this is a great option. Their wine selection is fantastic and the fresh fish selection is...
Classic, old school and great service. Best wines in Toronto for sure. A bit expensive, I mean really expensive, but it's a Toronto institution for sure.

Incredible experience. I haven't had tastier, fresher, or more skillfully prepared seafood in Toronto. The wines were fantastic, and I was delighted at the fact that several were offered by the glass. Between the grilled calamari, the shrimp with spicy peppers, the filet of grouper, and the dry soup, I'm not even sure I could pick a favourite. You better decide for yourself -- go hungry.

We were underwhelmed by both the food and service. Is 'Chiado' Portuguese for short cut? Dinner for two at almost $300 and we are poured wine by the glass and do not get the bottle we ask for. The lobster risotto lacked authenticity and the single piece of calamari app seems mean. Our waiter dropped by from time to time but seemed focused elsewhere. Not a great anniversary dinner.
i love this place.  so beautiful.  great art and wonderful food

Went to Seattle many years ago for a family function and was so impressed with everything from the bread to the steak to of course the seafood. I can see that nothing has changed with this fantastic Portuguese restaurant. Will be back very soon!

reviews.text: I was here last night for a Corporate Christmas Party, It was very professionally organised. The servers well welcoming and knowledgeable in making drinks....

The only way my experience at Chop could've been better, is if the waiter accidentally
brought someone else's cake to our table and started singing happy...

Outstanding.  
Was taken here by a work colleague and very impressed.  
Much thought and effort has gone into the menu and ambiance as well as a hand picked...

Wife and I make annual trip to Sheraton Airport  for tax convention and make a point of going here for dinner on Friday night.  Food is always great, sometimes service is slow because of crowds.
This past visit, there was a slight mix up with service and we contacted them.  They bent over backwards to apologize for something minor, they will use it as a learning tool.  The owner called us twice to fully understand what happened and was more than generous.  To them, every customer must be completely satisfied.  Why can't every business be run like that ?
Nov 2017 made another annual visit.  Four of us went after gruelling all day conference and although it was a busy Sat night, we enjoyed ourselves.  We could carry on conversation without shouting, beer was cold and large size, food (tenderloin) was good as usual.  Will continue to visit on my Toronto trips.

Cab Sav was lovely, beer was good, server was very pleasant and knowledgeable - King Crab was cold and dry.  Advised them of this and they were apologetic and did take care of the King Crab bill and very graciously gave us gift cards to return another night.  Next time I'm in Ontario visiting my best friend we will return as other than tonight I have had numerous wonderful tasteful meals at Chop.

Large group so we shared nibbles to start. The steak bites and crab cakes were amazing! Also tried the lobster and vegetable tempura. Main was a perfectly cooked tuna steak with lovely creamy mash. Well looked after by the staff also.

Once again, an amazing experience at Chop! From the first greeting upon arrival, to Sean and others for the great service, and the perfectly prepared meals for the 5 of us! Thanks to Dylan and Matt for their help as well! Cheers and Merry Christmas!

There are only three places in the city I would have gone to for steaks and now this location makes it four. Steaks were prepared perfectly. One of the rare places that makes a perfect gin and tonic, and they use a craft gin which is rare. Great service from staff.

Overall, a basic experience for the heavy price tag! And what restaurant doesn’t accept American Express?! That’s the first clue of being a sub-par establishment

We were a party of 8 (4 
couples) had an awesome time. food was fantastic. Damn that man can cook. will be back this weekend.

Group of us went on a Friday night, food was fantastic very high quality second to none., our server Kat was amazing always checking up on us and made sure our drinks where good and food was to our liking also one of the owners Ugene sat with us had a drink with us courteous of him and was double checking to make sure everything was perfect, thank you to the Church team for. Great evening and we shall see you again very soon

This is honestly the worst place I’ve ever been in my life. Don’t go here this place deserves to go out of business. Who runs out of beer on a Friday night and makes you wait over an hour for your bill? This place.
The new Pizza menu is amazing. Im guessing this will be a top pizza place in downtown Toronto in 2018. Crust is the best.

reviews.text:
Ordered from their summerlicious dinner menu (Yes, this review is way overdue.)

Appetizer: Shrimp. Was probably best part of the meal. The shrimp were...
Wow, tough crowd to please but I was extremely impressed with Cibo. Went on a Friday night at 7 and scored a seat at the bar immediately! Customer service...

Service: Average
Food: Good variety on the menu, however 2 out of 3 orders had salt on the higher side
Drinks: Good listing of wines and spirits
Price:...

Dine here on a Saturday night for our anniversary. Great atmosphere and the restaurant was packed. We were seated by the window which was lovely but was a bit cold. The food and drinks were great, well presented and tasted fresh. The only downside was we felt very rushed. Our mains were brought out less than  30 seconds after we finished our starters and they cleared my main plate away whilst my partner was still eating. That's a No No in restaurants. Wait till all are finished before clearing. I suspect the wanted the table back. All in all it was a good experience.

Service is so great and kindness. The all of pastas we ordered are so good but it is small portion. The restaurant is bigger than i expected. It is not that loud. So we could keep our conversation. I should have had wine as well. They have so many wines which are different from others.

Service here was great, wine was delicious, a little pricey but still delicious. Food was okay, pizza base I had was a bit burnt but their home made bread and olives they brought round were fantastic. Enough so that me and my partner came back two days later

Everything was great for my first visit.
Appetizers arrived quickly and food was brought shortly after. The waiter paid attention to when we needed refills our our plates taken away. 
Everything tasted great. And it's walking distance from the subway. 
It's a nice location to just walk around after or before visiting the restaurant.
I would definitely return.

Took a third trip to Cibo - Yorkville last night and they never disappoint. Our server (Christian) was fantastic and catered to our needs willingly. (Even with a picky eater and changed orders), the manager (Allessandro) also took the time out of a busy evening to introduce himself and make sure our party was happy. Just a great team at this restaurant and I will surely be back soon!

Note: This review is only for the boulangerie. 

I came here during the Christmas market and was intrigued by it's patterned foyer. One thing for sure: the...
Spent Boxing Day Brunch at this French bistro at the Distillery District.  The decor is on the spot a nice cozy ambience of Provence and chic. Love the...
We came for meal a long time ago, but this is our first time stopping by at the bakery patisserie section. There are some nice random finds like hazelnut...

Cluny is always a great experience and we enjoy visiting quite regularly when in Toronto.  Great location, atmosphere and most importantly cuisine.  The cafe is always good as well if you're in a rush and want to grab a quick coffee or pastry.

Note: My only advice to the owners is to please not allow birds to be flying around in the building from a sanitary standpoint.  I understand they come in sometimes but you need to do more to keep them out.  Please acknowledge this issue and I will edit my review accordingly.

The atmosphere is great.  The place was packed and, given they don’t take reservations, we had a bit of a wait (20 minutes).  I tried the chicken, and it was really good.  I would definitely recommend it.  My spouse had the vegan option, and it wasn’t that good...  a bit tasteless.  We ordered dessert with coffee and hot chocolate.  The drinks took some time to come out, and they were cold.  The dessert came a while after we were done with our drinks, thus as much as it was really good, it would have been better enjoyed with hot coffee and hot chocolate at the same time.  Our waiter was a nice guy but completely inattentive.

Came here for a birthday recently and left already wanting to return. The restaurant itself is absolutely beautiful and the ambiance is French perfection. The staff were extremely friendly and knowledgeable, we were so happy with the service. And of course the food was delicious!  (probably my favourite French fries of all time.) Would highly recommend!

Went to a party in Cluny back private room.  It was fantastic.  The room was beautifully decorated and it didn't feel too small or too big.  we had our own bar access without leaving the room.  Service was fantastic.  Food was delicious.  Isn't cheap but worth every dollar.

The first time I visited the restaurant, I was amazed at the atmosphere as it really is a gorgeous place. 
Each time I've come back however, I've enjoyed it less and less. 

Last night was probably my last visit, and while it was extra busy since the christmas market is on, I don't think its an excuse. 

We were greeted by an impatient and sassy hostess, perhaps she was overwhelmed by how busy the restaurant was, but still, she was rude to both me my husband (in front of both sets of our parents!!!) which made us all uncomfortable and set the tone for the evening.  

Our waiter was lovely, can't remember his name, but he was doing a great job and recommended a fantastic wine.  However, about half of our appetizers came cold, and at that point I think everyone was disappointed.  The mains we had were pretty lacking and we didn't bother to stick around for dessert and coffee.  I get the sense that things are getting a bit lax- food coming out cold, poor customer service, menus that have become a bit tattered, just not what it used to be.  

Not thrilled about where this restaurant is going and won't be racing back anytime soon.

lic_profile: The cuisine, décor and atmosphere at Colette Grand Café celebrate the essence of French style. The French are praised for their impeccable cooking techniques and refined dishes but it is the simplicity of France's national cuisine that put it on the world stage. At Colette, the ingredients are treated with integrity and care to bring you a culinary experience you will cherish.

reviews.text: Being able to make reservations is a huge win in my books, especially for Sunday brunches. For whatever reason, toronto seems to lack restaurants that...

My visit was for a business lunch with my boss & co-workers. 
This is a chic experience from the moment you walk in, the food and the staff. 

I had the...

A friend of mine from Toronto couldn't stop talking about this restaurant.. so I had to try it out for myself. I went in for Sunday Brunch. 

This place...

I had New Year's Day Brunch here. The ambience is nice, the servers are friendly, and the food is quite good.

I must say it was interesting to have an all you can eat buffet style brunch, with lots of eye-catching items you'd never expect, and I enjoyed myself.

This was my first time here, so I can't speak for regular days, but wow was it ever crowded! I know there's not much they could have done because of the holiday but it still coloured my experience.

The food here is delicious and excellent but you had better be prepared to pay for the privilege. Our bill for four people came just shy of $400; I didn't mind the price but it's something prospective diners should keep in mind.

Overall a very positive experience. I will be returning when I have a special occasion to celebrate for sure.

Colette Grand Cafe has super cute Parisian style interior with French spirit of place. Amazing brunch with  tasty food ,very nice service and friendly atmosphere. We had a reserved table for four people but didn't really liked place we have been seated by host. Our waiter did his best to make us happy and arranged another table for us. It took less then 2 min even place was packed. Cafe was pretty busy during Sunday brunch time but no one bother each other at all. Everyone enjoyed food and company. Sommelier was very helpful and knowledgeable to  help us with choice of wine. Very much impressed.

Relaxing place with good food options for brunch. However, the service is pretty slow, and a few different people forgot our drink orders. Also, the chairs in the sunroom look nice but are not very functional. They are also close together so the waitress would always numb into me when going past. 

I recommend bar Wellington instead, it's just down the street east 50M.

The food was amazing! We got the pancakes, the smoked salmon bagel and the avocado toast. The only downside was the staff kept on mixing up our orders and making mistakes. But overall, still very friendly and we could see they were trying their best! (They even gave us free croissants to compensate)

Would definitely come back and I am very excited to try their buffet

We held our wedding at Colette Grand Cafe and Kaylie and the entire Colette Staff went above and beyond to ensure it was the most memorable evening. The food was absolutely delicious. The service from the staff was amazing. Highly recommend them if you are looking for a venue to host a party!

The bread served with olive oil and rosemary was great! The server kept pushing alcoholic drinks on us as well. After asking the table as a whole, he went around individually asking about drinks.
Dinner is always amazing at Coppi.  All the entree's are delicious, however, my personal favourite, is the black cod.
Was here for Summerlicious 2017.  Delicious food, great service, nice décor!  Was a little disappointed that they changed Atlantic Grouper to Halibut on their Summerlicious menu.

Our server Kiri was also wonderful!! She is such a genuinely pleasant person and goes above and beyond to get to know you. Thanks for an awesome celebration District! We will be back.

Great food at a good value in an lively and comfortable atmosphere. Food options is classic fare with a twist, great tasting, rich and flavourful, but not heavy. The service was great, friendly and considerate while not being overwhelming. Restrooms, downstairs and not wheelchair accessible, were clean and acceptably laid out.

A+ Visiting from Australia and called in after hearing good things - it didn’t disappoint. Great service, music and food. Legit healthy options on the menu and make sure to get something off the drinks menu as you might not see Kombucha with a shot elsewhere! Enjoy.

Great variety of healthy eats & neat decor/vibe. We came here before a show and enjoyed two salads which were both delicious. First course had the shrimps and assorted...

Excellent food, staff and atmosphere. The decor is beautiful and the food is one of a kind. The falafel is the best I have ever had. The flat breads fresh...

Came here with a large group. We ordered a variety of dishes that everyone was satisfied with whatever we ordered. Great place for tapas. The server was accommodating for our group and we're very courteous.

I had an incredible evening here for a Miss Universe Canada event. The food was so delicious, and they had different options for people with allergies. So accommodating, and knowledgeable about their menu. Very friendly staff. The peppermint tea was a perfect finish to the amazing meal. I will be coming here every time I'm in Toronto!

The food and the service are spectacular! We ordered the mezes appetizer and it was perfect; from the hummus to the tabouli. It also paired really well with the sharing kabob plate. I recommend to ask for the garlic sauce and the garlic yogurt sauce as they added so much flavour. We also ordered the fish of the day (it was perch) it was seasoned perfectly, and the crust was the best! Also, our waiter, Antonis, was super helpful, very knowledgeable with the menu and so kind.

The place was good. Staff was really friendly. Food was good; they mentioned that they offered halal food as well. It sounded like the owner of the place was a bully who scared the staff and made them change our table because he had priority customers who were given that spot after we were told to get up. The staff was nice enough to offer us free drinks.
Best food in Toronto. Well worth the price. Go with a group so you can split a bunch of small plates. Would give this restaurant 6/5 if I could.

lic_profile: Diwan's elegant interior evokes the luxury of a private Syrian home in the early 19th century.  Sumptuously decorated with wooden panels inset with mirrors, the room extends the Museum experience to diners: the panels are original and form part of the Aga Khan Museum's Permanent Collection.  Diwan's floor-to-ceiling windows offer a stunning view of the formal garden of the Aga Khan Park designed by Lebanon-based landscape architect Vladimir Djurovic, who visited the world's historic Islamic gardens for inspiration.

Master Chef Mark McEwan and Chef de Cuisine John Kovac offer a menu that highlights flavours and fragrances from the Middle East, North Africa and the Indian subcontinent. Prepared with local and international ingredients, the menu celebrates the many textures and flavours of traditional cuisine with unexpected twists on spicy and savoury dishes.

When we were...

My mom...
A friend and I decided to check out this restaurant out of convenience since we were also going to look around the museum. It was easy to make an online...

Good food and service, prices are not bad either but I got very upset when I saw a $7 water bottle on my receipt. After asking for the drinks (we got 2 beers) the server asked "And the water? Still? Sparkling?" even though we never mentioned water, so I was led to believe that it might have been complimentary. 7 dollars for a bottle of still water (plus tax, so basically 8 dollars) that we did not even ask for...I felt robbed.

A real oasis in a big city. Wonderful surroundings like shimmering pools with an elegant ethnic subdued interior. Friendly servers. They are only open for Lunch which is a pity. Menu a little limited but does have seasonal changes

Enjoyed a lovely lunch with my sister yesterday. Had the calamari appetizer and beet falafel burger, both were delicious. Our server, Angelo, was friendly, knowledgeable and attentive. Would love to try their dinner menu!

Came here for lunch with a friend while Summerlicious was on and had the hummus, chicken and the carrot cake.  The hummus with eggplant was really good that I forgot to take a picture. I guess I was a little hungry as well. 

The chicken was okay. It wasn't spectacular but the flavours were good. It was just that the chicken was a bit dry. 

The carrot cake ended the meal nicely. It wasn't your traditional carrot cake. This one felt light and airy and had more of a cupcake texture. It was delicious.  I may just have three of these for the app, main and dessert next time. Haha. 

The atmosphere was nice and the service was good. The only thing that could be improved upon is a bit faster service but we weren't in a hurry so all is good.
It is very unique and seren.  Beautiful atmosphere.  Diwan restaurant food is amazing and so is the decor.  Visit is a must when in Toronto.

Never stayed in a hotel room here but I do go for the food. Its a great spot for brunch, dinner or partying on the weekend. Always a good time at the Drake. The upstairs patio in the summer time is a great hangout spot and an awesome date night spot. Good place always packed with people and a good vibe. Food is great to. Nothing bad to say about it.

Went for breakfast on New Year's Day. I was very excited about the menu and ordered the duck confit hash, which sounded delicious. The food was underwhelming - the egg was scotch but yolk was cold, potatoes were chewy, not in a good way, they doused the food with cream that was tasteless. I've had better and far cheaper meals at other places in Toronto. I do love the atmosphere in the Drake's restaurant, especially all the different kinds of lighting and the artwork upstairs and quirky bar. Our waitress was also hilarious and totally worth the visit, but it was her last day. My partner also had an average looking breakfast- she said it wasn't bad. Photos of our meals posted. Our friends had pancakes and I can't remember what else. No photos of their food taken. pancakes were colourful and pretty.

Drake provides an edgy atmosphere. The restaurant has great service and provides with vegan options. I loved the Avocado toast with a touch of spice. There tuna salad is also delicious. I wouldn't recommend getting a coffee, instead get a cappuccino since the price is the same.

Very nice hotel. I think the building is beautiful in it's age. The staff are attentive and friendly.  The menu has some nice choices, but it is not a budget place to go to. Back to the building, I am impressed with the old ways things were built and this gives a lot of character to the Drake.

Came here for a club night. Older crowd (men +25). Multiple floors with different music and vibe in each. Top floor was better for talking, ground floor for oldies dancing, and a dark basement. Can get super packed on the ground floor given the restaurant layout. Fun experience overall.

If you don't mind that then no worries, we went elsewhere as soon as we finished the food.
Fastest service I've ever experienced in Toronto. Great cocktails, fantastic sharing dishes, and a lovely decor make this a step above your average bar. A tight menu makes a quality experience.

lic_profile: Entice Culinary Lounge is an upscale bistro located on Queen West, offering a welcoming and stylish atmosphere that transitions to a social and pleasing vibe in the late evening. Seasonal ingredients and in-house specialists are used to create an elevated globally-inspired menu within a modern open concept kitchen.

reviews.text: Pricey, but the food was delicious!!!! And amazing service!!! I had the risotto as my main and my friend had the steak! It wasn't busy the night we went...

Came here for brunch and was pleasantly surprised.  It's a pretty large space so great for big groups.

The decor is unique in that weird but interesting...
Great for groups and dates alike. The setting is very trendy and warming. The room is also designed to keep your conversations within your own are.  In...

Great environment (very clean and modern). Staff are super friendly and engaging, I truly felt welcome. The cocktail selection is definitely one of the best I've seen among Queen West eateries. Very unique and creative to say the least. In terms of food, I had to beef (braised short rib with duck fat potatoes) and needless to say I will be back again very shortly. 10/10

Entice lounge is a restaurant that everybody needs to try out, at least once. The atmosphere is lovely. The food, delicious. The drinks are fantastic - one particular drink that my fiance enjoys, is the tea cocktail.....if you haven't had yet, take my word....try it!! I always have the best experience possible :)! Don't miss out, get Enticed today!
Entice is fantastic. The cocktails. Are amazing, food is great, and the chef specials are creative and amazing. I highly recommend this place!

Hilarious food ... Steak and BBQ turkey drumstick is just amazing. Make sure to ask for dessert menu and go directly for chef 's creation .... 
Great selection of wines and cool cocktails. A perfect place corretly named as lounge!!

We came here for my fiance's birthday on a thursdayt night.  It was neatly quiet with 2 couples sitting at the bar and a couple at the lounge.  I ordered a tea cocktail and was shocked it's served in gorgeous tea cup!  For good my fiance ordered a beef dish and I ordered their daily special, risotto stuffed inside calamari.  Both were perfect and melt in your mouth.   For dessert we ordered their pb&j which is cake acting like bread with cake toppings acting like sandwich fillings to look like a sandwich.   It was creative and delicious and was served with a birthday card signed by all the staffs!  We enjoyed the experience here very much and would definitely come back!  The best part though! Our bill was under $60 after tax! Which is absolutely reasonable!  Look forward to trying the rest of their menu!

reviews.text: I am sorry say this, but the service was very bad. What can you expect when you say that the store is very nice and you only get stared at? Very bad...
This pipesmith is located at the lobby level of the Royal York Hotel. Their forte are handmade pipes but they do sell cigars as well. However these are all...

Came here for Sunday brunch.  To be fair... I really need to break this review into 2 areas... Food and the service (or the lack of...)
For the food offered, the cooking and selection was nice and tasted well. The cooked to order selection was amazing and Chef Cory went above and beyond to accommodate our requests.. .

The wait staff. The staff here has little to no interest in serving you... at least during the brunch service.  They are no where to be found and you need to flag down others just to grab their attention.  Big time negative points.  

Last note is the US exchange truly sucks here.   At current I can get 1.27 for the dollar...  I was only offered 1.15 and that was their special rate for hotel guests...  I will think twice next time returning to the area.

Top notch breakfast... A wide variety of options for breakfast from good bread to fresh fruit and juice to hot dishes.   You will get what one would expect of a high end establishment.  Loved the atmosphere, the food and the restaurant!
Had Christmas Eva dinner with my friend. Nice food ,nice wine and nice service

Had the summerlicious lunch menu and found it refreshingly good. It was definitely one of the better tasting (summerlicious menu) restaurants in the financial district for me. Servers were attentive and generally friendly. No views unfortunately, but I felt the food was delicious and worth it.  I plan on coming back!

My wife and I had dinner there before Christmas 2016.   Atmosphere was cold with more than drafts coming through from the street entrances.  The food was nothing special - below expectation - and prices were above expectation even for Toronto.  Service was attentive but not friendly.   Not to be repeated.   The Epic Restaurant is way overpriced!

My husband and I celebrated our Wedding Anniversary here and we absolutely loved the food, music and service! 

We tried the Saganaki, and grilled Octopus...
Very nice establishment with an excellent menu. All the food I seen walk past me, looked stunning and from judging by other patrons, it seemed to taste...

Stopped by for a Friday night dinner. It is an upscale Greek restaurant with a posh but comfortable vibe. 

Saganaki, $14. Unique presentation (flaming),...

Was there for a dinner with work. Supposed to be our holiday party. The service was good. The waiters were smiling and courteous. The food was very amazing. Well prepared nice display and delicious. The only reason I will put 4 stars is because of the seating. This was a 30+ people and we had 3 tables of 12 seating. We were Mix with the clientele that was dinning there. We were loud and took a lot of space. I can only imagine how annoyed these people might have been.
We had a holiday event here earlier this month.  Very good food (hard to do for a large crowd) and the vast majority of the staff were attentive, positive and helpful. Will definitely be back.
Service was very good definite 5/5 there. Reason for the 4 star overall is the food. Food took a while to get to us and was not at the level I’d expect from Toronto for the price.
Friendly, modern, good food quality Greek place. A good place to go for a dinner. We were both happy with our sea food stew as well as a fried clams on lentils. CAD $33 and $31 respectively.

- Amazing service. 
- Ordered grilled octopus, and it was REALLY good! Cooked and seasoned to perfection.

Serving fresh, daily homemade pasta, risottos and pizza, the cuisine finds its inspiration in Northern Italy. The wine list features some of the best and most affordable wines sunny Italy has to offer.

reviews.text: This place is SO cute, reminded me of one of those homey movie scenes with the snow falling outside. The service is very quick and friendly. And the overall...

A hidden gem tucked inside an inner street of cabbagetown.

Creative name for a restaurant. Amelia is the street that they are on and it sounds like family...

I've walked by this place many times - it was finally time to try it.

Great little restaurant on a side street in Cabbagetown.  They have a cute little...

My husband and I came here for dinner on a Tuesday evening. The place has nice ambiance and good food. Waiter seemed to be trying to up-sell. We had octopus salad and arugula salad to start and a pizza loaded with chicken, sausage, basil, and more. All was delicious. Some may find the octopus salad to have too much vinegar. We had lemon tart and chestnut cooked. One of the best lemon tarts in a long Time.

Absolutely great food!! Finally realized how great Italian food truly is. Great experience, great food, great location and great staff!! Btw i never review places but this place more than deserves it!

We came there with a huge group of like 17 people and they accommodated us even tho we only had a reservation for 10-15 people, plus we were a little late. They setup a pizza menu for us with drinks and desert. The BBQ Chicken Pizza and Cacciatore Pizza was amazing.  And we all had the best Tiramisu ever...it was so light and fluffy. The servers and staff were excellent and were really sweet. P.S I liked the romantic candle light dinner vibe, that was cool.
One of the best places to be. The food is amazing and  the staff is always welcome. A great family feel...LOVE IT and the service never failed!
Great service, very fast and not at the expense of the food! Don’t miss out on the cookies for dessert!

reviews.text:
On a freezing cold Saturday Night after the movies this was a pleasant spot to eat.  Decor was very nice.  

We all had their pizzas.  All different.  All...

Took my mother here for her 80th birthday. 

The staff gave us a great table  for 8 right at the front if the restaurant. 

Our server was very...
came by for brunch with two friends, we ordered funghi pizza, eggs all inferno and eggs benny. food was alright at it's best but overall, super...

Was there for an Office Christmas Lunch.  The pumpkin pie was the best dessert ever.  Had the steak salad as the main, and the mozzarella as the appetizer.  While it was fine dinning prices, the food was definitely worth its salt.

All in-house made pasta and cured meats. We had a dinner "family style".  Great to choose from a lot of different dishes.  Having said that, the braised shortrib pappardelle was amazing ...I'd definitely have that on it's own the next time.  Excellent service.  Funky, upscale hip atmosphere.

I'm not one of those people who write negative stuff, but I was compelled to do so with Fabbrica.  Let me start by saying something positive. The ambiance was great.  Staff at the front were excellent. It just went downhill from there.  The food-over priced albeit it was tasty. The meat selection was a la carte.  It did not come with sides (who does that?).  Our server(the biggest disappointment) was not very engaging, was only interested in taking our orders. He was not very proactive in recommending or even asking if we had any questions.  For the price we paid, we could've gone at a much better establishment.  Really disappointed.

Pretty decent meal. I didn’t find it too special for a Mark McEwan restaurant. Cocktails were great. The only off putting thing was that the hostess was hysterically crying on the phone when we arrived.

The food is amazing!! I came here for a family outing and was very pleasantly surprised by the incredible White Truffle Cream Pizza for only $20... But tons of truffles!! It was absolutely incredible and the last time I had something like this, was in a small Italian town. The service was friendly and speedy and I enjoyed my experience overall. Not too pricy but try and stay away from the appetizers, they're not very large portions but high prices. An entree, coffee, drinks, and dessert are all reasonably priced however.

lic_profile: Figures is serving more than just exquisite food and crafted cocktails - they're also drawing on some of your fondest memories of comics and superheroes and bringing them to life again. Nostalgia at its finest! Guests will be met with enchantment and delight upon entering the venue as decoupage style comics and poetry decorate the walls and complement the dark wood tones. With plush seating the venue is a refined and eclectic space to host any gathering.

reviews.text:
This has by far become one of my favourite restaurants in the city. 

I guess I can start with the fact that the owners are obviously kids of the 80's much...

Overpriced for the portions you get, and while the concept is interesting, the execution is like an art dealer's idea of nerdy fun. 

Good service though.

The food is great. Typical tapa bar, service not so much. Really slow wait for tapas and to get the bill. 

Server also spilled a drink and dropped a plate....

Ambiance ✔️
Food ✔️
Music ✔️
Friendliness ✔️
Service ⭕️

Went for a friend's birthday on a Saturday. The vibe, layout and design of the place is really cool.. very creative. We ordered all the "earth" items from the menu. They were really small portions but very tasty. The mains were delicious. The music was very nostalgic, bringing us to our high school days. The only area for improvement is service. Although everyone was extremely friendly, especially the manager. Our table wasn't ready for 15-20 minutes even though we made a reservation. While we waited at the bar, they gave each one of us a drink on the house. Recommend to go on a weekend. Fun date spot or a night out with friends.

Got the chance to try out figures for the first time and I must say until about halfway through our meal we were not happy with the way it was presented to us. I didn't quite like that the first thing that they did is try to sell us action figures. It honestly seemed like rich people trying to make it seem like they genuinely cared about what I'd 'peasants' care about. Our first two entrees were pretty good but then we ordered the duck, and oh my God it was incredible. I would literally go back and order just that again. Bottom line, the food was pretty good and service was pretty good too. Wouldn't come back here without a gift card but not a amazing experience.

Couldn't have had a better time!
The food was incredible and the presentation was even better. 
The drinks were super creative and every single one tasted just as good as the last. 
To top it off, the comic book atmosphere made it a really enjoyable time. It's like every time I would look up I would see a new character on the wall! 

Definitely recommending to everyone I know.

I have been to Figures twice and both experiences have been great. The first time was just for drinks, and the second time was for a meal. The drinks are excellent and super creative. The food is also top notch. I was actually very surprised how good this food was. And the desserts! Wow! So good! The comic-themed details are carried throughout all aspects of the restaurant. They even had a Darth Vader-shaped cheesecake. 

I would (and have) highly this restaurant. Definitely worth it!

Visited Figures over the weekend and was excited considering all the hype around it. 

Upon arriving we were greeted by a red carpets and media walls (I think there was an event happening) we got to take pictures on the red carpet which was fun, it is TIFF week after all.

When you enter the restaurant the front is a comic store, with toys and comic books and the walls are full of art which looks really good. Fun part is you hit a button (Captain America's shield) and a door opens in the wall and you go through to the restaurant. 

It is definitely is different on the inside, looks very upscale with tons of cool art on the walls (they won't let you take pictures of the art but it really is amazing).

They had a really intricate list of cocktails, I tried the Maleficent and Bramble Bee, both extremely delicious, like wow.

We tried the Beet salad which was also very delicious and the presentation was A plus, then we noticed a table next to us get this massive platter of sea food and meat and obviously we could not resist, it was not on the menu but the waitress mentioned it as their "special" . It was to die for, unreal and a must!!

Service was good, food took a little bit longer than I would like to come out, but they were very busy and it got really busier as the night went on. After dinner Figures turns into a lounge with really good music so we ended up staying late, it got really busy and apparently there was a celebrity in the house (although we didnt see anyone specifically).

I will absolutely visit again.

Thanks!

reviews.text: I am happy to have rediscovered Five Doors North after having dined here years ago!  It was a cold Wednesday night so the restaurant was quite empty but I...
First time coming here.  Where do I start.... Well, I will start by parking.  If you didn't know, there are ton of inner streets that you can park without...

Awesome personal service from James to welcome us here on our first visit.
All courses were 5* with great knowledge and smiles.
The striploin special was...

Had a Christmas party there with about 20 of us.  There was a set menu so they came with various dishes of food.  Unfortunately they were a bunch of nothing dishes.  All fillers no substance plates.  Pastas, rice, nocchi, which were all sub par.  Very dissappointed.  Then at 9:40 the meat finally came.  And it still wasn't enough.  What a joke.  It's too bad that a place can just serve sub par and think they are getting away with it.

Just attended a work Christmas Party here on Saturday evening.
Small place, good for small groups
Great food and great service!  We had shared plates which were all good.
My favs were the Risotto and Salmon, also loved the Creme Brule!
Well executed food, friendly casual cool service. Would definitely come again.

Walked on a cold night to this restaurant as a recommendation of a friend. Walked I the door to an amazing welcome from James who has been extreamly diligent the whole evening! 
Good amazing and would deffo recommend!

Not sure why people love this place so much. We were a group of 8 and got to try many different dishes. The starters we're good but the mains not so much. In my humble opinion the food if mediocre and the service subpar. Finally I would like to mention that the place is very loud and the tables and very small and too close to each other.

reviews.text: I was so thrilled when i heard my book group would be dining at an Italian restaurant. I had visions of homemade fresh pasta & hand carved chicken cutlets....

SERVICE: 10/10. Courteous and friendly with a smile. No complaints whatsoever.

FOOD: 2/10. I have no idea who is the chef, but he's / she's clearly not...
We had lunch today at Florentia. We enjoyed our food. The service was responsive and friendly. I would go again.

Lovely ambiance and the waitress. She went out of her way to divide an order of spaghetti into 2, for my kids. The pizza and the seabass were great, however, we found a small metal wire in our daughter's spaghetti. The waitress was way too nice so I didn't mention it.

I wish Google Maps allowed .5 increments as I would have given Florentia a 3.5. 

I went on a busy Saturday night, the wait staff were very friendly. Our mains took an hour to reach us from when we arrived until they were at our table, which is too long in my opinion. I think there are better options on Mt. Pleasant for a similar price point, although I am very interested in the Monday-Thursday prix fixe menu.
Fresh pasta made on the premises from scratch and it’s amazing! We’ve eaten here a few times now sampling different dishes. Every single one has been a delight.

The service is really good and friendly, the food was ok , except for the muscles it was amazing.
Street parking only, we went there on new years day with the family,it was not crowded,I don't know about other days.

The food was amazing and reminded me of the gastronomic food last year in Umbria, Italy. The service was excellent, the food was delicious and fresh, and the ambience was perfect - we had a seat right by the window.  Would definitely recommend for the true Tuscana experience.

reviews.text: Fonda Lola is a Mexican restaurant by Trinity Bellwoods that serves a variety of tacos and magaritas. I had the pleasure of trying some of their menu items...
When this place opened it was good.  Now the service is awful. The food is overpriced for what you get. Ordered the steak in lettuce and got two, that I...
I reaaaaaally liked this place! Took me back to my honeymoon in Mexico! The ambiance of the joint was perfect for me. Felt as though I was transported back...

The food is very good and fresh. Nicely decorated restaurant with friendly atmosphere.

Just two things that would make our experience better:
- We showed up with a group of eight, and not being able to split the bill was a problem.
- Portion sizes; it would be nice if sides were provided with the mains (like good rice or beans)

Overall, this is a nice restaurant for a date.
Great food, friendly staff, nice outdoor patio... What else do you need?! The fish tacos were great, not greasy, lots of flavor... Paired with a can of tecate with salted rim and lime, heaven!

Let me start by saying we were a group of 12 that did NOT make it easy on the staff. But I took that into consideration and still think the 1-star is earned.

This restaurant had major operational issues that were painfully apparent to all patrons. The reviews already posted are pretty accurate about service, speed, etc.

The kicker of the evening was when the waitress came back to the table after the service and asked each member of the group of 12 what they'd ordered over the past 3 hours. Presumably she spent the next 25 minutes trying to reconcile the receipts.

Ultimately:
* Good, not great, food
* Decent drinks
* Slow, inattentive service
* Obvious under-staffing issues in front and back of house

* NOT good for groups

They need some serious help running a restaurant

Won't be back
Really enjoyed this place. Authentic hand made . Well worth it
The menu does not describe the dishes accurately. The steak taco was like mush. Horrible. And the tables are way too small. Waitresses with facial piercings are unacceptable.

reviews.text:
Decent place to get prix fixe lunch, and they can accommodate large groups. On all the times I have come here, the service was quick and very good. 

Today...
It was ... sort of okay. The service was "doing their duty" and nothing more. There are two restaurants here: "Fred's not here" and "The red tomato". When I...

8 oz steak: a bit too tough despite it being medium rare, but the crispy outer layer was nice touch

Frites: they were more like potato chips to be honest

The foods were amazing. We had the holiday dinner menu which came with one appetizer, one main course, and one dessert. The baked lobster & crab soup was delicious, the lobster and seafoods risotto was tasteful. The corn bread were fresh off the oven. The serving staffs were friendly and made sure our meals were good. I highly recommended.

Would never eat here again. My fiance and I went for dinner after an event. Our waiter was very annoying, constantly making snide and somewhat inappropriate comments to us throughout the whole meal. At one point when we were eating, he stopped by our table to check up and noticed that my fiance was eating his food somewhat quickly and remarked "wow, hope this isn't a first date". We informed him that we were actually engaged and he said rather rudely "really?". A little more than halfway into our meal, our waiter, tried to take my plate away. I was only half way through my steak and hadn't even touched my pasta. He tried to take my food 3 more times when it was very clear I was still eating. When I was done, I had about half of my pasta left over and asked for a take out box. He said he would box it up for me in the back and took my plate away from the table. I then went to the washroom after paying and got distracted so we left. I forgot about my pasta! He never brought it back to the table in a box, even though we didn't leave until a good 15 minutes after he took it away. All in all, awful experience. The food wasn't even that good and the staff was very unprofessional. Don't waste your time coming here.

It didn’t ruin our evening or anything but overall pretty disappointed. Greeted by who I assumed was the manager (tall Asian guy) who seemed annoyed that we were late for our reservation. Ordered a bottle of wine and our meals immediately. Everything came in dribs and drabs. No flow at all. Server tried his best and still had the balls to appease us with a $70 dollar credit for something we didn’t order.  When called  on it, he stood by his offer that he at least tried to help us out. Weird right?!!
Anyway. Go there if it’s in your  budget (we spent $300.00, tip included for 4 adults and 1 child). 
Much love. 
Raj

Went for lunch with colleagues.  Had the holiday lunch special which was a 3 course meal for $29.  The crab and lobster soup was a great start for the season.  Had tilapia entree which had a great amount of spice to it.  Finished with the bread pudding dessert which was delicious.  Enjoyed the meal.
Nice atmosphere, great service. Had decent appetizers (escargots, little watery), fab steak as main course, caramel Gelato unfortunately only average. Still great time. Good wine selection.

lic_profile: Fring’s is the Bent-Lee boys’ latest and most ambitious venture. A breathtaking dining space with a cool and global fine dining vibe and aesthetic, it opened its doors last October on King Street West. Years of experience working for the family operations, Susur, Lee, and Bent, provided them with intimate knowledge of the dining industry.

The menu at Fring's, reflects the now comfort-food trend, along with acknowledgement to Toronto foodies’ appetites for palate-expanding world cuisine, was developed by the Bent-Lee sons, along side with their father, world renowned Chef Susur Lee.  Accompanying the menu is an extensive wine & cocktail list, curated to further complement the vast diversity of flavours and textures.

reviews.text: The ambience was nice and luckily we got the cool throne chairs/tables. We saw that a couple was leaving so we quickly requested it and our server moved us...

Although not totally my cup of tea in terms of taste and ambiance, this Susur Lee joint is par excellence in terms of execution.

Was here for a large group...
New Year's Eve dinner at Fring's, a Susor Lee Establishment, was a very dissapointing experience. Despite creating a custom menu for the evening, management...

I was very disappointed by the service. The decor and music were great but the service was very bad. Our table
ordered a full course but every meal was 45 minutes apart. It was also unfortunate that we had to wait 45 minutes for our drinks, which we only received after asking our waiter twice and another waiter for a third time.  We also had to ask a staff member to call our waiter since he was no where to be found when we were ready to pay.  Our table felt very uncomfortable having to ask for our food, drinks and bill multiple times. Although, the front desk staff was very polite and apologized for the bad service I will not be returning. It is unfortunate that the service was very disappointing and overall uncomfortable. I do not recommend this restaurant.

3.5. Takes a while to get a reservation - as in a week or so. So we took a cancellation at last minute when our flight got it. 
The food was good, had high expectations but didn’t quite meet. Good service, pricey bill though and didn’t leave full. Nice vibe. Will come back for drinks though!

Can I tell you what an amazing experience we had?! The food was totally delicious, perfect portions and packed with very intriguing flavours.  We read some bad reviews about the restaurant so we went in quite skeptical.  
The restaurant was amazing and our party of 4 gave it "two thumbs up" for service, presentation and quality of food. We will definitely go back!

This place was interesting. Drinks were very good but food was just ok. Strange combinations of tastes but interesting. Worth a try but no need to go back. Service was great and sitting outside in the summer was really nice.
Nice setting but that's as far is it goes. their portion sizes are so pinch for the price you pay! it's like a bag of chips filled with 80% air. Good riddance save your money folks!

lic_profile: Located in Hart House on the University of Toronto's St. George campus, Gallery Grill is Toronto's best kept secret.  Filled with 20th century Canadian portraits, a vaulted ceiling and hand-painted stained glass windows, the dining atmosphere is second only to the seasonal creations of Chef Suzanne Baby. The artisanal lunch menu features locally sourced ingredients for a comforting, yet cosmopolitan experience enjoyed in front of a wood burning fireplace.

reviews.text: My friends and I went there for winterlicious lunch. Not my pick, but I went along. It's situated inside Hart House which could be a hidden gem....
Ambience & decor: When you enter this restaurant inside the Hart House, you need to look no further to be at Hogwarts. Beautiful building - Gothic...
Well, well, well...a very stately establishment much in keeping with the university setting.  Lovely wait staff.   Offered good salads for lunch.  Limited...
We had a great breakfast here. Great portion sizes, super friendly staff, and a home style menu. Fantastic!
Pretty good food and service. The interior is remarkable. Wouldn't have expected anything like this to be inside Hart House.
A fantastic restaurant hidden on the University of Toronto campus. I always try to visit when I am in Toronto and have time.
Had brunch here on Mother's Day.  Service was very friendly and helpful.  The food was delicious!  Have to try their fresh scones!  Love the ambiance with the interiors.
Amazing creme brulee

reviews.text: Love this place. Food is so tasty, with an emphasis on local and seasonal and the service is excellent.  Daily soup of parsnip puree with white chocolate...
Went there for breakfast, bit gloomy n cold day outside, globe bistro was even gloomier inside, v dark for the morning.... felt like We made a wrong brunch...

Note - review is based on Winterlicious 2017 experience ($23 lunch).

Location/Service
Located in the heart of Greektown on Danforth.  Pretty busy area -...

Excellent! The food, service and atmosphere are excellent! The maitre d' was especially helpful and informative. Food is fresh and sustainable. Plates made in-house and sustainable. Happy Hour from 4:00 to 6:00 p.m. and includes in-house wines,  beer, drinks and half-price oysters.  Reasonably- priced happy hour menu. Fish and chips ,very fresh and delectable! Definitely will go back!

Elegant dining room, sophisticated food, and great service come together at Globe. I've been three times for their tasting menu which changes regularly and features locally sourced ingredients. They also were able to accommodate my partner's food allergies. Brunch is also great. I recommend the dining room over the bar seating area if you can get it as the artwork and lighting are beautiful back there. The best fine dining in the neighbourhood.

A must. Had the Tagliatelle and soups (seasonal squash) and superb is an understatement. The soup had a hint of sesame and was perfectly portioned. The pasta was hearty and very creamy.  Started with oysters. I recommend you take their wine pairing advice, it is perfect.  The butter is homemade and you can tell. If you have anything here, have the ketchup. Even if you don’t like ketchup.  The tomatoes are smoked prior to them being puréed with local heirloom apples.  This place is a must.

Came for the Thanksgiving prix fixe dinner 2 years in a row. Service was good and the food was delicious both times. Only complaints were the ambience was a bit off on my most recent visit- the 80's mix played a little bit too loud in the upstairs front room. The portions were quite reasonable, which is great... except for an American Thanksgiving dinner where it's kind of expected to be stuffed. Small complaints for an otherwise solid restaurant.

I tried the prix fixed thanksgiving menu. It was very delicious. Everything food wise was perfect. The service was a little slow and we were seated right the front where the garage style window was opened. Not the best for October.

reviews.text:
Quaint restaurant, with decent food and beer. They also offer free parking although if planning to drink then that won't be of much help. 
Tried their beer,...
We came for dinner as part of the Old Toronto Beer Tour. This was our last stop from an exciting day of drinking and sightseeing. We ate from a fixed menu...
Grabbed a spot on the patio at the end of the season. After a great run, we were starving. Ordered a pint and my stomach screamed for a burger. No question,...

My wife and I had our wedding reception here on January 6th, and we can not recommend the Brewery highly enough, whether it's a dinner, brunch or your wedding reception. 

We want to thank Ron and Chris so much for everything you and your staff did for us. From helping us start planning the evening a year ago, to helping us bring everything in on Friday. When our rehearsal dinner space had a fire Chris saved us some tables so we could still have dinner, and of course thank you for everything you did the day of the wedding.

The food was amazing. It was the first time I ate at a wedding and all our gusts raved about how delicious the dinner was. 

You did so much and it was such a special evening that we will remember forever. You and your staff are wonderful!

Thank you again,

Elizabeth and Alexander

Great service and beer. Good food. Cozy pub. Been around since 2001. Neighbourhood staple. Flights are available which allows you to sample a lot of the different beers for cheap. They have a fireplace. Lots of seating, large place. Reservations are available if you have a large group (or small).
Wonderful staff - all of them. Good prices and quality food and drinks. Great for family, friends and even  business meetings.

Love this brewery/bar/restaurant. They have a front patio as well as a much larger very lovely, courtyard-style patio out back that fills up quickly in the summer. 

The standing menu is great, but the weekly rotating menu is what it's all about! Fantastic options at great prices!

The beer here is fantastic! They have standards and then a rotating cask that is a great choice.

Staff are friendly and love what they do. They are honestly happy to be there.

They also put on lovely weddings here. All around, it's a great place!
Good staff, good food, reasonable price. No complaints here^^

reviews.text: Hapa is the best izakaya that I've been to in Toronto. The food was amazing, the servers are very kind and always chekced up on us. The hello kitty drink is...

With its colourful LED lighting, Hapa looks more like a night club than a restaurant, and that's really not too far off. 

We were seated at the back of the...
The interior of this place is really nice - looks more lounge-y like than restaurant like, and it can accommodate large parties (there's a whole section in...

This place completely transformed me! I hated seafood before I had the firecracker tuna sushi. The food here is very fresh and extremely tasty. And they have a great selection of sake too. The prices are very reasonable too.
The place is very busy, so it's better to book a table beforehand.

Went here for a friend's birthday dinner last week. The restaurant was super dark and the music loud. It took us nearly half an hour to get the attention of a waitress to put in our food order after we sat down.

When the food did get to our table, the waitresses had no idea which end of the table got what order - making the process super confusing. It also didn't help that we didn't see the same waitress twice. We weren't sure who to ask for what. 

The food itself was okay. The torched food items appeared cool and definitely Instagram worthy, but the torching didn't add any flavour to the dish. My friend loves this restaurant, so I'd probably come back for her... But I'll stick to another Izakaya.

Spent my NYE at Hapa and had an excellent night :) Food was delicious and the servers/bartenders were super friendly and attentive. A big thanks to the Hapa staff for ringing in the new year with a good time

Great service but the food was disappointing. The jerk chicken rice bowl was missing the basic seasoning of salt and the firecracker sushi roll was a bit sloppy in presentation. The short ribs were wonderful however for the price could have given a bit more.

First time at this place, walked in with no expectations or reservations, service was really great from the moment we walked in. Tried a few very good dishes. Manager on duty was very helpful. The servers were very knowledgeable and helped us greatly when choosing which dishes to try! Thank you Hapa for the great experience!

reviews.text: Pretty cool spot! We stopped by here for dinner one night and I really liked the restaurant. They were pretty booked, but they had some seating in the back...

On the hunt for a line-less Sunday brunch we easily found seats at Harlem. Who knew they had food besides chicken and waffles?!

Fried okra: really...
The fried chicken and the crunchy thick batter was outstanding. LOVE the cornbread, it had corn bits in it and had just a slight spicy kick to it. The thick...

Live music was outstanding. Food quality was excellent. Not 5 stars because the portion size was small and the food was overpriced by a few dollars. I would fix up the place by hiring 1 server to work Friday and Saturday nights (the 2 busiest nights in the industry), 2 more people in the kitchen, and lowering the food prices by $2 on average and/or increasing the portion size. Overall a great experience, not perfect but still well done. Also get some desserts, you can make them in advance or outsource to a local bakery, and it can stay refrigerated for a few days, if not weeks! And typically, deserts are one of the most profitable menu items you can have, so why not!
Staff really nice.  Good food portions for prices. 10/10 recommend for a nice meet up with friends.
Went for an event, it was sectioned off. Separate bar and seating. Small but with patio and small dance area. Feel like it's more of a summer spot.

The staff went ABOVE and BEYOND to ensure both myself and my guests had an incredible time! From the selection of DJ/music, amazing cocktails, and private bar, we had everything we needed to make the night ABSOLUTELY outstanding. Our private party was well managed, well served and well entertained. The Caribbean food was phenomenal, the service was great and all details were taken care of by the staff on the day and the days leading up the event. This is not your average restaurant, and I had an above average experience. Huge applause to Harlem!

I've never had a bad experience at Harlem until today. The vibes were amazing the chef's platter Delicious however the chicken is where they lost points. The waitress brought the chicken to the table and then asked me "can you cut it open to see if it was cooked" . That sent off read flags and had me thinking maybe I could cancel it as it had me second guessing myself. I just wished they took a little more time and maybe checked a piece themselves instead of asking the customer to do it. I don't think I'll be getting their chicken again.

reviews.text: Hawthorne Food and Drink is located near Richmond and Church, a short walk away from Queen Station. I had heard about this restaurant for a while now as it...

Best place to work for free forever!

It is sad to see how they take advantage of people eager to work, grow and learn but they do not know where to start...

Great food and outstanding service by the two gentlemen who served me this afternoon. 

Shrimp was a little bit on the blander side, but overall, a very...

Really enjoyed our meal - food was generally delicious - trout nicely done, weiner schnitzel was overcooked,  accompanying vegetables and rice/potatoes nicely done.  Protein portions on small side but reflect the reasonable prices.  Beverages reasonably priced which is nice to see in Toronto where beverage prices continue to escalate.  Service was very attentive and #diverse (another nice change from usual Toronto dining scene).  Nice clean modern decor.  And by the way, the social enterprise ascpect is a big bonus and great idea.

Best place to work for free forever!

It is sad to see how they take advantage of people eager to work, grow and learn but they do not know where to start looking for jobs as they are starting to adapt their lives in Toronto or have special needs.

I worked for them in 2016 for 3 months full time, spent all my savings paying for transportation, uniforms and lunches.

I heard from the second week of the course that I was "so ready and prepared to work" as well as promises of help to start working with hotels and recognized companies and that never happened.

I was only offered to work full time for free. In 3 months of work I only covered about 5 paid food events where we were not offered food or drinks and the payment was minimum wage. But I worked 8 hours, 5 days a week in Hawthorne without receiving any payment, without right to eat anything, and with a break of 15 min maximum. Pops where the only thing we could consume freely.

After some weeks of training they believed I was capable enough for me to open or close the restaurant by myself. I did it. For several hours I was in charge of the whole restaurant by myself with 1 or 2 cooks until the trainer or another trainee came. So I was managing the whole front house by myself and not getting paid, or offered food and breaks longer than 15 minutes.

I met people with quick learning skills, and at some point all those people were very disappointed with the course. Some of them did not continue the course, others like me, we had already lost so much that we had no choice but to stay and wait to see if at any moment the promises came true.

After several months of my experience with this company, I got a job in a restaurant (without the help of is company) and the reality is completely different from what they do in Hawthorne. I get all the food I want to eat for just $4 per day. I get paid tips plus a salary. The training was just 3 days and it was paid. The break is 30 min every 5 hours of work, one hour every 8 hours.

I did 2 courses with this company. Front of house and Guest services. I regret so much doing both courses. I would never get that time of my life back again.

This is all my personal opinion and experience and I wanted to post it so people are aware of it before starting losing their time.

If you are new in Toronto and thinking about starting one of this courses because you feel lost about where to start finding jobs in Toronto, send me a message. I’m not an expert, but I can give you my opinion on the matter and maybe make your life a bit easier.
Got the burger with fries, and it was great! The dipping sauce was amazing. Head chef came to chat and talk about the food. The atmosphere and service was also very good.
Service was good but the food was mediocre at best.  Wouldn't go back.

I ordered a breakfast sandwich advertised as being a country biscuit including bacon, cheese, tomato, greens, but asked for no egg.  It came as ordered but to my great dismay the biscuit was completely slathered with margarine on both sides. When I say slathered, I mean literally dripping as if it had been soaked. The waitress tried to suggest it was butter, as if that would have made the slightest difference but I have never in all my years seen melted butter drip into a yellow ooze. It was disgusting.  I refused to even consider eating it. I didn't say another word. She must have said something to someone and as such, my tea was removed from the bill as if that would in any fashion placate any hungry and disappointed customer. 

A reasonable facsimile of customer service would be to apologize, recognize the customer's concern, offer to replace the meal immediately and ask afterwards if the food was ok. 

My guest and I were the only customers that Thursday morning.  I now know why.

We were here at lunch today.  Had absolutely fabulous service but the food seriously left a lot to be desired.  The mushroom bruschetta with the balsamic aioli just doesn't work and the veggie pizza seemed to have the same toppings with  just some add ons.  It's sad when the onion rings are the best thing  we ate.  We have eaten regularly at the cafe for many years and the last couple of times, the food hasn't been very good at all.  Not sure if we'll go back

The recent 'face-lift' to the iconic 'Holt's Gourmet' café in the Holt Renfrew Centre concourse is sad. Seating within the cafe has been dramatically reduced, the always welcome potted plant on each table is gone, and refreshments are served in paper cups.  Considering the outstanding quality of food that the chef/kitchen has become famous for, this cosmetic change smacks of 'cost-cutting', not renewal. If I want cheap and cheerful, I'll walk down the hall to a fast-food joint. If I want a surprisingly delightful experience I will go to...Holt's, are you listening?
Nice oasis in downtown...stylish and relaxed. Simple cocktail menu and nice tea menu. Cheese board is nicely out together.

The owner was a delight - friendly and spot on with his recommendations. I started with the Beef Carpaccio generously sprinkled with fresh grated Parmesan and my spouse had the colourful and flavourful Caprese Salad. For my entree we had the veal medallions Il Posto and veal chop. The portions were perfect and accompaniments were fresh, flavourful presented with creative flair. We didn’t have room for dessert but that didn’t stop us from ordering the chocolate banana meringue cake and a bowl of Amaretto ice cream. We are big fans of restaurants that can serve up traditional recipes with creativity and we were not disappointed. Thank you Sokol and chef for sticking around despite the weather.
