To the owner; if you are that desperate to grab people's money we'll here u go!!!!!!! See if anyone or who knows your doing will even come anywhere near that vicinity! reviews.text: This place, as always is exceptional! I've been to insomnia many times and have not been disappointed even once. I recently went back and had the Charlotte...

This was a really pretty restaurant near Danforth Subway St. They had Christmas decorations on (not too much) and it looks fantastic.
 
Customer Service was...

Yummy brunch date spot!

Food: 4/5 Simple but yummy menu
Service: 4/5 Fast and friendly
Environment: 4/5 Modern but busy
Washrooms: 4/5 Okay
Worth it?: 4/5...

Friendly staff, lots of seating and cozy environment. They have lots of good food choices also. The service wasn't the fastest (for food) so be sure you aren't rushed to go somewhere after. It's a good place to catch up with friends or go on a date. Would definitely come back here.

I went to insomnia on Saturday morning for bunch. Got there at about 11AM and put our name in for a table. We ended up waiting 50 minutes to get our table. Food was definitely worth the wait.

I got the eggs Benedict with smoked salmon. It came with an arugula salad which had a great dressing and potatoes with also an amazing sauce. Mimosas were only $5 and could be made with grapefruit, orange, or cranberry. Great brunch spot. Definitely need to try to go earlier though if you want to avoid the wait.

A damn fine place for brunch. Tasty and huge portions at a decent price makes it really attractive with the college crowd. The drinks both alcoholic and non-alcoholic are great. Can't complain with $5 mimosas!

Really cool vibes, very cheap beer after 11pm, but felt my dinner was just OK. I had the mushroom white wine penne and was not that impressed, but also not disappointed. Our waiter was super sweet and friendly, which made the whole experience even better. Note that fries do not come with burgers, so remember to order then extra. Really enjoyed the decor, and loved the lights on the ceiling. Overall nice time, great for a large party (we had about 14 people served quickly and nicely)

Don’t go here if you are hungry because you will not be fed before dying of starvation.  Waited 40 minutes for a table. Finally got seated. Server took another 25 minutes to take our order and then we had a lovely hour and a half wait for our food to come. Better off going to cooking school and mastering the art of poaching eggs for yourself - you’ll get a diploma before your order from Insomnia ever comes to your table.

lic_profile: The first North American location of Jamie Oliver’s internationally known brand of restaurant opened in 2015 at Toronto’s Yorkdale Shopping Centre. Jamie’s Italian has an inviting, relaxed atmosphere, consistent with other locations worldwide offering simple, freshly made Italian-inspired dishes with a Jamie twist. Focusing on fresh, sustainable ingredients and bold, classic flavours, the nofuss menu includes delicious bruschettas, made-to order pizzas, and antipasti planks of cured meats, cheeses and vegetables.

The restaurant features high ceilings and an open kitchen, accented by vintage school chairs, leather banquettes and a statement wall of reclaimed wood. A welcoming bar and friendly service will make each guest feel like they’re at their new favourite local gathering spot. The restaurant design is also family-friendly. Unique to the area, a private mezzanine dining area with space to seat 24 for a meal will provide an ideal place for work functions or for family and friends to come together.

reviews.text: I've been a huge fan of Jamie's since he was the Naked Chef, so any chance I get to dine at his restaurants, I do - whether it is in Toronto or in London,...
Big new restaurant by the famous chef Jamie Oliver.  Lots of high expectations for a place like this, even if it's not intended as fine dining.  No fuss no...
Update: Perhaps the magic isn't there anymore or I just thought it was there when it wasn't.. Came back for a friend's bday yesterday and the service was...

Amazing food at an excellent price point. I have been to many restaurants around the world including those with Michelin stars and this one stood out for two reasons:excellent food(better than some from expensive restaurants) and fantastic value for your money--I would pay more for some of the dishes I had as would my friend. The only reason I am not giving five stars is that the server,although good and friendly,lacked basic knowledge of authentic Italian food-she tried to talk us out of a semolina-orange cake which we ordered anyway as we had a good understanding of regional Italian cooking and thought it sounded delicious;it was. Going back tomorrow with my Mom...-Thank you to Jamie and his team. Keep up the good work!

It was good, but not amazing. Perhaps I had a high expectation of this restaurant since it's from Jamie Oliver. I ordered the lunch special with the nachos and linguine. Nachos were interesting as they were deep fried squared puffs; the salsa sauce was a little bland. Linguine was pretty good except that the pasta was a little undercooked (i.e. it was pretty hard + chewy). Service and atmosphere was good. Other than that, worth a try, but expected more from this restaurant.

My friends and I came here for a meal after another restaurant wasn't seating people anymore.  Jamie's was pretty full but there was still a lot of space for the evening and got seated right away.  It was a homey and warm atmosphere albeit a little loud.

Once seated, we got our water and took the waitress quite a long time to get back to take our order.  We were pretty hungry. 

I ordered the breaded Turkey and the Buffalo Mozzarella. Salad.  I thought the mozzarella salad was delicious with endive, drizzled vinegar and citrus.  Well balanced and lovely.  The Turkey, however, was a schnitzel which I was expecting more of a cordon blue.  Not much stuffing and the breading was too over powering to taste the truffle shavings.  Slightly disappointing.

Overall, the food and service was mediocre but if you need a place for resonably priced food and drinks, this is a place to go!

The food was delicious and the portions are a decent size. Just a note that the appetizers were not portioned for sharing. The waiter was very friendly and knowledgeable about the food. The reason I didn't give it more stars is we were there as a family celebrating a birthday and they sat us next to the door to the patio (it was cold that evening) and beside the cashier (my poor hubby kept having to move his chair). I don't know if this was because we had a small child with us and they wanted us away from other diners. I would understand this reasoning were it not for the fact that there was another family with a child in a stroller that was seated in the main dining area. Plus they charged us a $3 per slice fee to cut the cake we brought. They did a splendid job of serving the cake but I have brought cakes to restaurants for birthdays before (many, many times) and have never been charged a slicing fee. I can see if you bring a dessert in and it isn't a special occasion but for a birthday you would think they would be more accommodating. That being said, the food was very good and the atmosphere laid back which is nice for bringing families.

Food: 4.6 out of 5 it's pretty good. Close to great. 
Food presentation: 4.4 out of 5, really can't find their flaw. It's the whole presentation overall is good. I have been to a few great Italian restaurant. You will know when great presentation is present to you. Something is missing.
Ambience: 5 out of 5, love it. Not very fancy, it's great atmosphere for gathering with friends and family. It's cozy. It's quite down-to-earth. 
Service: 4.9 out of 5, our waitress tried. On a busy Saturday dinner, restaurant is full house, it's hard for her to listen. She is quite attentive. 
Price: 2.5 out of 5. Somewhat pricey. Eating at Yorkdale in a restaurant name after a celebrity chef, can't complain.
Overall 4.7 out of 5. I guess the name brand itself give us a high expectation. It turns out almost meet up these expectations. No complaints.

Overall a very solid family restaurant. The menu had a good selection of food and variety of items. Some seemed a little pricey in comparison to other similar style restaurants. There was something on the menu for everyone though. 

My meal of ribs were good. The mashed potatoes than came with them were a little bland, and I wished that the hot sauce had a little more heat to it. 

The service was fantastic for our large group though and the venue itself was great. While it was the middle of winter we didn't get to enjoy the patio, but it seems like a great spot come summer time.

Love this place. Staff are friendly and typically efficient. Three favourite dishes are: 1.GRILLED VEGETABLE SANDWICH ($15 with a side) 2. SANTA FE SALAD ($24) & 3. SEAFOOD LINGUINI ($26)
Wish they would add a few more Pescetarian meals to the menu.

Always the greatest staff...was met by Olga and served by Tim. He was kind, attentive and got us a sparkler for our son's ice cream - it was his third birthday. Bathrooms are clean and tidy and the food and drinks come out fast.

Pretty good food. $12 lunch menu (till 3pm) is a good option if you are stopping by for lunch. Dinner is pretty good as well, though I think a bit pricey for the kind of food that is offered. Portion size is good, enough where you'll probably take some with you.
I've always enjoyed their service, food and drinks. I'd recommend it to most people.

It's been my favorite place to enjoy lunch for the last 15 years. Great atmosphere, lots of background chatter and a nostalgic decor with a great menu. The food is fresh and the portions are adequate. The service is friendly and they check on you during your meal. Get there early if you want to avoid the line-up at lunch time. I love their grain bowl, their greek salad and the liver and onions. Their white wine never disappoints me. They also have gluten-free bread option. If you didn't have time for desert, have a look at their cookies when pay your bill at the cash. Enjoy!

Awesome restaurant - every meal they make, they do it up right. Fantastic and friendly service from all their staff. Beautiful interior and small patio for the summertime. Definitely the best Indian cuisine available in the greater Toronto area - possibly all of Ontario!
very good food and great staff. some unusual dishes worth trying. dont be afraid. better than Amaya which is our takeout spot.

Went back tonight after a great experience the night we arrived in Toronto last week. That night the blonde female waitress was excellent.
As a vegetarian I was impressed with the wide selection of options and found the food to be absolutely phenomenal and genuinely the nicest curry I've ever had.
However tonight the food was great but found the male waiter to be way off the mark. 4 of us went in and were seated. I ordered a Guinness but was given a cider which I pointed out and it was immediately changed. When the waiter was taking our food order, halfway through the first member of our group ordering he interrupted and said something along the lines of "hold on, order your dishes first and then tell me what nan bread you would like". 
When our food arrived it was great, however twords the end of our meal we noticed we had recieved a huge amount of butter nan - when we pointed this out to the waiter he said "that's what you asked for, I called the order back to you", when we stated that we had only ordered one nan each he said "yes, but I called the order back to you!", (bit strange to argue with a customer) after we sat in silence for an awkward moment he said he'd take the extra nan off our bill. I think he made the mistake of writing the nan down twice when he asked for our dishes before our nans and confused the situation.
When we were finished eating it took a while to get attention. We weren't offered tea or coffee or asked did we want a dessert menu. When we asked for separate bills he said "ye should have told me it would be separate bills at the start" and seemed annoyed about it. 
I'm sure it probably seems like I'm being very dramatic and hope I took him up wrong but his demeanour was wrong and it made me feel uncomfortable and unwelcome. 
If I eat here again maybe it'll just be a takeaway unfortunately.
Chicken tikka and vindaloo are great choices. Elegant restaurant.

They have good selection on their menu and I definitely suggest go with their lunch specials. It might seem a little expensive but you will have a choice of 3 course meal.

Definitely a should try place.

No smiling, non-professional, and for that alone this place loses a few stars. Also, it’s quite crammed.. tables very close to one another. Went on a Tuesday night and it was very busy! Definitely a hot spot if you love Japanese food.
Excellent service and amazing food. The lobster tacos are a must. Great place for a special night (it is pricey).

I'm Japanese, but there were almost no customers look Japanese, and staff are Canadian. It has the normal level of quality of food with very expensive cost compared to the ones in Japan. The interior and the customer service there are great but the taste is not authentic enough while trying create the style as hi-ranked and very expensive Japanese food.

I'd love to give this restaurant a higher rating because the space is beautiful. The food is good but portions are on the small side. The desserts could use some attention. My main concern was the service. I don't have terribly high standards but the host and wait staff were disorganized from the moment we showed up. Nobody offered to check our coats which is fine because the coat check is actually just a bunch of rolling racks in the public space outside of the restaurant. The host checked in a group of people who arrived after us and without a reservation, before showing us to our table where people were waiting. Our server didn't introduce herself, she just started talking over us to ask if we were ready to order. Left feeling underwhelmed.

Loved the food here and also loved how smooth the sound system is too.
It's a good spot for groups, it has a great view.
There is a bar side and a dinning side; I really dig the room design. 
If you're traveling from out of town, this is a great spot to check out.

The very seating comfortable and there is a coat check.

Hope this place will continue to develop excellent experience.

My friends and I had an amazing experience! I called in a few weeks prior to see if they could accommodate a party of 14 for a birthday - they said it wouldn't be a problem at all. I had to make a last-minute change to 12, and on the day of, a switch to 13 - all the while, they were very patient and accommodating.  

They set up an amazing 4-course menu. Wine selection was very good. Cocktails were great! Love the cozy interior! A wonderful addition to the neighbourhood. The experience as a whole was amazing, and parts of it (most importantly the delicious food) reminded me of my time in France. 

I'll definitely be back to sample more of their menu!

While this unassuming location could serve your need for a quality cocktail or glass of wine, I opted for a four course meal built around my taste. Water buffalo was amazing (never had before!) And wine pairing was excellent. High quality meal without the pretense! Reasonable cost for the high quality local sourced ingredience. One of the best meals I've had in a long time. You won't be disappointed!
We had an amazing dinner off the tasting menu tonight! Great food and wine, great atmosphere and great value. So glad we found this place.

What an amazing experience. My friends and I made reservations to celebrate our birthdays and were highly impressed. We did a tasting (my first time) and were walked through the process thoroughly. My friends did chef's choice while I had dietary restriction (which they went above and beyond in accommodating for). Even though I did post a picture of the food; it doesn't do it justice as it was top class food for a reasonable price. 
The highlight of the meal was the veal water buffalo. I doubt I'll be able find anything like that elsewhere. The duck, the escargot, the desert plater and cow shoulder were also top notch.

After visiting the St. Lawrence market, I wanted to...

I dislike having to write unfavourable reviews, but my wife & I were quite disappointed with our meals at Le Papillon on a recent Saturday evening.

First...

I have been here a few times and all visits have been splendid! The servers are very friendly, helpful and courteous. This is a perfect place for special occasions, dates or having dinner and wine with friends. They offer the best French Onion Soup I have ever tasted. I also recommend the Escargot and an entree from the daily specials.

I ordered the Cesar salad as appetizer. It had great flavour with a hearty portion of cheese. My main was the traditional tourtiere. It was excellent. It came with mashed potatoes. They were rustic with skin on. Quite tasty.   The side of veggies included beets. One of my favorites which you don't see often! 

For dessert I had the key lime pie. It was a bit watery and didn't have much of a lime flavor.

I would definitely try Le Papillon again for a special occasion.

Food was very good...quick service but almost too quick.  Felt a a little rushed at the end of the meal.  The restaurant was very warm and we expressed this concern to our waitress and the manager who didn't seem to care.   Manager said I was dressed to warmly and he was fine.

One of the best restaurants in Toronto. Great ambiance with delicious food and excellent service. They have free valet parking which makes life so much easier. The staff are very nice and attentive. We felt very welcomed and well cared for. We always enjoy the food. Their seasonal recipes are a great way of taking advantage of what's in season. We always have a fantastic experience here. Highly recommended!!

lic_profile: Praised as one of the "Ten Chefs of the Millennium" in 2000 by food & Wine magazine, Susur Lee is still at the top of his game. Between helming three restaurants in Toronto - Lee, Bent & Luckee - and overseeing his prestigious TungLok Heen in Singapore, Chef Lee makes numerous television appearances and travels the globe as guest chef and consultant. Balancing the epicurean traditions of China with the classical techniques of French cuisines, Chef Lee improvises a daring and original culinary aesthetic.

Frequently appearing many of Toronto publication's "Best of" lists, Lee offers a menu inspired by the convergence of land and sea with seasonality in mind.  From the bar comes a sake driven wine list and fresh-to-order cocktails with handmade ingredients.

lic_profile: A Chef Anthony Walsh creation, Leña pays homage to his Argentinian mother-in-law, Elena, from whom he has drawn great culinary inspiration, and embodies what he experiences in her kitchen – a passionate food philosophy that brings people together. Imaginative yet rooted in tradition, Leña’s cuisine showcases the vibrant essence of South American cooking, with unique Spanish and Italian influences. It, along with the stylish design, warm character and lively tunes, promotes a “live to eat” ethos and fosters a convivial spirit at the table. Above all, Leña celebrates authentic, flavourful food and drink, enjoyed amongst old and new friends.

I came here on a Sunday after stopping by Kleinfield. Service was really slow, we did have a group of 5 but I still don't think that would warrant a 45 min...
Came in around 2PM for lunch on a weekday, it wasn't full but there were couple of occupied tables. I always wanted to dine here as they have beautiful...

The place is much smaller than I expected. And far too noisy for my taste. Upstairs they have corner tables where the chairs are angled, making it a rather odd sitting arrangement for dinner. You end up looking at your dinner companion at weird angles or leaning away awkwardly when being served.

Service wasn't bad, our server was nice when we asked to be seated at a different table as I couldn't sit so awkwardly for the duration of the evening.

We did the Taste of Iceland menu, and this I have to say: the smoked salmon and arctic char trio were the highlight of the evening. I'd say the smoked salmon was one of the best tasting I've had anywhere.

Apart from that, food was presented nicely and tasted good, as were the wine pairings.

All in all, it's a place to go to if you don't mind the noise level. Nothing exceptional (smoked salmon not withstanding), but not terrible either, prices are on par with midrange restaurants downtown.
We had a great experience hosting a corporate event. Everyone loved the food and the service was fantastic! The decor is exceptional. I would definitely come here again.
Such a lovely place downtown Toronto, Kevin is a amazing waiter. He did helped us find the appropriate wine for the diner. I highly recommend this place

Place has nice decoration but layout is a bit cramped. We were a party of 6 ordered at the same time, 2 of us got a 4 course meal with wine pairings.  We got our apps an hour after ordering, and only saw our waiter once an hour, we were there for over 3hrs. The 4 course meal was served out of order and wine pairings for it were also out of order. And we got our entrees before the rest of the table had their food and had to wait 20+ min before everyone else got their food.  We had to complain 2x to get their attention.  Service was not good, my 2star rating is only for the chef as the food was good, just service was horrible - cutting lamb and rib steak with a butter knife was not fun.
This restaurant is really nice. Convenient to go by subway. The brunch was really good. We ordered full Gaucho, breakfast empanada  and toast. Everyone loves all dishes.

reviews.text:
This is my second time here, the first time was for brunch a few weeks ago.

Didn't realize how nice this place was as from the outside it just looks like a...
This review is limited to the basement (brew pub) as it was late night and upstairs was closed.  We came in after the Royal Winter Fair was over - so around...
Good place to visit if you're looking for pub-food or somewhere to watch a sports game.  Drinks can definitely be very cheap certain nights, but I'm not a...

We had the toasted marshmallow soft serve and the sticky toffee pudding. It was fantastically sweet. The soft serve was nutty,buttery and light. The pudding's heavy sweetness was nicely complemented by the refreshing vanilla ice cream. We drink a lot of water, so we appreciated that it came in a half gallon growler. Staff were very friendly and quick - we were practically swarmed by 4 staff members for service. The pudding wasn't punched in correctly, but the manager quickly took a discount off our bill, so we were very happy overall with the service and the quality of food.
Venue is very nice.  Great bar and patio. We came for brunch and the food was very good. Service was a bit slow and our server was very monotone.  Not very friendly but service was ok.
Possible that we were there on an off-night, but it doesn't really stand out, given the bar-saturation in the area.  Definitely not a bad choice for a pint though.

We got the shared meal called Coq in the Can and it was delicious! The house made sauce was very good when paired with the chicken.  Very clean and great atmosphere! Friendly staff as well! Definitely going to come back!
We had a short wait on a Saturday with a lot of things going on in the city. Once in, service was fast, server was polite, and food was great. Would come again.

Ahh, forgot to post this from Sept. :(

The main course was very good and one serving was more than enough for both of us.

The food and service were continuously friendly, attentive, and informative.

Incredible brunch! I got the Double Pancake Pork Burger and it was like a Big Mac but sooo much better. The Pad Thai fries though are what sold me. Great food and great service!
Great place for brunch, menu is "éclectique". Food is is delicious, environment is young and hipster. Music was a bit loud but the food makes up for it. Best of all, you can make a reservation!!!!
Very cool atmosphere and really amazing food! Interesting and fun menu items! Will definitely go back.

I had the bacon explosion benedict for brunch and waiter suggested the pad thai fries. The pad thai fries was good, although a little spicy. reviews.text:
I was invited to a business dinner here with 5 others, and we were treated to excellent service, beautiful decor and great food. 

We were there for 4 hours...
Including today,  I have been here twice now.  Both times it was for a company lunch - the first time we ordered from their regular menu and the second time...

We were very disappointed with our experience. 

We made a reservation for 7PM and arrived at 6:50. We were not greeted and the hostess only came around...

Very flavorful food preparation with a nice, but small, wine selection. Traveling alone I appreciated the nice wine by the glass selection. Staff was extremely nice and always making sure I was taken care of through the dining experience. It is always hard to judge/grade Italian restaurants since everyone has their own preferences on flavor of sauces. I felt they provided a Good flavorful selection for my tastes. I will come here again

Little Anthony's has the highest quality ingredients all wrapped up with Italian love. The service is beyond impeccable and the food classic with surprising little twists. House make ricotta to slather on warm crusty bread is sure to please as are any of the really cool pasta dishes. Fish is treated with respect and that always makes me happy. Save room for dessert. The list is short and perfect.

We appreciated the attentive and friendly nature of the staff but the food was very ordinary and fell far short of our expectations.  For example, the Caesar salad was not crisp but rather soggy with too much dressing; the salmon was overcooked and on the dry side even though I asked for it to be prepared medium. Overall the food was more on par with an East Side Mario's type of establishment (no slant against East Side Mario's) but not what we expected from LA's. On the positive side, the Minestrone soup was good and full of fresh vegetables. Based on this first time experience, I would not go out of my way to return to LA's.
A must try appetizer is the honey ricotta. Carbonara isn't authentic, more like Canadian Italian rather than Italian. Pasta with clams was almost perfect.
Wonderful Italian restaurant. Perfect for a business lunch or meeting. The food is delicious.

On the advise from a business associate, we made reservations for dinner last week and it was worth it!  We were a party of 6 and if you need your space while dining then this might be a little too cozy for you.  The restaurant had the feel of dining in Europe and the atmosphere was lively and fun.  Our waitress helped us along the way throughout the entire meal and each plate was just what we expected.  Looking forward to our next visit!

Love this place. Cozy and intimate vibe with delicate food that has great flavour. Its just unique enough  that you feel like you aren't  getting the same food as everywhere else. Service is also excellet. You can order anything on the menu and you won't be disappointed.

Great food and service. Great place for a date or celebration for a small group. Very intimate yet not posh or upscale. 5 star cuisine with local ingredients at a modest price and relaxed unassuming setting. Portion sizes are perfect.

This restaurant did not meet expectations at all. The cocktails were so unbalanced (too sweet, or too much campari, etc) that no one at the table could drink them. Mains were either too dry or too greasy. We all had complaints, with the exception of the brussel sprouts appetizer, we all loved that. I wanted to like this place since we were referred by friends but won't be going back.

Came here to celebrate my friend's birthday and came based on a recommendation from another friend.

We made reservations in advance and were seated as soon...

Was present at this restaurant celebrating two birthday . We are met with warm smiles and great attitudes. I notice there were selling Avon (best tequila IMO). I was excited to taste it again. Definitely would go back

Celebrate a friend's birthday. She love the experience. She usually does not order much but she could not stop eating and drinking because of the friendly service by our waiter and the food was amazing. Be preparing but it is worth it. I spent this birthday dinner around $250 with tip.

Came here a Summerlicious lunch with a few friends. Ordered the chicken salad for appetizer, and the baked chicken for the main course. The chicken was okay although it lacked flavor. The baked chicken was soft and tender and flavorful and came on top of some sticky rice. The dessert was a tea spoon of very flavorful ice cream (very good), a small piece of sponge cake and a small fried glutinous rice ball in chocolate sauce. The overall experience was so so. After spending close to $30 on a lunch ... I was still hungry.

Came with a party of two, and tried their tasting menu. It's different because it isn't a set menu, and it's based off of if you're still hungry. So things can add up pretty fast. We ordered a bottle of red, and had maybe 5 dishes. It came up to around $200. Just to give an approximation of price. Food was alright. I wouldn't say it was spectacular, but it was good. If price was a little more affordable, I'd go back.
Delicious - so different from any other restaurant in the city. Everything we had was great. Service was friendly, and helpful. Definitely going back!
Nice atmosphere with excellent food. The wait staff was very knowledgeable BUT tended to push certain dishes too heavily instead of just listening to what we wanted to order.

Very cool vibe and awesome menu of non - traditional dim sum. Highly recommend the Rainbow Basket from the menu and then the options from the carts.

The cocktails are excellent although I was surprised there weren't twists on the brunch standards line Bloody Mary or mimosa.

They lost a star because I was starving and the carts felt like they took forever to show up and our server was new and slightly clueless about brunch service.

The atmosphere makes this place stand out! We opted to eat on the rooftop patio for an amazing view of the CN Tower and Downtown Toronto and the view was...

The service was fantastic.  The venue is well designed and spacious.  Enough room to feel private but still experience the overall experience of the space.

Granted, they were 2 days in to a new menu however my dish (The Duck) missed the mark.  The sausage and the overall salt content overpowered all of the other elements of the dish.  The duck was overly tough.  

Looking forward to the opportunity to trying some other parts of the menu as I feel this may have just been an off dish.

Great overall experience.

Luma is the perfect place for an upscale lunch in the city. The restaurant is really well furnished, the atmosphere is calm and sophisticated, really easy to talk to each other. The lunch menu is not too long ( I appreciate a short menu because usually means that the ingredients are fresh) and prices are not much higher than any other lunch restaurant in the area. The food is in tune with the location, sophisticated and really really good!

Luma was a big disappointment. We booked the private room for a group of 11 (of which ambiance wasn't great - it feels 'cold' and office-like - the table looks cheap and in need of work). We had the chef's appetizers selection which were mediocre at best - steak tartar on a toast (not a great selection for a group), veggie spring rolls and jerk chicken sliders. I then had the kale salad for my first course - it was the worst salad I had at a good restaurant ever! The leafs were soggy and it felt like the salad was sitting in the fridge with the dressing on for an hour or more. 
For main I had a duck dish, which was the best part of the meal - it was well made and tasty. 
Then came the bill - we were charged for 12 people even though we were 11, as 'this is what the reservation'. We actually did send an email in the morning to update that we will be 11, but it shouldn't have mattered as the minimum order for the room is $800 and we spent well over $2000 - they insisted to have us pay for 12 and said that the events coordinator will contact us the next day and reimburse us the difference if all is fine.  That's awful customer service!

Had a birthday dinner at Luma, and our group of approximately 20 people was easily accommodated between two tables. It was a very nice setup, the service was on point, and the food/drinks were enjoyed by all. Definitely worth repeat visits.
Came here after a show. Fantastic food, great atmosphere. Our waitress Meaghan was enthusiastic, attentive, and engaging.

There's an outdoor patio that I'm sure it would be lit AF when weather is nice. I came here to grab drinks one Friday night two weeks ago after having had dinner at La Cubana which is right across. Their cocktail, beer, and wine menu are extensive. The staff is charming and I need to definitely bring someone on a date here. I just need to be patient.

The bistro feels relaxing on the bar side with booths, counter seats and high tables. It also has a more formal dining section with dim lights and candles. It was quite busy on the Wednesday night when I visited it. The food was ok. Price wise, it's about $50+ per person for a beer and a couple of dishes.

Small family-owned place with a cozy vibe where everything is cooked from scratch in all the delicious Indian aromas you crave, made with love from family recipes that infuse just a touch of Thai flair. The people were nice, though.

I've been...

Best Italian food in the area, by far. Pizza was great but the gnocchi were incredible. We enjoyed it so much we went back for a second time and the service was very good and quite fast. The pasta was cooked perfectly and tasted amazing.

The bread basket had two types of pizza and thin cuts of bread. The mini pizza slices were amazing but the bread was very dense and dry.

Mezza Notte has true authentic Italian food.   North York is lucky to have such a fantastic restaurant.  Great food, Daily specials always available.  Take out, Delivery, Dine In, family gatherings, office parties;  I have experienced  all of these events and have never had a negative experience.  The service is great from the chef's in the kitchen, wait staff, phone operators and the owners  always attentive and always reliable.  My most favorite italian restauraunt in the city...

lic_profile: Michael's on Simcoe, located in the heart of downtown Toronto, is an upscale, modern steak house with an Italian touch. Specializing in premium beef, seafood and handmade pastas, carefully selected ingredients are sourced from trusted suppliers who only offer the finest of products. White table cloth service is complemented by valet service five nights a week, a gorgeous bar and lounge offers live music four nights a week and the exquisitely designed dining room is accented by a fireplace. The menu is enhanced by Wine Spectator award winning wine list featuring nearly 700 offerings.

The sommelier nailed it with a great...
Came here for a business meal and had an incredible meal. First impression upon walking in -- the atmosphere was sophisticated and inviting. The hostess...
This restaurant tries to put themselves out there as high class. Unfortunately, they fall a little short as I wasn't sold on mainly quality of food, price...

We had a birthday dinner at Michael's on Thursday night. There was lovely live music, acoustic guitar and piano. The food was to die for! Such a great selection of dishes, cannot wait to come again for dinner with my coworkers this weekend. What an incredible experience, 5 star dining, service, food, drinks and atmosphere. Couldn't have been more impressed. Highly recommend.

My compliments to the chef and whole team.

This place has been on my “things to do in Toronto” list for some time. I feel stupid for not visiting sooner. 
I am a pasta snob/scientist and I don’t always try pasta when I am in restaurants but, when I do it is because of unique placeless like this, superb! 

What is being executed here can only come from a place of genuine passion for food and the arts. The quality and selection of meat, music, wine, brown-booze etc all top notch. 

The menu is exceptional and very reasonably priced. The physical environment is spotless, fresh, warm, modern, business casual a perfect spot for any occasion in my humble opinion.

We recently had an amazing experience at Michael's. It's a great place with exquisite food, knowledgeable staff and perfect customer service. We were recommended excellent wine pairings with each particular dish which made our experience outstanding. Everything was paced perfectly making it a wonderful dining experience. Absolutely recommend Michael's, and can't wait for our next visit!

I went to Michael's recently with two friends and had a great evening! Going to a steak restaurant as a vegetarian isn’t normally my first choice but there were tons of options which were all great. They even had a vegan “steak” made from eggplant! The food and service we both amazing. Our server was very sweet and attentive and other staff members checked in to make sure we were okay several times. We were given great recommendations and had wine paired with our dishes which was really nice. The live music was really nice, and added to the already great atmosphere. Can’t wait to go back 😊

Long overdue review.... but wow! This restaurant blew me away with their service and food quality. We were a table of 4 that stumbled upon this gem because all the other fine dining seems to be booked up. We walked in expecting good things since reviews looked good online but we all know this is not necessarily true all the time. Being a high end steakhouse, the steaks held up to its name but surprisingly the pastas and apps did not lag behind at all. I have dined in some fancy restaurants in the past but from the owner to the servers, this place really go out of their way to please their customers and that itself makes it worth spending your money on. Thoroughly impressed and will make it back again!

lic_profile: Miku Toronto, Aburi Restaurant's first east coast location, is situated at Bay and Queen’s Quay. With over 7000 square feet, a raw bar, sushi bar, large patio and private dining rooms, Miku brings contemporary upscale design to the southern Financial District. Corporate Executive Chef Kazuya Matsuoka along with Chef de Cuisine Michael Acero and Head Sushi Chef Kazuki Uchigoshi bring Aburi Cuisine to Toronto combining traditional Japanese flavours and techniques with local, East Coast elements to create a truly unique dining experience. The menu focuses on Aburi Sushi as well as fresh seafood, respecting the natural flavours of the ingredients while adding a signature Aburi twist. Japanese and European inspired desserts made in house create the perfect ending to the culinary experience. The menu is complemented with signature cocktails, wines, and an extensive sake list. Knowledgeable staff is always happy to make suggestions on pairings that will please your palate.

reviews.text: Miku has quickly become my favourite sushi restaurant in Toronto. My boyfriend took me here for my birthday and I am so happy he did! Every piece of sushi...
I love this place.  My first experience was in Vancouver at Miku and was excited when they opened in TO.  Expect to pay premium but I feel you get more than...
From the service to the food to the decor, this is probably one of the best experiences I've had for sushi in Toronto so far. Our server was extremely...

First time came here with my boyfriend, the restaurant looks truly great. We simply wanted a spicy salmon roll, however we couldn't see it on the menu so we decided to ask our server if the chef can make us a spicy salmon roll off the menu. 
I would give a five star to only my server who name is Angela as she instantly provided all the services we needed with great smile. However, we were successfully disappointed by the spicy salmon roll ( or not even) The presentation of the plate looked great, yet the taste of food was quite a failure. The salmon meat was quite chewy and fishy, they probably used the worst part of the salmon ( the belly ) to make the entire dish, which means the salmon wasn't even cut properly. Ridiculously, they filled the roll with asparagus, we were both stunned by such a weird combination. Maybe the chef was trying to impress the guests with some creative ideas, or maybe it was just us who can't appreciate the taste. Anyways, It would have been much better if it was a regular spicy salmon roll. I was disgusted a while after as I could still taste the fishy flavor in my moth. 
When we requested our bill from another server, we were stunned again by her ruddiness as she only pointed her index finger to suggest that she will be with us soon as she was quickly passing by. Finally, one of the host lady with glasses came to us to collect the money with no facial expression or whatsoever. 
The reason we came to this restaurant was because the 4.5 google review. Until this point,  for me this place is overrated by its fancy look, menu design, yet hardly see the value of food and service.

Wait staff were on the ball, once you're done your dishes they would take it away and wipe your table. Service was great, food is amazing. The prime rib strangely enough was absolutely delicious. I never would have imagined my favourite prime rib would be at a Japanese restaurant! We tried the Miku set dinner and from start to finish all items were excellent and served together and on time. Would come here again

Sushi quality here is good and was up to expectations. Although I find the price to quality ratio is not as good as some of the competitors it is still a wonderful place to visit at least once. The interior though feels a bit too modern and contemporary and is probably not something I personally prefer at this price point and level. But still delicious fishes here to eat.

Many very interesting dishes, tantalizingly presented, with fresh and tasty ingredients. Never had to wait long for a table, however kinda weird that we have been seated at the same table each visit ;-) Staff have been generally very helpful and attentive. However, there have been times where we have waited a bit too long between courses.
Went there for dinner last night. The best calamari I had in a while. The main course was as good as the appetizers. The staff was extremely helpful. Will definitely visit again.

Service and view of the kitchen is the added bonus but wine and knowledgeable staff takes the cake. Oyster Thursdays are always a nice touch from 5:30-7.. It's always a nice treat without having to be in the busy core

Delicious brunch! Their potatoes are nicely fried and seasoned. So far all of the breakfast sandwiches are always delicious with no issues or complaints. Only thing I didn’t like was the long wait times during the weekends and perhaps the very modern feeling interior. Personal preference for a more cozy environment for brunch but this doesn’t take away anything from Mildred. Absolutely fantastic food and service.

Went with a group of four Dec 2017. Top notch service, felt very well looked after. 

Ate family style so I got to try quite a few items on the menu.  Food was excellent, all meat was cooked to perfection. If I had to find something to complain about, its that the menu seemed to lack a signature dish - there wasn't any over the top dish that completely knocks your socks off. 

Will definitely be adding this spot to my regular rotation.

Food is the only thing that is good there to my view. Service is average at best, attention to details front the wait staff that is expected from such a place is non existent. Serving 2 different glass for one bottle of wine is just one of many.The ambiance i guess to reach his own, just not my cup of tea. This said would I go back? Maybe! Just not at my own will.
Friendly and warm environment!   Great food and service! Got to meet the owner Paolo, whose constant attention to detail makes Mistura special!

Where do i begin ! Everything was perfect.  Wait staff extremely attentive, very helpful.  the owner Paolo went out of his way to welcome us and even showed us his new lounge upstairs. Super friendly.  The food was to die for.  Lamb ribs and beet risotto are a MUST.  Will be returning for sure !

I took my best friend out to Mistura for birthday March break weekend. The place was spectacular, the bartender suggested an awesome drink that we later enjoyed with dinner. Our waiter was amazing (wish I could remember his name it was really unique). He plated our food properly, answered any questions, just made us feel really special for being there. I would go back simply because of the waiter he was amazing. The food was pretty and the place is very classy, beautiful ambiance.

The pisco sour is terrible... they should not be offering it as it diminishes one of the best drink cocktails in the world. Overall would not recommend if you want good peruvian experience.

This is not authentic Peruvian Food, The Jalea has Huancaina sauce on top, Anticuchos with sweet potato, Lomo Saltado with yuca instated of fries, ceviche with juice of pomegranate, the picarones were hard and pale   this restaurant only cares about presentation but the food is not in anyway as our bandera food , they want to do it as gourmet but to be honest I prefer the original Peruvian food .

The first time I went I got good service but the food was alright. The anticuchos were good, aside from that The ceviche felt it lacked a lot of flavour. My second visit I went with family and friends to watch the Peru vs New Zealand soccer game. The TVs were unsynced with the sound. We might as well have been listening to the radio because the image was much more delayed than the commentary. We had a long wait for our food and drinks. But we were trying to enjoy our night and watch the game with atmosphere. My friend waited over an hour for his food . He was promised to get comped for a plate. He offered to pay for half. When it was time to pay the owner came out and accused him of not being a man and lacking intengrity. He said if he did not have money, there is a Chinese buffet accross the street, but to never come back. He paid for the full sum to not place blame on the waitress. Overall, decent food if you know what to order. Would not recommend otherwise.
Got tray of oyster, one of it so bad and it bring tears in my eyes and I felt I am going to hospitalize. I ran home and drink lot of apple cider vinegar and lemon. I still feel sick.

My husband and I went on Black Friday night. It was really cold that night so we wanted something warm. 

Food: We ordered the pork belly buns (3 per order)...

This is a really trendy spot. I liked the bench seating that was something different, and making a reservation online was a breeze. I really loved what I ate here. The menu doesn't have a whole lot on it, but everything we ordered, my party really enjoyed. The waitress was also really helpful in helping us navigate the menu, which was a little daunting with lots of words we didn't know. With her help we picked what was right for us, and everything is made to be so delicious and everything was nice and warm when it came out. The only down side was that not all of our dishes came out of the kitchen at the same time, so we had one person who was there with nothing in front of them while the rest of us were able to eat.

So delicious, really love the ramen! I've tried all their  no broth noodles and they were all rich in flavour (Pepper Noodle with beef sausage is the best!). Great selections of drinks and desserts. Definitely make reservations, it can get busy. Limited seating area so don't bring too much stuff with you. They just got Caviar and Fired Chicken which serves 4-6, saw people beside us eating it and it looked amazing!!

This restaurant defiantly lives up to the hype.  We went with a group of 7 and ordered the fried chicken dinner.  Unbelievable.  Great atmosphere, excellent service.  I can wait to go again.  Note that if you are interested in the fried chicken dinner you need to make a reservation

I can recommend the pork belly buns and the ginger scallion bowl, they definitely go well together. However, don't sit on the ground floor while on a date unless you want to sit with strangers. It follows a traditional sort of 'beer hall' seating arrangement that works for groups, but quarters are a bit tight if you're a couple. Ambiance is quite upscale, and doesn't quite fit the cuisine in my opinion. It's sort of takes you out of the experience while eating a heartier meal.

Bear in mind this is a casual noodle bar so it's always busy and noisy. Design is modern and chic. Sitting on the 2nd floor will give you a great spot for people watching and meal prepping. The noodles and the soup are on par with any top notch noodle places in T.O. Food comes not too long after ordering. Not pricey considering the location. Definitely a good pick for people working around the area or tourist looking for a unique place to refuel!!!

servers.  Another...
I came here on two separate occasions.  The first time was during the Summerlicious event, and they had certain menu items at a reduced price to let people...

Okay so first I like the location and the style of the place. Very comfortable place. Now for the food the starters were really good specially elk sliders. For the main I got the the beef cheeseburger and the presentation of the plate was great but the taste wasn't the best. I can't put my finger on it why I didn't but it was just a strong uncomfortable taste. For dessert my father enjoyed the pecan pie. Also the waiters are on top of they're job also filling up my drink without me asking and around 10 minute wait for my food. My experience I give it 6.5 out of 10 but my family gave around 7.5/8 out of 10.

Great food, great atmosphere. Server was knowledgeable, including our bartender, Justin. Worth the walk in the freezing cold for our meal! Split the fried chicken burger and burger between hubby and myself, and i wish I was hungrier so I could eat one of each whole. Fries were good too!

Can we just talk about this burger? I mean, it's the best. And yeah, I know that world gets thrown around pretty indiscriminately, but no jokes, this is the one you've been waiting for people. It's a double patty with pickles and cheese on an honest bun with all the fixings you want. I'd eat one now if I could. Oh, and the drinks are good. I mean, I don't really drink much but I see a lot of nice looking cocktails waft by me while I'm choking down that burger. Fancy drinks is what I'd call them. But I usually opt for a coke.

I was surprised by the buzz of this place when I arrived. It was busy for a Sunday night with a great atmosphere. Do not be deceived by the outer appearance, the inside has a feeling of old New York. The food was delicious but the service was lacking. I do believe that was down to my specific server so I've still given a rating of 4. He was inattentive, slow, and when we were finished just sort of left us. No offer of coffees or dessert or the bill, he just sort of moved on to other tables. I would recommend!

We went to Museum Tavern after a visit at the ROM for a drink and snack. We first realize that for a pub it was over price. Anyway we order a nachos which has a good tasting but only serve in 8 pc. That's insane and cost $14.
Honesty i don't think i will recommend it.

Delicious food! With ok service! A must if you like sushi! However be ware of your bill, like any good sushi restaurant the price can go up fast, specially if you choose some of their premium ingredients like imported sea urchin.

Love their sukiyaki hot pot on a cold night. Sushi was fresh.
Good service and nice decor. There is also an option to sit on seiza style on tatami flooring. A bit on the pricy side but the sushi is fresh. Good place to go to for lunch.

reviews.text:
My best friend took me here for a birthday dinner after wanting to try somewhere new (to us) and stumbling upon it on Yelp.

I'm so glad that I did!

The...
Gorgeous decor, terrific service, and wood FIRE! They use it to great effect wherever they can. Definitely will return to try a pasta dish.

Went for drinks in the newly opened bar area and was quite impressed.

Service was top notch. Everyone from the bartender to the bar manager and hostess...

Absolutely delicious!! Cannot recommend enough! Myself and a friend found this little spot for his going away dinner and it was just perfect! The service was top notch, conversational and personal but knowing when to leave us alone, the food was out of this world! Great quality with good portion size and very reasonable!!

Visited Noce for dinner on my last evening of vacation in Toronto - and what a fantastic end to a great week! Everything here is spot on. 
From cocktail to dessert, my meal was superb. The service team are friendly and attentive, the ambiance and decor relaxed and welcoming. I even met the owners. 
I hope I get the chance to visit Toronto again soon; when I do I will definitely be coming back here! I recommend you try it too.

A really lovely neighborhood restaurant. I went with my husband on Sat night and it was a very relaxing atmosphere and an escape from the king west hubbub. We sat in the front dining room which was lively and had the kitchen in it with the wood burning oven. We had a burrata, tomato starter followed by a whole fish. All the food was very fresh and delicious. It was simple but done perfectly which is what you expect in a nice restaurant. Service was on the ball and very pleasant. I'm really glad we finally managed to go here and will definitely be back.

Stood at the door with no greeting or welcome for well over 5 minutes. Reservation was split tables but the restaurant never bothered to tell us theyd be splitting the table up. No one offered to take our coats but everyone who came in afterwards was asked. They were out of regular menu items on a Saturday. Two pizzas served were burnt black on the bottom, not just spots but completely. Overall not a great experience, very disappointed after reading these 5 star reviews. Would not recommend or return.

My boyfriend and I fell in love with this place immediately- the food, the atmosphere, the SERVICE. So we decided to throw my best friends surprise engagement party here. They allowed us to rent out the lounge area AND the patio and worked so hard the entire night to make this the best experience ever for us- which it was. Words cannot express the love i have in my heart for this place and the people we've met. Mikele, Kyle, and to the ENTIRE team- thank you ❤️❤️❤️

Staff and atmosphere are wonderful. Food portions are on the smaller scale, but not unusual for higher style restaurants.  Came here with a colleague and was overall pleased and the valet parking is a lovely bonus.

Summerlicious. Try the Tasmanian pinot.

Located in the heart of downtown, Nota Bene is steps away from the Theatre District and Four Seasons Centre for the Performing Arts.  Open for both Lunch and Dinner, the menu features the fresh, contemporary and globally - inspired cuisine of Chef David Lee.  Whether for a business lunch, celebrating with friends, dinner before the show, or after work cocktails and snacks, Nota Bene is on everyone's shortlist when seeking a great meal downtown.

reviews.text:
New Canadian restaurant conveniently located on the corner of University and Queen.

Service: I thought our hostess and servers that day were super friendly...

I've been here a couple of times and I have to say it's always a hit and miss with the food, but ambience and service is always superb. 
I came here on a...
Came here for a friend's birthday party last night. Despite our table of 8 plus a table of 10 beside us, the restaurant was half empty at 8:30 PM which is a...

It's a fairly expensive and classy looking place, but the service was a bit slow and they forgot a few items.

The rib steak was excellent. 
The venison was awesome.
The "fresh" pasta was average at best.

The molten cheese cake was excellent.
The cheese plate was average.
They forgot the "figgie smalls" cocktail, so I can't speak for it.

Chef David Lee is always tweaking the menu items, so even if the outstanding side dish like the brussel sprouts, you will note that they are always a welcome change as well as a familiar taste to them.
Of course the service is also always top-notch.
I am always happy to dine at a place where I'm made to feel welcome despite my very, VERY laid-back bum-off-the-street vibe and this restaurant with superbly executed food, is a fave for that reason as well. They do get busy, so I highly recommend reservations and don't skip out of any of the entrees, or their delicious cocktails.
Had a wonderful time here. Wait staff is very professional and hospitable. Just wish there was more on the menu for vegetarians.

The service, at least for large groups, is nightmarishly bad. A $60 prix fixe menu was required. No one would take orders or commence service until absolutely everyone was seated. The result: many left with lunch bags. I left 2.5 hours later without the desert paid for (bill was paid 40 minutes earlier). 

If you’re planning an event, consider planning it elsewhere.

Amazing atmosphere, service & food. Our host Celine was such an amazing host. My two colleagues and I requested non ordinary requests & she handled them all with class. Her service, smile & enthusiam is worth the 5 stars.

reviews.text: Welcoming staff, I stay here often after a long days work when I can't face the commute home. Super central location with tons of food around, but honestly...

Hotels Tonight coming through for a mini, unexpected luxury.

We were planning to book through the app, but I figured why not stop in first and see what...
Great place to kick back with your laptop and work on afternoons or weeknights. Affordable drinks and not a sleazy crowd, also has coffee and snacks hat...

Went to OCHO for a wedding - excellent venue. Food was great. Cozy/intimate setting. Service was good. Easily accessible downtown. Only reason for 4/5 instead of 5/5 is not a lot of bathrooms on second floor, and servers making a little bit of noise in the back while people were giving speeches.

We hosted our wedding reception at Hotel Ocho. I'm so thrilled with how everything went: the service leading up to the wedding, during, and after. The food was amazing - our guests are still commenting on how delicious everything was. Would 100% recommend to anyone looking for an interesting location downtown. A+!

Attended a cozy wedding here. The food was tasty and the steak was a good portion. The staff was very apologetic and tried to make it up to some of the mistakes made with food. The upstairs dining can accomodate a large party ( 10 - 12 tables with 6 people at a table) but the stair case cuts the room in half and so it's difficult to hear speaches or see the newly wed table if sitting on the other half. There is only one washroom on this floor. A few more washrooms on the lower floor.

Cool venue. Staff were great up until the end of the night. One of the bartenders were kind of rude over an order my coworker made. It was a busy night though so some frustration I guess was understandable.

I have nothing but great things to say about the OCHO, from the perspective of their bar / lounge (I have not stayed at the hotel itself yet). There is a great, relaxed atmosphere that is paired with exceptional service. The food quality is fantastic and the drink selection is impressive. If you're there on a Wednesday, you can take advantage of the $5.75 2oz cocktails. It also makes a great place to go out with a date or with co-workers. I highly recommend it!

Went to a dinner & dance event at the restaurant here called Groove Night that was awesome! Kind of wished they had a disco ball, but it was a great time. The food was excellent too, but I thought the portion size of the chicken I had could've been bigger. Extremely fancy place with corresponding food prices. One thing however that wasn't so impressive was the men's washroom - I've seen much better in simple bar and grill restaurants. That was the main drawback of the experience.

Fantastic experience. We had our family Christmas dinner and gift exchange here on Boxing day. There were 7 of us and the staff made us all feel right at home. The food was excellent, (although it could have been a little hotter). The staff were super. It was a buffet, so there was only one waiter in our section and he really was not much of a waiter. I asked for coffee 3 times before finally getting one, 45 minutes after our arrival. I was a little surprised and disappointed that refills on soft drinks cost extra. Parking cost extra too and 3 of the pay stations I tried were not working. Despite all of these little things, we had an excellent time and we will definitely be back. I highly recommend it.

LOVE this place. My sister got married in the chapel which is so romantic. I love the patio with the waterfalls in the summer. The bar is always cozy and great place to meet. Food never disappoints! Love the winding corridors and little nooks and crannies. Great atmosphere. And service is always excellent too.

Great romantic get away right in the middle of Toronto.  Historic and beautiful grounds.  We both thought this place would be a great place to have a wedding, in fact, there was one taking place while we were staying.  The stay was not cheap and the amenities were not modern, breakfast was OK, but it was historic and beautiful.  The experience was worth it and we would consider staying here again.

Really great service here. Waiter/waitress' were terrific. Food was enjoyable. Many options for breakfast or lunch.  As a bonus they have a chocolate fountain. What's not to love about that. It's a classy place so I didn't see any jeans or t shirts.

I guess for being near the airport everyone is likely just used to worse service at a higher price...but I like coffee sans soap as a minimum.

reviews.text: I was there on Monday for an early dinner with wife. Place was pretty empty but picked up rather quickly with dinner crowd. The interior and seating is...
One of the servers here was absolutely despicable - and I made sure to keep my receipt so I can remember who she was. Her name was Addy and I really hope...
It's not the same anymore. Low quality food and service was very bad. Bread cake after we finished our dinner. Caesar was watery, mule has no flavour,...

I have eaten here 5 or 6 times, each time out of convenience.   Gotta say that I have found it to be nothing special.  I think it's overrated.  I wouldn't go back by choice.  If I'm meeting friends or family and they want to try it or it's conveniently centeally located then sure, I don't have strong objections, but the food isn't so great nor is the decor so stunning as to make me count down the minutes until my next visit.

If you know Bayview Village from back in the day, before its upscale renaissance, then you'd remember Max's was here, and frankly I liked that place way more (not that the quality of food was better -far from it, but rather it had a more family friendly casual happy vibe that O&B can't come close to replicating).

Our family usually visits this restaurant and we have noticed a decline in both their Staff and Management. This past Saturday( Nov 18, 2017) we decided, my wife and I to go for their brunch at 11am. We had made on line reservations and when we arrived we were welcomed and taken to our tables. Upon arriving at our table we were approached by our server and both of us requested to having hot water with lemon and we were still served with cold water until I brought our request to the server's attention a second time.My wife ordered the Smoked Salmon Croissant and I the Egg Benedict - the cheese scone on which they serve the poached eggs on was absolutely stale and "dense" and the home fries which my wife received were absolutely cold. So we brought this to the notice of our server. She explained that she would have to report to her manager on site. After a pretty long while the manager shows up with a tiny bowl of home fries and states that we found their fries cold so here is a replacement. No other talk to say that we are sorry that this occurred or anything else. This just showed us and confirmed in our minds on how their service was dropping.

I'm not picky but I like a good meal and I  didn't have a good brunch. Cold eggs Benedict and holondase sauce, I felt like the English muffins tasted hard and stale and my potatoes were so hard and undercooked. I was so incredibly hungry and tired (newborn at home) that I ate all of it and didn't say a word.  My husband did the same, i found out after. Also the plate just had the food slapped on so it didn't even look pretty. I was really surprised as I remember it being great food. 

I hadn't been here in years and I won't go back. They seem inconsistent based on all of the other great reviews.

Had one of the worst experiences of price gouging that I’ve ever experienced in a restaurant of this reputation.  My husband and I ordered the bouillabais — a $32 per dish meal. It came out in a shallow bowl with 2 calamari rings, 2 small sized shrimp, 3 mussels (one did not open), and a piece of fish the size of a quarter on a bed of tomato sauce. The description of this meal stated that there were scallops and I could not find even one on my plate while my husband showed me the 6 tiny baby bay scallops he had in his dish. 2 pieces of toast were placed on top.  I wish I had taken a photo as proof that this is no lie. I think OB should be ashamed.  Our $14 calamari appetizer had more food than both main meals put together and the $22 a plate seafood spaghettini I ordered on two prior visits in the past few weeks had more seafood on the bed of pasta than this $32 sauce with a few morsels of food. We went home hungry and perplexed.  Our waiter was amazing and friendly and saved our evening so this rating is only about the food.
Exceptionally friendly and professional staff (especially Steve!), delicious food, and an ambient layout. Also, definitely the best cheesecake I've ever had. Thank you for the great experience!

With low light and textured walls creating a sumptuous ambiance, it is the spot for entertaining. The tree-lined candle lit patio is the perfect place to sit back and savour ONE's culinary creations and unique signature cocktails, all the while taking in Yorkville's bustling and exciting street life. With dishes that will amaze the palate and an energetic atmosphere, ONE is sure to be an experience to remember.

reviews.text:
Enjoyed a couple of cocktails and a dozen oysters with my mom on the patio following Toronto Fashion Week in Yorkville. How boujee!

When we initially sat...

This place is incredible!  

We were fortunate enough to have a really nice server that made our fifth anniversary feel special!

Our evening started off...
We came for dinner as a group of four during Summerlicious (3 courses, $48). The meal started with a bread server coming around with a big board from which...

Service was good but I think it's because there is an army of wait staff. Fresh bread was fantastic. Dinner was very good as well. The indoor dining area is a little too dark for eating. The seating in the lounge area is very uncomfortable. The tables end up being a bit high when you sit down. Nice place for a date night but find there are other businesses in the surrounding area that are a bit lighter on your pocket book.
Expensive, but very delicious! The atmosphere is great and the location is perfect, especially in the summer. Best truffle fries I've had so far.
Always love stopping by - even for a snack! Great patio in the summer, and fantastic dinner experience inside as well. One of the only places in Toronto serving quail egg on their tartare!

Today, I went there with my family for a casual afternoon meal. Got a table inside, ordered some drinks, my wife and my daughter ordered two Cesar salads from the first course menu, and a linguine and spaghetti from the pasta menu. I skipped the first menu and ordered instead a chicken shawarama from the second course menu. Now, here happens the funny thing. Apparently in the name of "One Restaurant tradition", one cannot order from second menu before ordering the first menu. Two salads arrived at our table in about 25 minutes. I waited another ten minutes, then tried to get the attention of the passing waiters, all ignoring me. Flies and wasps were more attentive than waiting staffs. Finally, a server came and I asked for my dish. Here was his answer to me: "We usually serve the second course after everyone finishes the first course". I said please bring my dish now. In another 10 minutes, a staff from the kitchen brought my dish, with two pieces of totally burnt and charred pita bread resting in the side of my plate. I asked the avoiding server to my table, protesting about the state of my dish, and I was told: "Why don't you start your dish and I send for some more bread". My jaw dropped in awe, no apologies, nothing. Aside from the charred pieces of bread, the saffron rice was not fresh, didn't even have the saffron taste or aroma. Then arrived the pastas, no offering of additional Parmesan cheese or pepper, a standard courtesy at any restaurant. Apparently we were getting the full package Canadian hospitality. My appetite was ruined by then. I paid around $200 and a 15% tip. I called the restaurant later to address my complaints to the management. She suggested next time better communicate with my server. I hung up the phone.

Had dinner here and the service  and atmosphere were great. Food was good too but just not as memorable. The bar is quite lively and the bar menu is quite extensive. This is more of a see and be seen kind of place. I mean, it is in Yorkville after all.

reviews.text: As soon as we entered the restaurant we were impressed by how nice the place looked. I know a reviewer said it was cramped but I thought they had a lot of...
The atmosphere and service here were kind of blah.  The food however was excellent.  I was thinking that the place was going to be a bit more elegant than...
Had dinner with friends here the other night.  Food was very good and it was nice to have the live entertainment.  Waiter was not attentive and made a...

Wow, just wow! Stopped mid-meal to write this review so I wouldn't forget. Ordered 6 dishes to share, and every single one was beyond amazing. Flavoured to perfection, and cooked with care. Our server Roula was very attentive; kept our water glasses full, and made great suggestions. Highly recommend, will definitely come back!

We made a lunch reservation for 13 people. All students and teacher from a reputable institute. Just one person in this place served all amd dinally she played her role as cashier. Food is low to middle quality. Not crowded at lunch time on Mondays just one or two table occupied
The service was absolutely disappointing. I would never go again to this place for any reason and I don't recommend this restaurant, not even to my worst enemy.
Stopped by wanting a nice quick lunch and I must say everything was delicious. The grilled calamari was out of this world! Service was good. Great value!

The multi-region wine list is not only a wine lover's dream but is reasonably priced for all to appreciate. Enjoy!

reviews.text:
Another tasty meal from Paese.
We both had specials tonight - I had the thick cut New York steak with red wine reduction, while my wife had the manicotti...

If you're looking for Italian fine dining just north of midtown, this is it. Paese is consistently excellent, and has been for years.

They seem to do...
I went here with my family and had a blast. The server we had (although I forgot his name) was superb and knew the menu inside out. The food took a while to...

Excellent food and service. No issues with that. I would give it a five star rating if it were based only on food. The temperature of the restaurant wasnt that comfortable as we found it chilly and advised our waiter twice. He said he made adjustments but it was still cool. Other than that, great meal!

Among the very best Italian food I have ever had. I came with family for my birthday and truly everything was delicious. Service was prompt after waiting 30 minutes after reservation time... We were a large group, I understand it happens sometimes. The experience was so excellent that I'm not even mad.

Highlight: 72 hr sous vide beef short ribs was worth killing for.
Delicious calamari fritti. Great service and courteous staff. Take out discount was welcomed. The place is nicely decorated and has a romantic ambiance. Full bar, I'd gladly come back.

I’ve been a few times for both lunch and dinner. Always excellent, and last night we had our office Christmas Dinner in one of the private rooms upstairs. Excellent menu, impeccable service and great wine.
100%!!!

Just had a wonderful lunch here. The Pappardelle Short Rib Ragu is so wonderfully fresh, tasty, fulfilling and super flavourful. Our server was attentive along with our table runner and the antipasti are the perfect size: not too small that you question the price not too big that it spoils your appetite. Our server was very kind and knowledgeable as well: great wine recommendation and very patient with our questions. My only regret is that I was so full I didn't get a chance to try their tiramisu! Looking forward to coming back!

reviews.text:
Came here on a Saturday afternoon. The place was pretty empty (probably because it was -25 out). We were seated and brought waters right away.

They had a...
I've lived in Greektown most of my life and have eaten at every joint on the strip. My fave was always Avli, but they've since shut down. I ordered...
The food and service was great... We had lamb shanks and lemon chicken and both were delicious...will definitely go there again specially on Friday or...

This is my go-to restaurant for a more expensive Greek meal on the Danforth. The atmosphere is always great and generally there is live music going on. The owner seems to be there all the time, running dishes, checking on patrons to make sure everything is just right. The food is awesome. Although they take part in winterlicious and summerlicious, you'll always find their "panlicious" menu which gives you 3-courses for a pretty decent price. Nice way to explore the menu and try new things.
Huge portions.  Lamb chops awesome.  They make Greek style scalloped potatoes with feta that are incredible!  Baked goat cheese and portabello salad is awesome.  The grilled calamari are terrific!
Great food. I tried the steak and it was delicious and perfectly cooked. Friendly staff and great atmosphere but the most important you can find the greek beer "fix" there.

The fig ice cream is genius! Fig, ice cream, red wine and cinnamon - who would've thought? The service is great, the alcohol is good, but the meze could be better. Meze usually consists of mainly pre-prepared appetizers. However, the meat should have been warmer, the burek more cheesy and one of the dips was too salty. The happy ending (dessert) made up for everything, however.
Delicious food. Amazing service. Beautiful and cozy restaurant and ambience. Highly recommended.

lic_profile: Established in 2010 this Parkdale hub boasts an haute cuisine restaurant and bar with live music on the lower level.  Unique design elements include exposed brick walls, a bar with corkscrew stools and multicoloured bar lighting made of re-purposed fire extinguishers. Chef Matty Matheson's uncomplicated, delicious food paired with upbeat music and great service make for the kind of restaurant dining you will want to come back for.

reviews.text: Parts & Labour is a trendy restaurant in Parkdale. The decor has a bit of a garage vibe. The lights above the communal tables look like lights that you...
Bias disclaimer: I'm a pretty big fan of Matty Matheson based on his shows on Viceland. Ok, now let me separate that because if the food here sucked I'd...
As a heads up, the service is quite slow here. I've been here a total of two times, the first time was specifically to try the burger since I've heard such...

A new place that we tried out and were disappointed.  Ordered the Beef Tenderloin and you get 2 small 1/4 inch slices for $32.  Loads of mushrooms.  Way overpriced.  Burgers were ok and nothing to rave about.  There were at least 4 different employees waiting on us and the entire experience felt like we were being rushed.  Too bad as it's a nice place inside and a kind of funky.  Definitely will not go back.

Drinks (and p&l burger) are great and the atmosphere is amazing. I've been here twice now, but this time around, it was disappointing and I don't think I'd be back. The server kept pushing us to order and made it seem as though she was rushing us to get out. She kept coming up to us every 15mins and brought us our bill without even asking if we wanted anything else. We weren't even there for an hour and a half. She was friendly but totally turned us off with her constant badgering.

I️ honestly wasn’t blown away by the burgers, but they were good. I️ was blown away by the cauliflower dish though, that’s what I️ would come back for and the mixed drinks are great. Nice atmosphere and decor.

Hosted my engagement party there. 5 out of 8 had the P&L burger. All 5 got food poisoning. Called them at 2:20am with no answer (they close at 3am) so I left a voicemail. They returned my call 12 hours later. I missed the call so I called them back and they didn't answer. Still waiting to hear back. At this point it's been over 24 hrs.

Dec 13 Update: still no contact.

Food was mediocre. Bitter parsnips. Sides came after entrees. Terrible service together with mediocre food means it is a bad place to eat. Had to leave a bad review because I was too guilty to not tip.

lic_profile: Peoples Eatery is a unique dining establishment that aims to celebrate the city’s cultural diversity with a menu that’s all over the map - but without fusion cuisine. Dishes are true to their respective origins and live happily together on a single menu, representing the city’s motto: ‘Diversity our Strength’. Chef/Partner Dustin Gallagher, recently of Top Chef Canada All-Stars, helms the kitchen with a menu driven by ‘crunch-to-squish ratio’, fun-to-eat, punchy-flavoured, technique-driven dishes. The bar program by managing partner, Matt See, includes carefully chosen beer, wine and cocktail lists which round out Peoples Eatery’s offerings. Dining at the bar or in a number of private spaces for larger groups makes Peoples a distinctively unique restaurant in an unexpected location: look for candle light in the front windows.
