Really great customer service from the waiter (wish I...

I fell down the stairs here in early June and fractured my tailbone. Poorly lit stairwell with no signage and slippery steps.

Food is mediocre (been here...
I really enjoyed my visit to Peoples Eatery. Both the food and the atmosphere were great. The Cornish Hen was absolutely amazing; it was juicy and...

This is a really special place and one of my favourites anywhere. Chill vibes all around on the main floor, or class it up a bit on the second level. The wine selection is fantastic and I recommend getting full bottles as they have cool stuff. Cocktails are also awesome, never been disappointed. Food is always incredible and really where they shine. The smoked fish platter is a constant favourite, but everything else is always great. Can’t wait to be back!

Great atmosphere, high quality foods and cocktails. They keep classics and update entrees regularly. Sommelier always picks the best pairings I've had with my dinners. They even let me change my nephew in the manager's office. Talk about service. A1!

Best meal I've had in a while- everything was flavourful and very good portion sizes. Staff were friendly and the amibance was very nice. Some people may find it a bit of a squeeze for space but the tables were large enough for the many dishes and drinks.
Does not fail to impress. Food and drink are consistently executed well. Little drop off in quality from the last time I visited but still pretty airtight. High creativity from the kitchen and bar.

The food was good, if not memorable.  It would have been better if said food wasn't delivered over the course of 3.5 hours (not an exaggeration).  Drinks were tasty, but painfully slow to arrive also. Our solution? See the Rol San review - popped in there after for better, faster, cheaper food.

The good:
- Gorgeous back patio, great for sunny...

French Toast tasted like sandwich bread.
Salmon Benedict is not fresh.
I have no idea why it is four stars in Yelp..

Overall experience: 7.5/10
Food: 7/10
Atmosphere: 7.5/10
Service: 8/10

Brunch in Toronto is quite a fickle thing. You have your amazing places, at which...

I’ve always wanted to try this place but sadly they didn’t seem to welcome customers with a stroller. I know it’s not great for restaurants to accommodate a stroller, so I don’t don’t go when the restaurants look busy. Fortunately I find most places try to accommodate and I appreciate that. 

Not this place it seems. I saw that it is empty with only 3 tables and saw empty tables with floor space before I decided to go in. I took the stroller through the first door and wanted to see if any staff would come open the second door for me since it’s a very cramped space between the doors, but both staff standing in front of the door chose to ignore me. At first I thought they were helping a lady so I waited, but when that lady left, they turned their backs (while still standing 3 feet away from me) despite seeing me at the door staring at them. It’d be hard for them to not notice me and the stroller being that close. No one acknowledged me during the 5-10 minutes while I stood there. I would appreciate it if they just tell me they can’t accommodate a stroller instead of pretending I’m not there.

This was my second visit here. The atmosphere and service was great, but something about the food left me wanting more, and not in a good way. The portion sizes are decent but the flavours just felt off to me and my partner. Perhaps this new-style Canadian isn't our thing. I would still recommend it to others but I don't see myself going back.

Been here twice. First time was nice: good cocktails and pretty standard bistro fare, with a Canadian twist. Second time my partner and I waited 25 minutes after being seated by the hostess, and no server spoke to us even once. The place was not busy (most tables were open) and there were three waitresses on the floor, so this kind of wait is inexcusable. We had plans for later that evening, so we left.

Very tastey eats and good service. Could be a little better though since I didnt understand the menu and had to google each item so I knew what i would be eating... they should know this and maybe have the server explain or a more detailed menu. But what I did order was amazing! (thanks google)
Great food.. great atmosphere. ..friendly staff. A place you need to try just once and you will be back  again and again. The menu changes weekly so it's a surprise each time you go.  A must!!!!

reviews.text: As a California native, I am no stranger to bright floral arrangements and positive attitudes. However after 2 months of being separated from my long...
I received a floral delivery form here. The arrangements was designed beautifully and Araz was very helpful when I had some questions over the telephone...
I got to use Posies on Monday and they were the best. A great selection of flowers and a talented maker of arrangements. But what was most important for me...

Ordered during the 50% off foodora deal this week and may not have tried it if not for the deal. Very happy I did!  Best gluten free pizza crust I've ever had.  I kept checking the box and almost called the restaurant to make sure it was actually gluten free. It's a little pricey. But I'm happy I got to try it.

If an open patio seating and some crazy good pizza is what you are after, then Pizza Rustica has you covered. Their pasta is really fresh and the sauce really melded well with the pasta itself. And most of all, the recipes are simple; just as it should be. Also, Jill and Alexia, the waitresses, are incredibly professional. Great place for food and fun.

My colleagues and I were looking for somewhere to have lunch before setting off to Second City Theatre. We found an Italian restaurant by the name of Pizza Rustica, and might I say, were blown away! Awesome taste and quick service. Plus the food is freshly made by the cooks.

This place, although place looks like it may be a great place to eat. I would highly suggest to avoid. The pizza is so cheaply put together, that the topping portions are so small you either miss them or cannot taste them! The crust is so dry and I'm flavorful. Drinks are highly over priced, and thank god I'm pregnant and can't drink, cause the two drinks my husband ordered cost more then our actual meal! In end our pizza was probably the worst I've ever eaten and we eat a lot of pizza... there just was no flavour from the toppings we wanted (cause they make they so small) sauce was gross. Service was great and that was about it, we will never go back and these guys need to learn how to make a real "rustica" pizza or change there name

Had my young son’s birthday party at Pizza Rustica. The service was impeccable and all the people left smiling and full of delicious food. The perfect celebration in the perfect restaurant. Pizza Rustica is a winner for sure!

reviews.text: Came here for dinner around hooch hour. Ordered some drinks for $5.09 each to start off. My friends had the custom burgers and I had the mussels. Not bad!...
Service was simply amazing. We were taken care of and checked up on frequently! Our waiter was super friendly and established a positive rapport with us...

Great food.
Great service. 
Fun atmosphere - loved the videos!
Looking forward to our next visit.

A trendy looking place that attracts a well dressed happy hour crowd. If you're into 'comfort food' you'll like the menu. The food was very good, and the service was pretty good. That's something of an accomplishment given how busy the place was both times I was there.

Food was delicious. I got the pulled pork grilled cheese. I went during lunch time and the service was slow even though it wasn't busy. Food didn't come out at the same time for our group of 10 people which sucked. It came out with like 10 minutes between the first and last plate. Server must've been new because he seemed confused the whole time. Everyone loved their food though

I've been here many times since this location opened, and I must say that tonight is the best service I've had. Emily was pleasant, fast, and went above and beyond. I really appreciate the excellent service from her tonight. Thank you Emily!

Brought my girlfriend of 2 years here for our anniversary. She's a health nut and was bit concerned but she found plenty of healthy choices. She had the Caveman salad with salmon. Very fresh! Yet still savory. I had the pulled pork grilled cheese sandwich. It was out of this world especially dipped in the cranberry sauce. I made the mistake of sharing with my gf...she ended up eating half and she doesn't even eat sandwiches!  The duck fried sweet potatoes were fabulous appetizer.  2 of us, including 2 glasses of the house....~$100.

I have no problem with an expensive menu, but when the prices are high I expect the food quality to be high as well. I think the food didn't measure up what it should be in that price range. Even though the staff was nice and it's a really nice restaurant, the meals should taste a bit better.

lic_profile: Pukka offers a forward thinking take on Indian cuisine.  Featuring smart, zingy flavours, the menu is prepared by chefs each hailing from a different part of India. Dishes take you on a journey through decadent tastes, while maintaining a lightness that enchants the palette.

reviews.text:
This was my first visit to Pukka.

The place looks fantastic and the staff were very helpful!

Tonight I found some new items on the menu that I haven't...
3.5/5 stars. We came for early dinner tonight (they open at 5PM on Sundays) and the place was pretty empty, which was fantastic because partner and I could...
I'm really quite confused as to why there are so many high reviews of this place. I came here on a Sunday evening with 4 other people. The restaurant itself...

This restaurant is INCREDIBLE. I went there for my birthday with some wonderful friends and I am so honoured to have been able to do so. 

Words fail to impress just how magical the food was. It is, hands down, the best Indian cuisine that I have ever had in my life. The food is prepared with true love and artistry, and the exquisite balance of spices is almost surreal. Proteins were all cooked to perfection, and the service was impeccable.

The server was professional, attentive without being intrusive, and the owner delivered us our appetizers with a humility and pride befitting of his craft. When I mentioned that it was my birthday, the owner gifted the table a beautiful slice of decadent dark chocolate torte that sat upon a drizzle of the most incredible cardamom infused butterscotch.

I cannot sing this restaurant's praises enough. I will certainly be returning and encourage anyone that is reading this to treat yourself and the ones you love to a quasi-spiritual experience of food.

Loved Pukka, the food is fantastic. The chat as an appetizer is a must. Crispy, fresh, simply delicious. Their garlic Nam is very tasty as well and so is their lamb. Only giving it 4 stars because the server didn't pay enough attention and served us something with cauliflower even though my wife said she was allergic to cauliflower and emphasized it. Allergy is a pretty serious things and details like this can't go unnoticed. Besides that, everything was great and I will gladly return.

We ordered the gunpowder King prawns appetizer, served on a thick bed of chutney. For the main course we had the butter chicken, lentils, and lamb lollipops. Each had its own flavorful sauce. The lamb was tender and cooked perfectly. For dessert I had the rice pudding, which was very flavorful. The service was friendly and attentive.

My boyfriend has a nut allergy and asked if their Punjabi chicken curry had any  nuts. The waiter told us no, so he ate his meal. Within a couple bites he was having a reaction. We told the waiter who then took the charge of his meal off of our bill. The waiters were very polite and attentive. We were VERY lucky that he did not have a more serious reaction. This could have been a life or death situation. Good food, not very attentive to nut cross contamination. If you have a nut allergy DO NOT order the Punjabi Chickien Curry!!
Great food. Just had a quick bite to eat before a movie -- for a light dinner the butter chicken, an app and an order of rice fed us really nicely. Would definitely order more if we had more time.

I had my birthday dinner at Pulcinella during the Summerlicious event which I strongly recommend. It's within walking distance from my house, Friday, summer...
The food/service is 5*!! Great selection of wine too. You're going to pay for the food and service though. A bit over priced and that's the only reason I'm...

Excellent Fine Italian Dining! Staff is great! Very helpful, approachable, friendly and engaging. Food is Authentic. Presentation of the meals were spectacular. Price is good. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone and everyone that loves fine dining and have exquisite taste with the need for authentic cuisine.
Saw the positive reviews and decided to give this place a try. Did not disappoint! The place was beautifully decorated, the service was friendly and pleasant and the food was the best part!

great service, nice setting , calm atmosphere clean restaurant ,clean, efficient, happy waitress. delicious food,reasonable prices.we will definitely return as we were told of live entertainment on Thursday evening..

Hands down the best Italian restaurant in the city. I've been here 3 nights in a row now and I can't get enough of it. Highly highly recommend this place. Thanks to Sal and Mitch for the A1 experience

Pulcinella dishes up some real good Italian food. We tried their pizza, pasta and risotto and they were all done perfectly. We had apple cake for dessert and that was okay. It's a bit pricey but I wouldn't mind paying more if the food is that good.

Their friendly staff are trained to guide you through their extensive selection of local beers and wine that match perfectly with their menu.

reviews.text: The Distillery District is a very unique and wonderful place to explore. Shopping off the Parliament street entrance we wove our way through shops and we're...

As much as we enjoyed oysters there a few weeks ago, disappointed now.  Customer service either suck or extremely stupid.
Called for reservations last...
While exploring Distillery District, we got hungry and had brunch at Pure Spirits Oyster House and Grill. In addition to dining room seating, this...

I called around four places for oysters everything was closed and I really wanted oysters. Pure spirits saved the day with some of the most delicious and fresh oysters in Toronto. Trust me I know. I eat oysters three times a week. Thank you Chris at the shuckers lounge for all your knowledge and education on my favourite species. Cheers and happy new year 
Dave

4 stars for food 1 star for service

A girlfriend and I went yesterday for a double birthday celebration.  We had raw oysters and champagne.  The food was good. The restaurant is very charming.  However, our waitress was not.  She was snippy and seemed to be in a bad mood.  From the moment we sat down we felt rushed. She wanted us in and out. We ordered champagne and after she poured us our first glass she asked us if we were ready to order. When we said we wanted to just relax a bit with our drinks she made one of many faces we had to endure during our meal. She spoiled what should have been a fun afternoon.  In retrospect I should have asked to be moved to another section.

We were greeted by Jake at the reception stand outside who kept us entertained for almost an hour while they found a table to seat 8 of us. Once seated our drink orders were promptly taken and delivered, food ordered were then taken and came out in a fashionable time. We ordered calamari to start which was okay, we wish the pieces were smaller as it made it hard to eat. For mains we order the lobster pappardelle, beef tenderloin and shortribs; the lobster dish and steak were perfectly executed while the short rib left a lot to be asked for. It was very well cooked but the flavours seemed odd like they didn't work well with the dish. 

We would come again for the steak and lobster pasta.
Great Customer Service. I never tried Oysters before and the guy let me try one first. Then eased me into until I was able to try the oyster without cringing.

Oysters are why you should come here and they don't disappoint. Very fresh and well presented. Prices are average so very worth it! Drinks are a bit watered down and small so don't come here to drink.

Service is 2/5

Despite the average ratings on yelp, we still came here for winterlicious.

Food isn't too bad. For starters, I...

Good times and delicious food. I had the lobster mac and I wouldn't change anything about it. The rest of the table had steak and the surf and turf, empty plates at the end so that must be a good sign. The service was a bit slow, for a New Years Eve dinner they should have been better prepared. The ambiance is fantastic to share a few drinks with friends or family. I like this restaurant because it's easy to book a table and the food is really good, considering the location it has attractive menu prices.

Decent place. As other reviewers pointed out, service really is slow, albeit very cordial. Portions are rather small, and the garnishes feel (and taste) like an afterthought. Very dimly lit, as one would expect from a place that places itself in the Irish pub/steakhouse category. Not worth it for the money, in my opinion. Although it feels like a class above your usual pub, the food underwhelmes.

Really slow service.  Six of us came for lunch on Nov 21st, with a reservation ahead of time.  Once there, we waited 40 minutes to place our food orders, during which time two of us who arrived a bit later than the others ended having to go to the bar to get drink service.  When the food finally came, the orders were staggered, with some of us getting food, and some not, and some orders not completed ("soup and salad" means soup and salad together, not soup and eventually, maybe, salad, 10 minutes after you've finished your soup).  The service was pleasant enough, but when you've got an hour for lunch before you have to get back to a meeting, and make reservations ahead of time to make sure that everything goes smoothly, you'd hope for more timely service.

Relatively upscale with a solid menu of classics. I ordered the prime rib dinner - medium rare and unfortunately, it came out too rare. I'm usually fine with some blood but the texture was too slimy for my taste 🤷🏽‍♀️. Other than that, everybody else in my group enjoyed their meals.
Food was ok but service was really bad. I won't be back

tldr: Social staff and repeat clientele. Food is above average for a brunch place. Mussels are to-die-for.

The Real Mo-Mo's is a great brunch/lunch/dinner...

I am so excited that we chose to have brunch here...everything was amazing!

I started with my very first Caesar which is like a Bloody Mary but with...

Lovely ambience for quiet lunches and romantic dinners, very conducive to conversation. And the food, drinks and menu are great at a reasonable price for the financial district -- highly recommended if you are fed up with throbbing dance music.
Food was decent, atmosphere is very much a French style cafe.  Brunch and breakfast only served on the weekend.  Probably wouldn't go back - just not my style.

We had our rehearsal brunch at this lovely restaurant (Sept 2017). Monique was a pleasure to work with, really excited to have and host us. We had 17 people attend and the food/drinks and service were great. Thanks again Mo!

Love this place.   The owner is exceptionally nice and the food and atmosphere are great.

My wife and I will definitely be going back.

My friends threw me a birthday party here and we loved the food! The menu is comparatively small but there's a lot of variety there. We ordered apps, entrees and dessert. All the dishes/items were delish! Its a small & cozy place to have a wonderful lunch or dinner! Oh wait, I have had their breakfast too, they make amazing home fries! My judgement of a breakfast place is typically by their homefries or eggs Benny! I think they do both very well :)

Came here for NYEs dinner and left again impressed with the food, service and drinks at Reds. 

They offered a $49 3 course prix fixe dinner which was a...
Went here because I really wanted the two bite butter tarts. I had them at the square one location and figured since I was down in the city I would fulfill...

First of all the food and The service is very good.
All our portions seemed generous except for the soup. For some reason the cup $9 and bowl $11 seemed to...

Following a tiff movie, my girlfriend and I were so happy that we crossed the road to Reds following a very cold reception at the E&C. We were promptly seated at a great table. The atmosphere was great and was further enhanced by a DJ spinning some relaxing house music. 
The cocktails and food were well presented and delicious. Sara, our server, was spot on and helpful in providing recommendations. Overall, it was a great way to cap off an excellent evening. I look forward to going back.

Amazing staff and a complimentary extra little bit of chicken so that we could taste it since it wasn't done on time. What an amazing experience great owners highly recommend! The serving sizes are a perfect portion so don't expect to get a massive amount for your dollar but the burgers are unbelievable!

Nice, chilli atmosphere. Fair prices. Special offers and great drinks. Service which is there and very good but doesn't feel that somebody is bothering you. 
My first time here in Toronto. Can really recommend it.

I come here once a year when we are in Toronto and everyone in our group is always quite pleased. The steaks are always perfectly cooked, the selection of other foods is balanced and the samples from other folks meals have been quite delicious. Service has been good, and it's a comfortable environment. We'll be back!

Great decoration and a good place to feel the vibe of the city. Their prices are average on the drinks side and the general crowd is 30+. Great hosts, they are helpful, chatty enough to entertain but not disturbing. Clean, calm amd relaxing place. Food prices could be better and a few more options wouldn't be bad. I visit Reds on a regular basis.

reviews.text: I've been to Ricarda's three times- once for dinner, once for breakfast and once for brunch. This review will focus on my brunch experience. I went on a...

We had a great time today at their Jazzy Brunch!
We enjoyed the food, atmosphere and service. 
I highly recommend this place and don't understand how I...

Came here for dinner a few months ago and was impressed so decided to try the jazz brunch HUGE DISAPPOINTMENT. 

When I made the reservation the hostess...

Went here for a Sunday brunch with my wife and 2 kids (4 & 1). Firstly they offer free Nanny service for Sunday brunch which is unbelievable. The Nanny's are extremely friendly and caring towards the children. The children have their own little selection of food (tenders, vegetables, pizza etc) and the play area includes a bouncy castle, toys and a variety of activities.

Coming to the main brunch...just wow. Huge selection of breakfast items and lunch items including made to order pancakes, eggs, omelettes etc...lunch includes a variety of meat, seafood, salads, flatbread, pasta and so so so much more. Great service and solid place to visit for special occasions. Food tastes fresh and amazing!

Highly recommend!

We went on a Tuesday around 6:15 PM. The restaurant was about half full.
The interior of the place was spacious, clean, modern, and bright. Very beautiful with an open kitchen area so you could see chefs at work. Our server was a friendly, professional guy with a cool mustache that offered suggestions based on his experiences.
They started us with some red pepper dip and an assortment of breads, which was very nice. The food itself was brought out decently quickly and tasted great, although the portions were pretty small. The presentation of the mains was beautiful. The quality was present even in the receipts, which were attached to a custom Ricarda's postcard. 
If you are looking to eat a lot when considering the price and the portion sizing, I would suggest looking elsewhere. If not, then this is a very cool experience in a great setting with high-quality dishes.

Ricarda's is a classy establishment for a girl's night out, a dressy date or a business meeting. (I think they film Suits here sometimes?) The decor is tastefully curated, in a non-pretentious way. Even the lobby is upscale. 

They served us bread with a red pepper hummus which I'm glad I didn't fill up on, because I had the lobster roll (3) with skinny fries and loved every bite. My table also ordered off the tapas menu to sample the meatballs and caprese salad, which was a whole lot of hype for not very much food. The service was fantastic and our waitress was one of the most attentive people I've ever met. We totally overstayed our welcome but she was gracious and let us chat long after we had finished our meals. For that, I might be back to try their bakery.
It's a huge space but it has their front of house well planned that it feels intimate. Loved the food and wine list. Really high quality food that manages comfort and uniqueness well.
Ricarda’s was excellent! Personable and efficient service with delicious food options. The home made pasta was delicious! Great vegan selection as well.  A must try!

reviews.text: I was searching for a place to take my partner to for his birthday and I happened to spot a review for this place in the Toronto Star for a pretty lunch...

The restaurant was completely empty when I arrived, and remained empty until the end of our meal, when one other party arrived. 

The restaurant itself was...
A wonderful hidden gem of a restaurant tucked away in the Columbus Centre. I found this place while wedding venue shopping and it was recommended by the...
I have been coming 4 times and was told different excuses about why they cant serve us. 4 times!  They are rasists im sure now. Please lets stop this guys.

The dining room was white linen and very somber.  The maitre d was quite brusque and impatient in explaining the menu.  The other staff were more friendly.  My friend and I shared the artichokes which were very nice although canned.  I had the gnocchi which was so so and the sauce very acidic and needed salt.  I had to ask for for more water.  Overall mediocre.

Had dinner at Boccaccio the other night with a friend. It was my first time at this restaurant and I chose it based on web reviews and the fact it was conveniently located for both my friend and I. While it was ok overall, I was hoping for a better experience.  Firstly, the restaurant was virtually empty despite it being around 7pm.  There was no soft background music either so it was so quiet you could hear a pin drop.  Too quiet actually.  The menus were a bit stained and "worn" looking.  That would not have bothered me if it was a low-end restaurant, but given Boccaccio's price point, this should not have been the case. We shared the fried artichokes and they were very good, although I was expecting fresh artichokes vs canned.  Nonetheless, they were tasty and we enjoyed them.  I had the gnocchi and while the gnocchi themselves were soft and light (definitely homemade), the tomato sauce was a bit acidic. Almost like it was under-cooked.  My friend had the daily fish special.  It was cooked perfectly and she said it was delicious. I had the creme brullee for dessert.  It was ok.   The service was good.  Wait staff was very professional and attentive. They knew exactly when to come and fill water glasses and ask if we needed anything.  So overall it was ok but I will not be coming back as I have other Italian restaurants in the city that I enjoy more both for ambiance and food.

The best Italian food in Toronto and I think probably the best in Canada. Born in Toscany, being myself a gourmet cook, just for my family and friends, I know good cuisine when I taste it and I may assure you that Boccaccio serves the best real Italian.

lic_dinnermenu: A variety of appetizers and salads served buffet style, including smoked salmon, mussels, mango salad, avocado salad, kale salad, octopus salad and many more.
A succulent variety of meat specially prepared and precisely cut to perfection., including assorted cuts of  pork and chicken, a variety of angus beef, and the famous pichanna.
Flip the red/green card on your table to green signaling the meat cutters to begin serving you. The red signals the servers to give you a break.
Served with a variety of side dishes including grilled vegetables, potatoes, and rice and beans.
lic_profile: Rodeo Brazilian Steakhouse offers a unique dining experience that includes an amazing assortment of prepared fresh daily salads on their appetizer table and a wide assortment of perfectly cooked and seasoned meat served Brazilian-style on large skewers. Enjoy an old Brazilian tradition in Toronto surrounded by bosa nova sounds while sipping on delicious lime caipirinhas.

reviews.text: I had a great time at Rodeo on a Saturday night. We chose the Summerlicious option, which has fewer options than the regular menu, but we still left quite...

This review is tough for me to write because I have mixed feelings about this place.

Here's why. I took my friend here for her birthday on a Friday because...

Very unique experience.  
A bit of a slow start.  Hostess didn't really give us a great run down of how it all works.  We started with the summerlicious...

What an amazing place! I had no idea what to expect. All of the food was fantastic, fresh and excellent quality meat and side dishes. Cheese board and meat board buffets, side buffet and all of the meat you can eat! Then live music, two women in real Carnival costume, and they got everyone on the dance floor! I can't wait to go back. We were there on all-you-can-eat night and it was such a great time. Absolutely worth the price. I was with a lively crew and that's how it goes there. It's not a good choice for vegetarians or people looking for a quiet night out. It is a PARTY place!

Excellent salad, veggie, cheese, deli, seafood buffet kicks off a a truly epic parade of meat and chicken that has to be experienced to be believed. Parmesan-encrusted beef? Yes please. Steak infused with cheese. Right here. I lost count of how many dishes there were because I was too busy eating for the better part of an hour.

Good food and entertainment. Come hungry, because it’s an all you can eat place. The music, performances and dancers are really nice. Our bill was little over 140 dollars for two adults, which although was a nice meal, will make us think twice before coming back.

Excellent place to have a nice dinner, specially on a Friday or Saturday.
Great service and good quality food. On these days there is live music and garotas dancing.
There are at least 15 types of meat and the salar bar has a lot of different options including shrimp, mussels, smoked salmon, cheese, bread and more.

Good service and atmosphere. However the meat was extremely salty so much so that I couldn’t eat most of what was served. Salad bar was good everything looked fresh. I would not come back for the price go to Copacabana

At Ruth's Chris, your steak is carefully selected from the finest USDA Prime beef available and served with gracious hospitality.

reviews.text: This was my second visit to Ruth's Chris downtown. My friend and I decided to spoil ourselves with a great steak dinner this weekend. We had picked up some...

I wasn't planning on reviewing this place but it was pretty exceptional so I'm going to go ahead and do it anyways. 

Our group all got the petit filets...
The various 'Licious meals is always a hit and miss in terms of quality and service, but Ruth Chris delivers on both! The restaurant is on the second floor,...

Don't know where all these 5 star ratings come from... 

Service was great,  nice atmosphere, but steaks and sides seem to just be a medium for butter. Buttery steak and sides typically aren't a bad thing - but when all I taste is butter, it's too much. 

For the record, a steak should not be served on a 500 degree plate that it went into the broiler on - it just keeps cooking the steak. 

I can think of at least three other downtown steakhouses at the same price point (or cheaper) that deliver a better meal - if you have a choice, spend your money elsewhere.

Best dinner I've had in my life.

We went here before a show at the Second City after our taxi driver suggested it as a great place for steaks. The waiter was really friendly and professional. He told us he had taken classes at the Second City in the past. The mashed potatoes and Brussels sprouts were delicious and the steaks were served with butter still sizzling on top.

Amazing! Went to this location for my birthday and the service and food was top notch! Best filet I have ever had in my life! Don't know if anyone could top it. I recommend this restaurant to everyone.  Good job.
This restaurant has less than satisfactory food at premium prices. The only good thing about this place was the service. Save your time and hard earned money and opt for Jacob’s or Harbour 60.

stopped in on a whim while craving steak down town.
on a Friday night with no reservations the staff were more then accommodating, while most other chain restaurants turned us away or gave us 2 hour wait times. The front of house were very quickly willing to provide my wife and i with a comfortable spot at the bar where we not only received full service but the bar tender and our waitress was very friendly and helpful.
The food was out standing, cooked and served to perfection!
We decided to get a cheese cake for desert which was indescribably good. Our bill was just over $300 before tip for the two of us, it was worth every penny as we left more then satisfied!

reviews.text:
Such a wonderful experience and the food was superb!

The ambience of R&D is a definite 5/5, and the serving staff go out of their way to make you feel...

Came here with my friend for happy hour excited to try a new modern fusion restaurant in Toronto and was unfortunately underwhelmed.

Let's start off with...

there is a hipster vibe to this place.   

The menu has evolved since it opened.  I ordered the chicken and waffles.  

only two words for that dish.  - Too...

We went as a group of 10 on New Years Eve for my birthday. We had one server Arthur, who was super attentive and fun! On such a busy night with a big party, I was so impressed with the level of service. The food was incredible, we got 2 ducks. It was by far the most delicious duck I’ve ever had. The Boa is basically like eating a fluffy cloud. Another dish we enjoyed was the octopus which was tender on the inside and crispy on the outside, not at all rubbery. The cocktails  were very good too! Our table tried them all and we loved each of them. Aside from the food and service the actual restaurant has a great vibe!

I had been wanting to try this place for awhile and it was definitely worth it! 
The food was delicious and interesting. The atmosphere was cosy and and relaxed. Staff was super nice and helpful, I believe our server’s name was Carly and she was wonderful! She made sure to check in on us and even brought us an allergy menu!

Can’t wait to come back and try more of the menu!

Went here for a birthday, 15 people, 2 large tables! Food is delicious and very tasty! Decor is nice. Service is fine. Only negative...it was pretty  hot in there. And we went in November. However  definitely recommend this resto!!!

I have been to R&D many times and I'm always seated at the same spot at the front. It's quiet and at times the pillar makes it hard for the service staff to notice us. That said, the food is interesting on the positive side for the most part and you can really tell they put in the time, thought and dedication in creating their dishes. Sometimes the cook and chef brings out the food, which is a nice touch in my opinion. Highly recommend coming here! 👍👍

I also recommend using ur GPS as this place can be easily missed.

A great fusion restaurant placing spins on traditional classics.  Beautiful ambiance and decor makes you feel like you're more in a lounge than a restaurant.  The servers were very friendly, helpful and carried on a rapport with us that made us feel like family instead of customers.  On top of that, the chef came out and chatted with us before we left.  A very classy act that won't be forgotten.  I recommend coming here to eat because I will be coming for another visit.

After 20 years of food experience, my worst 
 experience have occurred in this restaurant ,on Father's day it Took 20 min to bring wrong brunch menu , water...

Service has gone downhill since I last visited. Waiting for a salad to be prepared took 30 minutes. The lack of knowledge some servers have on the menu items as well as not giving us any cutlery/condiments with our appetizers really ruined the experience for me. If you ever come here for lunch be prepared to be out for 3 hours. An hour for the drinks, an hour for the food, and an hour in between paying the bill.

EDIT: Came back to Safari for dinner after this experience. I feel service was greatly improved and I’m surprised they’ve spruced up some of the specials. Safari offers a wider variety of red and white wines. Cashing out our bill did take a while, I feel that this can be improved.

Found this place when searching Google for a first date destination. Couldn't have picked a better place.  Very comfortable atmosphere. Beautiful decor. Friendly staff. I had the fish taco.. Excellent.So flavorful.  My date had the burger. It was a beautiful start an excellent evening. Will recommend and definitely will be back.

I dined-in once before, a few years ago. I enjoyed the food, service and ambiance. I am in the area this week and decided to order the Margherita pizza Because I’ve heard good things about their Pizzas. Very disappointed! The menu should describe it as a bruschetta pizza. I thought it seemed odd that one of the ingredients is onion, but I figured I could just pick them off if i don’t like it... wrong!   It doesn’t taste bad but management should definitely consider renaming it because it’s deceiving.

Food's tasty, if a little overpriced. Just don't order the chocolate pecan pie. It's gross. Nothing like a pecan pie.

Service was pretty slow considering it was a quiet Sunday night. There was plenty of staff, but we had to ask for basics like water. 

Was a challenge to get our bills in a timely manner and had to explain more than once who was paying for what. We were not a huge group, so this should not have been so hard for the waiter.

We showed up looking forward to an early dinner. We could sit anywhere as there were only 3 patrons in the restaurant. The menus were given to us as we sat and both of us couldnt help but notice how dirty they were. (Pet peeve) The menu prices were high. 18.00 burger! We stayed and shared an app that was awful, paid our bill and will never go back. Poor customer service, loud dated music and an uninviting atmosphere.

Truly a place for Japanese comfort food, I was thrilled to find this place only a 10 minute drive from the circus studio I visited.

There's room for maybe...
Definition of hidden gem. Came here on a business brunch and I was super excited and impressed. It's a small little cafe/restaurant that offers great...
I have been desperately wanting to try this place for the longest time, but unfortunately it's located on the Danforth and I come to this area...like never....

Update - stopped by for summerlicious 2017. As usual the food was really really good and the dessert was amazing. Hope they put it on their regular menu. 
Portions are just the right size. Fish perfectly cooked and tasty. Bread for the sandwich is baked in house - yum! Was a little disappointed to find out after I had ordered that the lunch menu was also being offered during the breakfast service. But not to worry I will be back! Drip coffee was REALLY good. Nice little cozy spot. Definitely would recommend if in the area.

A small place in the neighbourhood that serves great Japanese comfort food that makes me miss Japan. They can be a little slow when they're busy. But the servers are always really friendly and want to make sure you're doing alright while you're there. Have been coming here for lunch but would love to come try dinner as well eventually :D

Don't be misled by the name, this is a cozy cafe\restaurant with delicious Japanese comfort food you don't find at usual sushi joints. The ramen is as outstanding as the popular shops and is cheaper too! The staff are genuinely Japanese and definitely know what they are doing.
Unlike any other cuisine in Toronto. Food quality is top notch and the service is fantastic. If you're looking to try something different this is definitely the place

This place is a gem on the Danforth. 
In a city awash in Japanese restaurants, it's nice to see a traditional Japanese comfort food establishment. Soft jazz in the background, comfortable environment  puts one at ease. One of the cities best japanes cheese cake paired wonderfully with house  pressed  coffees can't be beat anywhere.
Escape from the norm and take a visit. 
Cheers 

.

reviews.text:
Last dinner for summerlicious for 2017.
Enjoyed the atmosphere for the restaurant. Service was great.

Got a plate of mussels, steak & lobster, and a...

The atmosphere is nice and the service was okay.

I ordered the spaghetti with meatballs. The meatballs looked and tasted like frozen President's Choice...
I went there to try their summerlicious dinner. It was $28 for the 3-course dinner which included appetizer, main course and dessert. I selected PEI...

Went there on a Saturday night with a large group. Our server was really nice and did a really great job. The menu was extensive and I had trouble deciding on what to get. I eventually settled on the special and really liked it. The service was fast and the price was decent. I would go back again when I am in the area.

I have been to Sambucas a few times and the service is very dependant on the waiters that are available and working. Their advertises hours are more of a "based on how they feel" rather than a set and advertised time. I walked up to the door this eveing and the gentleman working literally locked the door in front of me. When I said "Are you not open until 10?" The response was "we're closed" and a turned back. Great food when the time comes, But service can ruin an experience in a moment. If you're are based on service and service is refused... not sure what the point is. Kind of a contradiction to business. Not a go to spot for me anymore. I used to promote Sambucas and it's definitely off the list
Food is tasty. Portions are good. Prices reasonable. A good variety of choices.  Creme Brule is a very good dessert. Server Zane is efficient.
Must go if you are in the village. Best prix fixe in downtown.  Super food and superior service.
Always good food. Specials are interesting. Main menu has a great selection. AMAZING prices.

My partner and I came here last night for my birthday celebration. It was a lovely night. 

First off, I mixed up the reservation date but they graciously...

This should be a 0 star review.

We came here tonight after purchasing a Groupon last week for a 3 course meal, which we were really excited to try. I've...
Came here for two 3 course dinners. I tried the brown sugar pulled pork belly, pan seared digby scallops, and their cheesecake. The pork belly was mostly a...

Great food and setting.  But absolutely unacceptable for the waitress to hover over me in-front of my party of 6 and loudly point out that i should be tipping and giving me instructions on how to do it.
I witnessed her do it to other tables as well.  If you do not mind being treated like a 5 year old and embarrassed in front of your table then give this place try.
Food was excellent. Service was very professional and the vibe was very nice. It's a bit tight in the restaurant but you can still make your way around.

Wow! Yorkville's gem!  Great food that it's inspiring in a really cool venue. Balcony, living wall and a chef that is on the ball? Sign me up!! Intimate affairs of under 150 people is what they specialize in. Right in the middle of Toronto's swankiest neighborhood. Parking all around and lots to see and do. Wedding, shower or a product launch. It just works!

It's a beautiful restaurant, but service was really slow for a 1pm lunch. It took an hour to bring out lunch for 5 people. And unfortunately all of our food was cold. The dessert was very yummy and the people who work there were very nice. Other than that the food was sub par; which was disappointing for my first visit. 4 out of the 5 dishes were ordered were not that enjoyable.
Went for our office  Christmas party. The food was excellent. The banquet room was perfect size for our party. Attentive and professional staff.

reviews.text: Oh where do I begin? It was a chilly December day and I had no idea I was about to meet the love of my life - Zucca Ravioli. I hesitated briefly over which...

It's a shame.

The fresh mozzerella is pretty darned tasty! 

Unfortunately, Scaddabush seems to want to be a college bar, rather than a restaurant. 

The...
Scaddabush had a nice after work drinks/dinner atmosphere on the Friday night we went. They played top 40s during our dinner which was nice!  I went on a...
Our Server George did a great job.  The pizza was super.... The pasta was not bad(I'm fairly picky about my sauce). The noodles we're cooked properly.  I'd definitely go back.  Thanks for feeding us.

Had to wait quiet a long time until we got seated although there were a lot of tables free. We ordered drinks at the bar while we waited and when we got seated, we were asked to pay the drinks - very inconvenient.
The food - I had simple pasta with tomato sauce and arugula - nearly had no taste at all.
Because we were a large group, the waiter asked - or rather determined that everyone would tip 15%.
The atmosphere is nice but doesn't make up for the flavourless food.

A relatively new restaurant right downtown Toronto just off Yonge Street at Gerrard, I went with friends from out of town who had discovered the place. The decor is positively amazing given that it's in a new building. Very large and open concept, in spite of the noise from an enormous crowd, it was amazingly intimate. Service was excellent, food was excellent, what can be said! Certainly a welcome addition to this area.

Went today for lunch to celebrate a friend's birthday.  The meal started off fine, we had an attentive waitress.  One of our friends is anaphylactic to peanut, banana and avocado.  She ordered the Angus burger and told the waitress about her dietary needs.  The waitress assured us that the burger contained none of the allergens and would specifically talk to the kitchen about her allergy.  Then came the food and everything was fine until my friend found a piece of avocado in her burger.  Luckily she didn't eat it, but we were shocked and upset with it.  Especially when we had specifically told them about the allergies. We called our waitress over right away and she was very apologetic about it.  She offered to cover the cost of the burger and asked if my friend would like to order something else.  Honestly at that point, none of us felt like eating anything anymore.  We asked to speak to the manager just to make sure they are aware of the severity of this error.  Our waitress was very helpful and went to look for him immediately.

He came and we told him that we just wanted to let him know about the problem.  He offered his apology and to cover the cost of the burger.  We asked him if he checked with the kitchen to see how could this have happened.  His simply said the kitchen was busy.  Yes, I understand the kitchen was busy but that shouldn't be the excuse.  To us he simply wanted to brush us off and not deal with the real issue. 

Anyway by then my friend started to feel funny and we all decided to leave. The waitress came back to offer dessert on the house, but we didn't want to stay.  Then they came out to give us another burger as a gesture of goodwill...I guess the kitchen felt bad but honestly none of us wanted to take it as we didn't want to be reminded of the burger incident.  However we felt bad in wasting food, so we took it but gave it away.

This is the worst birthday lunch. Not because of the food, not because of the error, mostly the way how the manager handled the situation.  I do not recommend this place to anyone.  

I give it one star because the waitress was good.

Arrived here for drinks. Really liked the decor and the ambiance. The music level was not overly loud so we could hear each other well. Ended up ordering stuffed meatballs and it was pretty good. Would recommend to add more craft beers to the selection! Looks like a great place for big groups.

reviews.text: This is my first time here and I am beyond impressed. If you like traditional European food done right this is your place. The beer selection is fabulous as...
We came here for $38 Summerlicious menu as we were starving in this area of the city.  I grabbed the gravlax carpaccio, veal jaeger schnitzel and we split...

This schnitzel is the real deal! With so many options it's worth every penny. You can choose the protein and the toppings.

The inside of this modest hub is...

An interesting place. Small but good selection of German beers and their in-house infused vodkas are a good company for the schnitzels. And the schnitzels are really good. I come from Eastern Europe, I know what I am talking about.
Rita, Alex and the whole Schnitzel Hub team! We are so glad we picked you for hosting our Christmas Party! Everyone loved the food, the service and the decor. We will definitely be back!

Came here for summerlicious. I was actually really excited because the menu looked great and I was craving eastern European cuisine. But it ended up being a huge disappointment. I had the eggplant schnitzel, which was so greasy it was inedible. Had the cherry pierogies for dessert. They were very tough and not very flavourful. The beet salad i had as an appetizer was good--it's the only thing I would eat again. 

The place itself was really big, felt casual.
The Schnitzel was way over priced for what you get. I never had Schnitzel so greasy, all 6 of us felt the same. The reataurant was clean and service was good.

Absolutely amazing food and service .
Will be back for sure 👍

reviews.text: Great place for having good conversation but agree with most that the food is only average.  In fact, I enjoyed my appertizer (grilled calamari) a lot more...
My colleagues and I were hosting visiting delegates from Hong Kong and decided to make reservations here for lunch. Its proximity to the university and...
Don't know why this place is so underrated.  The atmosphere is beautiful.  We came here for summerlicious.  I had the Truffle Caesar which was good but was...

Both times we were there - for dinner and then for breakfast while we stayed at the hotel - it was not busy at all. Lovely environment. Perfect lighting and interesting features to draw the eye. The dinner food was great. The breakfast was pretty ordinary (and hence very overpriced). While we enjoyed it and the convenience of it being right in the hotel (so we didn't have to leave the building at -17°C ) I would not choose to go there for the restaurant itself.
Amazing service, amazing food (octopus and chorizo salad had the most amazing octopus I've ever had), really fair prices for a hotel restaurant, beautiful interior
Excellent service. The bread is very tasty. Food is quite good.
Recent renovations have completed revitalized this restaurant. Excellent service and delicious food, highly recommended.

On the several occasions I have eaten here the place has been almost empty. Not sure why. The food is excellent, the service very friendly and professional,  and the prices, while not cheap, not all that bad. 

Granted it is in the Annex/Yorkville area and within a ten minute walk of nearly 50 other great places to eat.

But it is exceptionally convenient in that you can park underneath the hotel, or get a cab from the front door, or come by subway and walk just half a block.

Highly recommended.

pros: they take reservations and were accommodating it moving it back 

cons: waiting 40 minutes for an avocado toast with no recognition that it is a long...

Amazing brunch, the best pancakes I've ever had in my young 21 year old life. The Orange juice was delicious and freshly squeezed. The home fries were crispy but not too much so, and they brought us an assortment of hot sauces. The staff was so nice and made us feel like we had our own personal attendant in the busy restaurant. If you have any restraint about the price just know that you will get what you pay for. Will be back soon.

Decided to check this place out with a co-worker for a lunch. Had an offer through TIFF ($25 off your bill of $50 or more) so it was a great deal. I had the Grilled Cheese with Tomato Soup and my co-worker opted to get the French Onion Soup with Avocado Toast. Everything well made, well-portioned, and tasted delicious! The toast and grilled cheese were shareable so definitely try out a few things.

I have been here a few times for brunch and it is great! 

Any style of eggs are really good and the presentation is also well done.  They have a nice vibe and really great atmosphere for sharing a late morning with some friends. The beef skillet is awesome and they also have a nice eggs benny.

Good choice for a morning with some friends!

I had my birthday dinner here with a group of close friends and it was absolutely perfect. Intimate, cozy, eclectic decor, friendly and helpful staff and the food is to die for. All of my guests were pleased and said I scored a home run in terms of restaurant choice. Highly recommend. Their patio is great in the summer, too.

Beautiful location. Street parking. Green P. Free until 1pm on Sunday's, which makes for a good brunch anyway. 3 levels each more gorgeous than the other. Food a bit pricy but well worth the experience over all. Wonderful wait staff. Great washrooms. NOT just for gays. Great for Instagram posting. Large groups can be accommodated and reservations can be made.

* Food took FOREVER to come. We were surprised since the place was not full. Waitress was apologetic though once food came.
* One of our guests' food was cold. Not just was-once-warm-and-has-cooled, but physically cold to the touch. They took it back, prepared him a new one, and comped it.

* I'd go back, probably just to drink.

Wow  Jason  was awesome and the dinner was amazing the boys in the back rocked the plates.

The Owner came over with a cocktail treat very nice touch .

W and G

Amazing food.  The staff and owner are always hospitable.  Highly recommend this restaurant.

What an amazing experience!!!...Worth every hour/minutes drive from Guelph/Canada & a visitor from Australia!!!  

The service was amazingly friendly & welcoming from the moment we stepped in the restaurant.  We were, by coincidence, seated @ the 'Table 21', which was an added touch. The cocktail, 'Blushing Bride', was made to perfection, my main meal was cod, very tender, juicy, no bones, (an important factor for me to have no bones in my fish) and the potatoes were cooked to perfection, plenty of taste & crispy!  The wine I selected was followed by a compliment & story by the 'Sommelier', which was a very interesting story about the owner of the vineyard.  Highly recommend this fine restaurant & I certainly could give more than five stars for service and food.  Thank you for a wonderful restaurant experience.  Wishing you more of your success!!!!  Cheers Martine De Groof

Located in the heart of midtown Toronto, Tabülè offers a cozy ambience with refined yet comforting takes on the exotic flavours of the Middle East. Using the freshest quality ingredients, Goraichy's interpretation of traditional dishes has resulted in a menu bursting with robust flavour to delight the senses. Tabülè also offers vegan and gluten free menu options, and desserts made in house.  The drink menu includes a variety of wine, exotic martinis, fresh juices and loose leaf teas.

reviews.text:
Love middle eastern food!! Came here at an odd time for late lunch/early dinner. Place was empty but lots of reserved tables.

We ordered a bunch of...
Delicious. Have been to this location twice now, ordered the same app (platter with hummus, babahganouj, gluten-free tabouli and a side of gluten-free...
This place was jammed for a Saturday nite. Even though we had reservations we still will waited for 25 minutes (kinda defeats the purpose of a reservation)....

Very friendly service. Middle eastern food with western influences. Local ingredients including the meat. The mezza is expensive for what you get but was delicious. Service was top notch and atmosphere was nice. Will come again.

Great authentic middle eastern food with a western vibe. I went in for lunch, but being me I ordered lamb chops. They tasted great but were very small, I ordered a flafel to fill the spot. Food came out in a timely manner by from fantastic waitresses. I'm from out of town but I don't see why you would ever go in and be disappointed with anything.

The food is good I've tried the veal and the lamb chops. I'm not generally a fan of lamb chops as o find the taste and smell too strong but these lamb chops are very tender and do not have any smell. The veal is also soft. The veal and lamb are halal the chicken might not be. This is a perfect place if you are looking for a good halal restaraunt

Great food for a very reasonable price. The staff is nice and efficient. The Tabule is to die for! I have ordered the chicken (Tawuk) and it is delicious. It comes with grilled tiny onions. Just make sure to ask them for a well done chicken. Last time, it was not very well cooked. As improvement, I would suggest to give a small quantity of hummus with the bread while customers are waiting for their food.

What can I say about Tabule? We'll, for starters, it's the best middle Eastern food experience in Toronto. Every single item on the menu is mouthwateringly good, and very consistent. The service is always friendly. The decor and atmosphere are beautiful. The cocktails are inventive and delicious. Do yourself a favour and get the babaganouj with fresh pitas, your regret it! Also, swing by with a bottle or two of wine on Monday or Tuesday for free corkage (2 per table max)! In short, it is amazing and you'll love it!

I came here for Summerlicious with a group of 8 on a Tuesday night. Our reservation was for 8:30pm so by the time we got there, the place was starting to...

Came here for Winterlicious 2017. (I didn't realize that I've been here before for Winterlicious 2016-- their paellas are a 40 min wait!)

It's a very...
The food was delicious, the show was amazing. Really enjoyed our dinner. The service however, was quite slow and we felt our table was forgotten at some points.

Good quality tapas at a very good price. 4 of us shared about 75% of the menu. There was flaminco dance show that was fun and was about 20min. 

The server was great but the guy who sat us was super pissy and really started the night off on a bad foot. 

Paella was a bit oily but good overall. Good wine selection but a bit pricey.
One of our favorites. Try to get as much tapas as possible and share it. They all good. Also, several days a week they have a flamenco show - check their schedule on website.
Charcuterie board over priced not enough food. Great service. Amazing sangria

I have delightful experience. Food was just a bit pricy but the Flamenco performance and how delicious everything was is just woah. Place wasn't packed during December 20th dates which actually felt really nice, no much voice and great vibe.

Highly recommend the brick chicken. It is extremely juicy and flavorful. 

Also it comes on a bed of veggies including Brussel sprouts, spinach and beans. I...
I came here with a couple of friends before the Lady Gaga concert.  The restaurant is huge, so it was one of very few that had reservations open near the...

We had reservations here with the family after a Jay's game. 
Staff was very welcoming and and wait staff we exceptional. Atmosphere was very good. 
Ordered...

Kind of hidden and drowned out by its neighbours but a really good place to visit. There is a large amount of seating for different group sizes. The staff are extremely friendly. This type of restaurant is family owned and the restaurant interior goes long and deep. Food is tasty and comes in adequate to large portions (i.e. calamari). Pricing is average and well justified for the food.

Great service by Colin, great atmosphere, warm welcome, manager stopped by to make sure we were happy with our experience midway (a chance to course correct if we weren't but we were!), and extremely attentive colleagues filling water, etc. Kudos to all of these gents. Salad was delicious but pizza a little disappointing (crust overcooked yet soggy/hard to eat, very salty/overly saucy, not much too it). However every other time I've eaten there had beyond heavenly food. Thanks for efficiently, great environment for a business meeting and superb hospitality! Kudos too for recognizing great performers with your recognition program...I understand this mention will result in Colin getting movie passes - love organizations that immediately show value to their best talent!

The food here is excellent. Really top notch. I had the beef gnocchi and the ricotta cheesecake. It's a pricey place, to be sure, but you get what you pay for. A great meal.  And the service was good too.  I was with a big party. They made sure to get everyone's orders all at once so they didn't have to keep coming back throughout the meal interupting us.

We went as a group of 13 people. Service was great and the atmosphere was as well. 

The place is not cramped and not too loud, so having casual conversation with a group was easy. 

The staff there were also very prompt and helpful. All of our orders, appetizers, desserts, coffee and whatnot were served without a hitch. 

The food itself, while not mind blowing amazing, it was still  good.
Absolutely delicious food, I had a hard time deciding what to get because I wanted it all. It also has pretty nice outdoor seating in the summer 👍

reviews.text: After a long day of being a tourist, I needed a beer and a nice meal. The Blake House was relatively close to the downtown Hotel I was staying at and it was...

I was extremely excited because this was my first Summerlicious. For appertisers, I got the fish tacos which tasted good and there were 2 of them.

The...
Went here for Summerlicious 2017. The gnocchi was far too salty, nearly inedible. I recommend the strawberry pie and strawberry drink, however - both were...

Liked this place very much!!! The service was top notch and the food was very tasty!!! The only reason I don't give it a 5/5 is because of the place itself. It is a gorgeous house with a lot of potential, yet in my opinion it really lacks character. They renovated the interior and tried to be loyal to the original style but the outcome was quite bland. However, by no means this is a reason to not check this place out! I totally recommend it.

I really want to love this place. It's in a beautiful old mansion and in a great location. 
Large patio great for the summer, the interior has been renovated, but I feel it lacks a cozy feel that should go with the ambiance of the building. The food every time I have been has been lacking, it's not horrible, but it's not great and given the neighborhood, there are a lot of other choices. Nice place for some drinks with a friend, especially on the large patio.

This used to be a nice place. I went in couple nights ago. It was a cold night and me and my friend wanted a warm soup and our favorite Irish nachos. The soup came lukewarm. Which was a surprise. And then the nachos. While the plate was hot. The chilli on top of the potato chips was completely cold. Topped with even colder sour cream. 
It was disappointing and sad.
Love the Blake House!! Jimmy, one of the owners, is always smiling. Comfort food is elevated. Staff is congenial. Location is close to public transportation and parking next door. Great for groups.

Situated in a renovated heritage building, this place is full of character. Elaborate food menu with rotating daily specials. Wall murals feature photos of Jarvis street from the early 20'th century which adds to the atmosphere. This place is perfect for a romantic date. A bit on the pricey side, but well worth it.

reviews.text: went here as a late bday celebration for a friend. the atmosphere of this place is business casual/romantic. the dimly lit place really adds to this theme....
What a great spot for a night out! Well, more like a great spot to spend two hours. I've been here a couple of times now and I just love it. The ambiance...

The oysters were great. Frog legs were delicious. Cocktails were really good (and had copious amounts of alcohol!!) We went here for my fianceé's birthday and we had a large group. Our server was VERY nice and friendly.
Pretty pricey, though. (Not sure how/why it's showing up as "$$" on Google Maps). And for that, -1 star.

Great BBQ food here! Ribs, chicken, and brisket is well done. I am more of a Texan BBQ flavour type of individual but these dry flavours are great that they offer here. Great looking restaurant and ambiance is fantastic! The only reason why I am not giving it 5 stars is because of the price. BBQ food shouldn't be this expensive!

Great food and service was great. Only problem.. I told them it was a birthday dinner in advance and whoever called me said she would leave that in the notes but nothing was done? We were just given our bill and left. Normally I would’ve made a fuss about it especially when I made the reservation a week ago and confirmed the birthday two days prior but I didn’t want to spoil my SO’s birthday with a situation like that. 

Other than that, the food was incredible and service was excellent. Just wish they actually followed through when I decided to bring my SO to this restaurant for her birthday. 

5 stars for service and food... don’t want to hinder they’re rating because someone dropped the ball.

Service was excellent; however, food was horrible. Five stars for hospitality, one star for the food. They need a new chef, asap. The bar is beautiful and the ambiance is great but I don't think I'll be coming back unless they change the chef.

Really cool restaurant. The service was excellent. 

The beef brisket was... Mouth watering. It was one of the most delicious peices of neat that I've ever tasted. It's as if everyone in the room disappeared, and it was just me and the beef. Highly recommend trying it.

reviews.text:
Very nice place .good food good service.
Excellent wait staff.happening place.
Very bright decor inside
We dropped in for a quick lunch at The Chase this week. It is an interesting experience since the dining room is divided between the first and fifth floors....

We ate in the downstairs part of this restaurant.

I have to say -- we were treated just great.
We did not have a reservation, and so ended up a table by...

Fantastic service staff give your honest suggestions and very friendly. The food was good just not wow nor amazing like what I had expected with the price. The panroast with a variety of seafood in broth tasted more heavy on the creamy broth. The green curry with chickpeas was good.

Disappointing. 
We booked our reservation online. The system asks if we are celebrating anything and even allows one to tick off 'birthday' 'female' etc. We also entered that we were celebrating our mom's 75th birthday and would like a nice table, if possible. We were seated in the downstairs area, it looked fine, I wasn't going to complain. It seemed  nice and the server we had was excellent. Just as the server started taking our drink order, the live music started. She cringed and said, unprompted, 'I'll ask him to turn it down'. We thanked her. We saw her motion to him to turn it down AND we asked two more times over the next half hour if it could be turned down, explaining we could barely talk to each other. It was never turned down. To be fair, the guy was a good singer and it would have been a very nice addition to the atmosphere if it was a reasonable volume or acoustic. (actually acoustic would have created a lovely, classy atmosphere as it's not a large restaurant). I'm going to guess that we weren't the only ones not enjoying it as people were not clapping at the end of his songs. 
The food was excellent but there is excellent food at many restaurants where you have have a more pleasant, enjoyable time and talk to your companions. Also, I don't understand why their reservation system asks if you're celebrating anything when they don't acknowledge it. Bottom line, I doubt we'll be back, we did not leave feeling happy.
Decent food. An obvious choice for medium-high end seafood. Nice atmosphere, though the acoustics might amplify the din a bit. Service was good. Dark and stormy was excellent.

Went here with two friends for birthday lunch. Opted to sit inside as it was quite humid outside. Good atmosphere. We shared the fish and chips, the Bay platter and the fried chicken. You could tell the clams were a bit old otherwise everything on the fresh seafood platter was fine. I'd have to say for a seafood restaurant the fried chicken is damn delicious!! Would go back there just for that. As it was my birthday they brought me out a flambe banana split with dark cherry sauce and Neapolitan ice cream. Oh hot damn - that and the chicken was my favourite part!
Wasn't thrilled with the quality!  Our server was good.  But for the price point one would expect better!

lic_profile: The Fifth’s boutique restaurant offers a rooftop patio, romantic ambience and delicious cooking. The Dining Room is an intimate space with fire-side sofas and eclectic décor while the Terrace is a rooftop oasis with spectacular views of downtown Toronto. Headed by Executive French Chef JP Challet and Chef Robert Toppan, the accomplished culinary team creates a modern cuisine to reflect today’s tastes and respect vegetarian and gluten-free diets. This summer, enjoy alfresco dining with Mediterranean inspired foods, wines and fresh flavours from the French Riviera to the Amalfi Coast.

reviews.text:
Small restaurant tucked upstairs of the club. Beautiful antique decor with superb food and service.

We were greeted at the entrance of the club and walked...
Came here with a big group and ordered from a selected group menu. I loved the big table in the Terrance. Its wide enough that you can hear everybody. (vs...
Located above the night club easy on the fifth, is a classy, beautiful restaurant. Lovely staff and lovely interior. Every dish we ordered was spectacular...

Excellent atmosphere with descent food. The restaurant is hidden on the fifth floor of the nightclub downstairs. Very well decorated. We ordered the lobster risotto and braised beef, they were not die-in-the-heaven good tasting but fits well with the atmosphere.  If you keep your receipt for the restaurant you get to go the club downstairs with the cover charge waived.

Very cool entrance. Felt like I was coming out of the movie Goodfellas. Its unique and cozy.  Food is good. Service was fantastic! We had the osso buco and lobster risotto, with a meat and cheese platter. Stayed for about 3 hours. And felt very welcomed. We could have got access to the bar downstairs (dinner includes the entrance fee) but we had other things on our mind after that meal.

Updated my review...
2016 review: 5 stars! Delicious French cuisine in a very elegant setting. The food was amazing from appetizer to dessert. The staff waa attentive and friendly. The freight elevator ride was a fun bonus 😉

2017 August review: 3 stars! I'm not sure if the ownership or chef has changed but the quality has not stayed the same compared to the previous times we have gone. The cocktail list is smaller. The desserts are not as elaborate. The opera cake I had before was house made but this time, I think it was store bought. The freight elevator is not functioning any more 🙁

I was at the Fifth last night for a wedding. The food was delicious and the venue was stunning! But what was really over the top was the service! Karen was the server at my table if 10, which included a 1 year old, 2 year old and 4 year old. She was amazing with them and so accommodating and attentive with us. Definitely recommend the Fifth for dinner or an event.
Had the best wedding here. Staff was amazingly attentive. Would use this place for every major event!

reviews.text: This would have to qualify as a "fine dining" establishment in my books.  I have had Indian food all over town, but this is definitely a more plush, upscale...
I've never been to the Host before in Toronto.  I went to their Markham location once many years ago.  I was working in the neighbourhood and looking for a...
When I went there the first time I thought their buffet was nice. Had some goat curry, butter chicken I think and some desert. But when I went there a...

Went here twice in 2017, once for Mother's Day - the food and service were amazing!  So we decided to come back again in November.  I don't know what happened in between, but the portions have shrunk, prices went up, and most importantly the recipes have changed (eggplant bartha, for example... what a let down).  The waiter had to be flagged down any time we needed something, otherwise we couldn't find him.
We might give this old favourite another shot, but most likely will go elsewhere.

Food was great, except I found the meats were all a little dry. Also, for the price, I do expect slightly larger portions. Very nice restaurant however, good service and tasty food otherwise. Meal presentation is top-notch!

A good Indian restaurant with fine dining ambience and well presented food. Time taken to serve food is very high. It's better to order all the course at once to avoid long pauses between appetizers and main course. Hospitality can be improved.

I have been to Richmond Hill location and enjoyed the service and the food. Last night, went to the Toronto location for the first time. Good service and atmosphere. Food is below average. Chicken of Butter Chicken was not fresh, all thee types of bread that we order were over cooked, actually burned black all under the bread.
I will not go back to this location.

First time going to the Richmond Hill location. Had to wait to be seated longer than I would expect. 
I found the tables to small to hold all our dishes. Did ask for a bigger table, server said no.
Food was okay. Biriyani was not the greatest. I’ve had from local take out places for cheap and tasted way better. 
Chicken tikka masala was great. This will not be my last time visiting tho. Will give it another try.

I dropped by based on the reviews here. 
Was looking for good food and a glass of wine. Veal was cooked perfectly  .
Great service.  Awesome food. Nice...
Dropped by for Winterlicious a little while ago ($38/person). Atmosphere is nice, it's very elegant and classy. I would say that the seats are quite tight...

Our Summerlicious pick this year in an effort to explore more restaurants near us. The set menu looked good for $35 tier. 

Started with the grilled octopus...
Love the chocolate molten cake!! They also serve wine and other foods such as salads and veal. Loved it here.
Excellent food and service. I am a repeat client. I know that I will leave satisfied.
Amazing for summerlicious. The lamb was great
Food is amazing, Calamari and Rack of lamb the best I have had. The chef pops out of the kitchen to ask how your meal is. great service and experience.

Maybe this is a fascinating place to folks living in around Lawrence and Bridal/Post Rd crowd but definitely it's not for younger crowd who's actually tasted a bit of diverse food and can take flavours other than salt. 👎🏼👎🏼

reviews.text: Great place to hang out for a quick drink Or have a night out with the friends on the weekends. The service is great. If youre a regular they will always...

One of the worst pub food I've ever had. Ordered four different take out items and they all sucked.

I ordered nachos, tacos, and two different spaghettis.

Went at around 8pm with a date just to check it out and get some quick food and shots in before a movie. --

(-3) Terrible, slow, inattentive, and at times,...

Food was not great, we got wings for 8 people, some of them were cold and in general not of a good quality. Other people in our party ordered other pasta and it was not good either.. the stars are for the waiter she was fun and nice. The menu is standard, the beer selection is really minimal and nothing worth drinking. The only reason we went was because there was rla table for a large group with no reservation. Now I understand why.

So this is the story of my horrible experience at the Office Pub on King and Yonge. As a young professional, I automatically thought of Office Pub when looking to book a friendly Christmas lunch for 15 people. I called the morning of, and they accommodated to my needs. Arriving at the pub, I was greeted by friendly staff, after we sat down I realized some of my colleagues could not make it to lunch and by some I meant 4 guests!!! The staff quickly turned on us, as they demanded we moved to a new table by the door ( side note: December in Toronto is freezing cold). I kindly asked if they would allow us to keep our seats and just move the extra table, but they instead they told us the only option is if we pay $20.00 per head that didn’t show up. I was appalled at the condescending comment, I felt so angry at the lack of service presented to a group of 10 people. I am never going back to the office pub and now I know why they’re never busy.

Terrible beer selection.  The bartender was somewhat awkward in serving us.  
Then he came to us and asked if he could give us the cheque.  This is a huge pet peeve of mine.  I didn't come here exclusively to tip him, and I only expect to pay a bill once in an establishment.  
Then we found out he is the manager.  
.................
Ummmm...taking tips, forcing us to pay up so you can walk away with cash.  You've got a lot to learn about hospitality.  Unfortunately it probably won't be at the office, because if people are treated this way on the regular it won't be around long.  
That is the last bill I pay at The Office for sure.
We had a couple of Whiskey doubles, which were prepared promptly. The service was attentive and the beer/liquor selection was pretty decent.
Friendly staff. Good food. Good entertainment. All around good environment.
