"Sure, Ivan. We can meet at the Queen and Beaver for lunch today". I said thinking it was probably like one of the firkins. 

It is definitely not one of...
I'm torn about the rating I've given this restaurant. The service was great and the restaurant had a coolness to it with the use of Brittanic kitsch decor....
Last night myself and two others came into an absolutely packed restaurant and immediately regretted not booking a reservation. Just before deciding to go...

To be clear, I am only reviewing on the service of  the beer we ordered.
  My wife and I stopped in on Saturday to grab a brew to kill time for our dinner next door.  We appreciated the decor of the pub on the second floor with a real cozy  warm feeling to help keep the cold wet weather at bay. The waiter was pleasant and informative with a good rapport. The beer choice was not as extensive as I would thought but it has something for everyone.
  I am willing to come back at a later date to try their food

Bit pricy for my taste, however great food and great service. Favourite location for our company's pub nights. Food is fantastic! Also, their Ketchup is the best I have ever tasted! Feels like a good English pub!

Service was friendly and attentive. Food was not quite what was expected when it arrived. The bacon butty is actually pork belly and is served on the bun with red cabbage. Pork belly is fine, but is mostly fat/gristly.
The mixed fruit/berry side was made of blueberries, raspberries, and blackberries, which was awesome - nice that there was no honeydew or cantaloupe (the filler in most fruit salads).

Very warm and friendly service. We stayed here for a couple of hours before our flight back home, and had a lovely lunch. Their burger is amazing. Chopped steak cooked to your preference.

The only complaint is that our server gave the wrong beer to my friend. She didn't want to mention it so drank the mistake beer.

Been here twice with friends. 

It has a much homier feel than most other places in the Yonge/Dundas area and there aren't many places I'd take over this one in this part of the city. 

Service is very friendly, and the decor is really nice. Last time I was there, I had the Haddock and Chips; it was tasty enough, but a pretty conservative portion at a high price ($19). The beer selection is good, nothing special but with a few local brews and a bit of everything. 

The Scotch Egg and Sticky Toffee Pudding are my favourite things I've had here.

reviews.text:
I just cant stop loving this place. 

Its tiny, tiny, tiny and if you blink you just might miss it from the street view, but oh so good. 

My personal fav's...
Just want to start off with how amazing their service was. We had the pleasure of being waited on by Caitlin. She made sure we were enjoying our environment...
A friend and I came upon this almost hidden diner while walking down Yonge street after touring the Mount Pleasant Cemetery. I think it was the word "diner"...

What a delightful place this is! Their menu is unique and full of flavours from all over the world, and the atmosphere is quaint and charming with a small interior restaurant and a bigger patio outside. Highly recommend their middle eastern food, as their hummus and felafel were to die for!
A favorite - shakshouka for brunch is the bomb, steak frites are the bomb, service is great, the place is cozy and cute but a little small to maneuver around. The washrooms are also a little smelly

Rosedale Diner is a Rosedale classic. Always good food, and good coffee and drinks. A tad pricey sometimes but for the neighbourhood understandable. Patio in the back is awesome, service is great. 4.5 stars if I could.

I had brunch here recently and the food I ate was very disappointing. The menu items all sounded interesting, but they cut a lot of corners on the dishes. 

I ordered the basic breakfast with poached eggs,  sausage, challah, and sausage. 

1. Eggs arrived cold
2. Toast was burnt (black) on one side but they flipped it over and served it anyways
3. Salad greens were wilted, and dressing was uninspired 
4. Breakfast sausage was just a totally regular grocery store sausage that was cut in pieces.
Amazing food.  Stopped in for a quick lunch and drinks. Blood brothers cherry ale was awesome!

reviews.text: The only saving grace for this restaurant is the BEAUTIFUL atmosphere and the belly dancing show. Otherwise the food portions for the appetizers were tiny...

I have only been to Sultan's Tent once, and had some mixed feelings about it, then I decided never to visit again.
Although it has some great potential...

First let's talk about food. As far as taste, the food was fine, edible but nothing to write home about. 

We ordered the Chèvre Brûlée appetizer, which...

A great, great bar. The food is incredible (the hummus is creamy garlicky heaven) and the crab cakes are nothing short of perfect. Eating here is a pleasure (did I mention belly dancers?) the bar staff is sheer perfection, if you want the dining room, better make a reservation, but...I have to say, as a place to snack and drink. They get it right. Love this place DEFINITELY going back.

Very delicious food!  Staff are very patient and will take the time to answer any questions you have about the menu, although service was a bit slow. Great entertainment. The belly dancing show is 15 - 20 minutes and if it's not too busy, the dancers go to each table and invite people to join them in dancing, which makes for a few laughs. Very traditional food, decor, and music which made for a great atmosphere, definitely unlike any other restaurants located downtown. Expect it to lighten your wallet, but overall a great experience.

For a few hours you feel like you've been transported out of the city to somewhere more spicy and warm. Guests sit in fabric covered tents with pillow covered benches. We enjoyed all of the food, especially the lamb shank. The mint tea is the best I've ever had. The belly dancers were fantastic.

Yummy food and great entertainment. It definitely is pricey but it is an experience. I would recommend to  atleast try it once. The food is amazing but pricey. You usually get a 3 course meal which is around $50 per person.

Been wanting to try this place for a while, (mostly for the belly dancers) and to be honest, I wish I didn't. Definitely not worth the $72 per person (tax and gratuity included for a group price) for the food or service. The food does not match the price even remotely and although our server was very nice, was not very attentive (probably because of the auto 18% tip he knew he would get regardless of service). The atmosphere was cool and belly dancers were very interactive. Less than mediocre experience, would not go again.

The atmosphere was nice, but packed all the time after 7 and too loud to hear the waiters/waitresses.
My friend pointed out two guys at the counter and said to a waitress that she wanted to get what they were having. But she didn't bring it for 10 minutes so my friend thought she forgot it and ordered again. Then it took her another 10 minutes to bring the drink though she was chatting with her co-workers.
When we asked for our bill, we were charged 3 beers that we didn't order. So we claimed that that was not our order, however, she insisted that we asked her to buy the beers to the guys at the counter and the way she explained so was very rude and unprofessional.
We were so shocked and disappointed with her. She ruined our pleasant Friday night and we will never come back even though we liked the place :(

reviews.text:
Tiny gem downtown. Because it is fairly small, it's better to come early or make a reservation if coming with a larger group of people.

Thoroughbred's...
I came here for my birthday just with my sister. Visiting Toronto I wanted to go somewhere with a tasting menu that would take a last minute reservation. We...
The word you are looking for is pretentious, there are better, cheaper, more comfortable or classier or more hip/fun restaurants in Toronto for less. The...

One of my favourite restaurants in Toronto. Food is absolutely impeccable -- always perfectly cooked, creatively presented, and of course, delicious. Service has always been great too. Highly recommend getting the tasting menu, which is amazing value for money. Atmosphere is cozy and romantic, but my only small complaint would be that its a little cold inside in the winter and they could turn the heat up higher. I did bring it up on my last visit and it got warmer but not as warm as I'd like. Will definitely come back here again!!

I came here for drinks while waiting for a movie and I was impressed.  Not only were the cocktails made to absolute perfection but the staff were kind, helpful and friendly.  The ambience was perfect - lighting soft, music wasn't too loud and could still hear your guests as they were beside or across from you.

My only regret was I didn't order any food!  Next time will certainly I dulge in their fare.
Love this place, the food is great and very well priced for the quality. Atmosphere is casual and intimate. The fried.chicken and champagne special has become a monthly outing with friends.

visited there while private event and had a great time but bartenders were horribly slow and terrible money and order handling. I felt I spend more time by bar due to speed of service. Great washroom facility eveb though small was clean and place capacity is not large either

I've eaten at Thoroughbred twice. Once almost two years ago as part of a group where we did a tasting menu and once for a quick bite before a movie. 

The tasting menu was good. From what I remember, the food was good. We went on a Friday or Saturday night and the ambience was the most memorable part of the meal. They have a DJ playing good music and nice mood lighting. 

Unfortunately my experience on my recent visit was not as good. While our server was friendly, she almost entirely forgot about our table. We waited for almost 15 minutes for the POS terminal before paying cash (no tip) and walking out. Food was not outstanding either considering the pricing. We had their fried chicken special, but the batter on both variations we ordered barely stuck to the chicken. 

TLDR: One good and one bad experience. Decent food and supbar service.

reviews.text: Decided to try out Toula for Summerlicious 2017. I had no idea the reviews for Toula were bad until I decided to check them out while waiting for our food....

A very disappointing night, but we made the best of it and enjoyed some fine company and good cheer together.

My review is quite delayed, though I have...
If you really don't want to leave the hotel or can't leave the hotel then go ahead and eat here but be prepared to pay 150% normal pricing for 50%...

I thoroughly enjoyed my experience at Toula. The view 38 floors above the city is magnificent. I was there for Canada celebrations and the view of the fireworks display on the lake was simply amazing. What I enjoyed most about Toula on this night was the service. Everyone from the hostess to servers to managers were extremely pleasant and professional. Their courtesy was exemplary. The quality, taste and presentation of the food was the clincher for me. I will return to Toula for all my special occasions.

Restaurant has an amazing 360 view outside and the interior is also nice. You can see the islands, lake, city etc. When I went it was pretty empty and nice. Not over crowded like CN Tower 360. This is a way better alternative and not known by most people which makes it even better. The food was alright, probably on par with similar styles of restaurants. No complaints.

The food was simply spectacular... I had the salmon on black rice and it was perfectly cooked. My colleagues had steak and fish (basso) which were perfectly cooked. The presentation was great. The only problem with Toula was the poor service... it appeared to stem from a lack of knowledge not any malice. For examples, and there are many; no water and no waiter for long stretches of time even though the restaurant was not too busy, not very attentive during the meal, the waiter did not know the menu and could not Pronounce any of the Italian names, nor did he even attempt. He was hard to hear when he spoke and he appeared very nervous. 

Despite the poor service I would come back for the food!!!

Service is fairly good, even though there aren’t many people here. The view is nice.
The food is mediocre and poorly served at least my risotto occupies only a third of the plate size. Also, my risotto should come with truffle slices, but maybe it’s an invisible tasteless specimen the one they serve here.

A very disappointing night, but we made the best of it and enjoyed some fine company and good cheer together.

My review is quite delayed, though I have been meaning to write this for some time.

My elderly parents live in Bruce County and came to visit me and my husband to have Thanksgiving in the city.  We were excited to host them here because we usually do it at their place up north.  However, due to unforeseen circumstances, as the weekend drew closer, it became clear that we were not going to be able to host it in our home so we had to find another venue to enjoy Thanksgiving with my parents.

There weren't a lot of places open that weekend, so we wound up choosing to go to Toula.  We thought that this would be a remarkable place to share Thanksgiving together.  Living downtown, it had the added benefit of being able to park there, which was a very important feature for my parents who can not walk long distances.

It'd been years since we had all gone there, but we all remembered it very fondly, with it's revolving view of the lake and city, the wonderful food and that "X" factor you have when something has a special experience associated to it.

Toula is also connected to a hotel, which we thought would almost guarantee that there would be a Thanksgiving-oriented menu to choose from.  I should have confirmed that in advance. You know what they say about assuming.  In any case, that was one of our several disappointments for the evening.

So, we arrived, granted, with high expectations for a lovely evening. 
Well, at least we had each other, and that was enough to be thankful for.

We arrived at the hotel to park our car, $25 right away for parking.  Fine.  We figured the night would be worth it.

We arrived at Toula and were seated right beside a not terribly exciting view of an old, brutalist cement condo building, which again we thought would be fine, because the restaurant revolves and soon we'd be facing the lake or other more attractive parts of the city.

Nope.  Not revolving.  Hasn't in years. Brutalist cement condo views are all the rage now apparently.  Welcome to the big city Mom & Dad.  Hope you enjoy our finest views.  

Fine.  We know the food will be great.  Bring on the turkey.

Nope.  Not turkey. Not stuffing. No cranberry sauce. Not even mashed potatoes. No Thanksgiving menu to be found....in a hotel restaurant.  Surprised, and disappointed, the blame is my own.  Note to self, call ahead to confirm things for special occasions.

So, we find things on the menu that we thought we'd like.  The sad truth is, even that too, priced as it was for fine dining, was anything but.  We found our food cold and flavourless.  Perhaps they gave the head chef the night off as well. Good for them if they did.  Too bad for us.

Well, we had wine, and we toasted each other and decided to make the very best we could of this night because that is what it was about.  

But wine has a way of travelling through you, so eventually, dad, unfortunately very frail, needed to use the facilities.  When he asked someone where they were, they pointed him to a stairwell he could take to a restroom on a lower floor.  He stressed that he was fairly disabled and asked if there was not a restroom on the main floor he could use. No, no restroom. Go downstairs sir. The restroom is downstairs.

I would have held it and stewed in anger myself.  Not my dad. Fortunately, he had the wisdom to approach another staff member who was kind enough to escort him to a staff restroom on the main level (i believe in the kitchen), but beggars can't be choosers.  I was just glad that he finally found an appropriate option.

I won't even get into the size of the bill considering what we had, but none of us felt the value was there. Weren't we thrilled that we paid $25 to park there to enjoy this night?

Whatever charm Toula held for us in the past, it is sadly not ever going to be part of our future.  Good luck to you if you go.  Ask for the lake view. You'll get it all night.

Terrific restaurant located inside the Marriott Eaton Centre (Downtown) so extremely convenient if staying there and worth a trip even if not.
Food is...
Décor is quite modern. Seating options include stools at the bar, tables, and high-backed curved booths.The hotel is just off the lobby, so it can be a bit...

Inside a Marriott Hotel near Yonge and Dundas, this is a small place with a modern atmosphere. 

I was pleasantly surprised at their Winterlicious lunch....

Worst food in Canada. They serve it on paper like McDonald's. Must be saving on dishwasher.
No plates in 4-star hotel bistro! All your lunch including a bunch of sauce dishes on top of your food will be thrown in one bowl like you do it for your pets. You are supposed to enjoy it.
Fries looked like somebody has already eaten them, smelled like machine oil. Most likely chef does not know what fries are.
Food Inspection Agency should've this place closed down.
Never again. There is a clear reason why its' not packed in the heart of downtown.

A fairly quiet hotel restaurant, came here on Valentine's Day and it was pretty empty despite being in a busy part of the city, didn't order much from their main menu so I can't say much for that but their desserts were delicious
Quiet venue despite the centrality of the location.  Amazingly simple yet yummy menu.  Discreet staff.

Our party of four went for dinner before the theatre tonight. When our reservations were made, they were informed that we had severe onion allergies in our party, and assured us they could accommodate. The atmosphere is beautiful but the meals were horrible. The chicken my mother ordered tasted like day old chicken, the lamb was inedible and hard to cut, never mind chew, and when we requested an alternative, we were told that they had nothing for us at all, despite having been informed of the allergies. The staff was very unapologetic, and were, in fact, quite rude. The inedible lamb was barely touched and yet the item appeared on the bill, even after it was brought to management's attention. Our entire experience was incredibly unsatisfactory. We are season ticket holders for Mirvish, are always entertaining out of town guests and are constantly looking for good places to go to dinner. We will not be going back. In fact, we will be letting everyone know exactly how rude and ignorant the staff truly is. The only reason it's getting a 1-star rating is that it will not allow me to post without it.
My favorite restaurant yet...food is amazing and prices are responsible.

reviews.text: I love this restaurant :) My husband and I come here on special occasions from time to time, and recently I also did a menu tasting for my dad's birthday....

We live in the city about 10 minutes away and wanted a nice break after a long work day and walking home after work. 

The vibe of this lobby lounge is...
Went there for winterlicious lunch. Hostess and all other people, we had to deal with, were super nice, except for our server. He came up to us with no any...

Very poor service. They advertise a Nutcracker menu but seem surprised when you arrive pre or post show. The menu for that isn't great. I've eaten there 4 times because I enjoyed the food. However the last time we waited over an hour for our food...at 3 in the afternoon. It was impossible to flag down a server. The restaurant was not full and there were 5 staff running around but not really serving. It was very disappointing. Although the food is good I won't be going back. The poor service ruins the meal.

I Haven't enjoyed a breakfast like this in a very long time. Breakfast included with the room was only the cold stuff, paid extra $5 for access of all the buffet. 
Atmosphere is great. Will definitely eat there again when in Toronto.

The bruschetta was lovely and featured a rather novel guacamole instead of the usual mix of tomatoes. My mac and cheese was creamy, but lacked seasoning. It could also have benefited from the introduction of a stronger cheese and/or vegetables. The quality of service was decent.

Went this afternoon for a late lunch before the nutcracker.  Service was AWFUL - took over an hour to get our food - due to the horrendous service was supposed to be have portions of the bill taken care of and was not - had to speak to the manager 3 times - will never go here nor will I recommend - waste of money - way to expensive for what was served - ordinary fish (cod) and chips which was $23 - completely outrageous

Excellent food and impeccable service. I ordered the maple-glazed chicken and it was absolutely delicious. The chef clearly put a lot of time in creating his dish as all the flavours were in absolute harmony, and I don't say this lightly, this is a very hard task to accomplish. Everything tasted like it belonged there: the sweetness of the maple glaze on the chicken was beautifully balanced with pepper flavours from perfectly blanched kale, a carefully-chosen mushroom species, and wilted cabbage. Furthermore, the execution was great; the chicken was tender and juicy and the vegetables are wilted to an ideal amount of crunchiness. To top it all off, my waiter and all service staff were courteous and exceptionally welcoming. The only thing I would change is the layout of the restaurant, ideally it would be completely secluded from the lobby and have a lower ceiling to give a more intimate feeling, but this wasn't terribly distracting, ad the food and the service were so good, I wouldn't hesitate to give it 5stars. Finally, yes this is more expensive than the average restaurant, you won't get a meal for under $20, however you are paying for quality that is miles higher than your average restaurant.

reviews.text: This is my favourite restaurant !! Everything so delicious and services are perfect!!!
I came here for summerlicious dinner on a Friday and got a really nice table in front of the open window. The ambiance of the restaurant is more upscale...
One would think being the only paying diners at the restaurant on a Friday evening would garner better service, but that was the exact opposite. The staff...

My girlfriend and I, along with another couple, had an absolutely fantastic dining experience at Tutti Matti. We originally thought that a 9 pm reservation might be a little late but the restaurant was still very busy and there was a great ambiance amongst the crowd.
I will keep it short and sweet about the food. EVERY SINGLE THING we had was perfectly cooked and absolutely delicious!!
I will say this.. GET THE SHORT RIBS!!! 
Our lovely server Holland couldn't stop raving about them so naturally we had to try them. Hands down the best short rib I have ever had.
There is an excellent selection of Italian wines that chef has taken the time to accurately pair with the seasonal ingredients being used in the dishes. Very close attention to detail in this restaurant and it shows. 
I highly recommend this place and I cannot wait to go back!

Weekly international travel has allowed the incredible opportunity to dine at some of the world's best restaurants. Unfortunately there has been an obvious decline of the attention many in the industry offer, to guess, their pride is lacking. Never could we have guessed, that mere blocks from home, my wife & I would experience an exceptional evening as a result of exceptional service. Our server Mark introduced himself & are we glad he did. Mark is in a league all his own.!! It was our 10th wedding anniversary & Mark helped to make it a night we won't forget. 
A suggestion: get to Tutti Matti & ask for Mark.  We can't say enough good things. Mark, thank you. You've created a loyal following. We'll look forward to returning soon.
Excellent service. Stopped in a little late and asked if the kitchen was still serving. Not pressured to speed up our dinner once. Very good.
Amazing food and ambiance, service was really good and they have nice wine selection.

Terrible experience !! Food is nothing special and too expensive , service is poor, but the worst is actually the owner , who happens to be the chef and a waiting tables  in the same time, very odd right?! She was so rude and angry, absolutely unprofessional . I prefer spend my money in a much more cozy and pleasant environment than this place

Although this place does not have the most accessible parking...

Everyone from the hostess to the waiters were...
I believe this place has the best burgers in the city. The service is usually satisfactory (no one would accuse this place of being fast, even at the best...

Really friendly staff, good food, excellent service, kitchen open late, and a fun place overall. Unpretentious which is refreshing in this city. Only comment us that the place is VERY LOUD so it's not conducive to small intimate conversations. You have to speak loudly to be heard.  Highly recommend.

Social Eatery is fantastic! Venue is animated and friendly; service is consisently top shelf; price points are very reasonable; good menu selections, all prepared to high standard. If you have a group function, Marla is great - very thorough and accommodating. The best!
This is a go-to place for my husband and I. Great food, great service and great atmosphere. Definitely try whatever the chicken sandwich of the day is, they're always on point.

This is an upscale pub with plenty of TVs for sports, and lots of different booths and seating options for folks who may not be interested in watching the game.  The food is above your average pub fare, and there is a good selection of beers; certainly more than most sports bars would offer.
Service is good. Great place to come for a few drinks. Nice dining/bar area with lots of tv's. Food is average.

SERVICE: Extremely...

Went to lunch after Christmas with 5 person family group. Prices were in line with the neighborhood - I understand going around the back there is a cheaper take out lunch. The dinning room was pretty setup. (If someone had low vision black nakpins and menu might prove difficult) Service was reasonable - all the lunch where a bit bigger than any non lumberjack need but the food was very good and the service was very polite and non intrusive. Would happy recommend.

Very good place. Discret place. Waitress is very nice and smile. Clean. The dinner was very good, delicious. It was very late and the waitress was alone and she was very operational. We will come back :)

we went for my mom's birthday and the food was absolutely tasty. on top of that staffs were very helpful and nice. I would recommend to anyone who would like to try Italian restaurant in downtown Toronto.

Fresh ingredients and such delicious food! Excellent service too! Catered our last event with them - and it couldn’t have gone better. Easy to work with and our friends raved about the food!  Loved it!

Hospitality at its Worst:
Nov 29, 2017 went around 11.50am. About 12 of us had a lunch reservation at Vagabondo. 
Went sat looked through the menu. The waiter came around 12.10 and we were about to order. One of our guys asked if we could order from the express instead the menu as he had a meeting at 1.00pm. The waiter cautioned that the space reserved was for menu orders only but since were already there and not all of us were to get express he would allow us. As some were getting ready to go to the express, and i was about to taste the bread the manager came up and ordered all of us out of the reserved space to the area where express takeout patrons sit. This was a farewell occasion to one of our colleague. I got disgusted the way the manager treated and walked out. I go for lunch to Vagabondo once in a way. Will not step into this place that lacks basic courtesy and hospitality.

reviews.text: Been here twice, and had a pleasant experience both times. The first time I tried their prix fixe lunch menu and ordered a Caesar salad, chicken parmigiana,...

Servers and staff are friendly and nice. Beyond that I don't know how this place is still running? 

Save your $ and go to some of the better options along...
This is a decent place to go for your summerlicious/winterlicious fix. For $28, the dinner portions should leave you full, although I found the taste to be...

This restaurant is one of the friendliness places I have ever experienced. It is very cosy but has a romantic feel, and their prefixed dinner have a super good deal, with a variety of selections. Our family comes here all the time, and is always greeted with friendly servers. This is definitely worth 5 stars.

I went to this place on a Sunday evening an hour before closing, and I was absolutely thrilled with my meal. The food was some of the freshest I have ever tasted. I cannot speak highly enough about how flavorful it was! Just like Nonna's cooking! Both myself and my date were completely satisfied. I had a pasta dish and he had a pizza, and both were incredible. Will definitely be coming here regularly! A true taste of Italy.

I've come only for breakfast/brunch and have only great things to say.
Pros: amazing breakfast complete with fruits. Delicious! Waffles are also yummy. Never a wait!
Cons: nothing to say!

Four of us enjoyed New Year's eve dinner at Valens and ordered four different mains - artic char, risotto, seafood pasta and mushroom ravioli. Rave reviews for all four - fresh, delicious, hot, and cooked to perfection. In addition, the carrot, pear and coconut soup was excellent as was the Caesar salad.  Dessert was included in the fixed prix menu and was not exceptional, but was good, and there were a couple of a la carte desserts (e.g. crème brulee) that we could have ordered for a little more $$. Valens offers fixed prix dinners throughout the year at $30 and kept NYE dinner at $30 as well - unheard of in Toronto!

One of the best dine-in lunch spots on Baldwin St.

My co-workers and I were sad when Sambucas closed, but glad that Valens menu and service continues to match in similarity to the previous restaurant.

Food (I've had the salads, pastas, pizzas, sandwiches, desserts) is delicious, fresh and good quality.  They have also offered pri-fixe menu during lunch time, where the portions are very generous, resulting in the need for take out of left overs (no complaints here)!

Staff are friendly.  Service a bit slower than when it was Sambucas, but still attentive.

Thought it would have been more authentic Italian cuisine, but it was very average. The menu and other ratings had us expecting a much more romantic and traditional Italian restaurant, but we were disappointed.

Had a beautiful dinner here. Homemade pasta with an amazing caprese salad and each were less than $20. Amazing waiter and a ton of cool photos on the wall from when celebrities visited and ate at the restaurant.

lic_profile: Contemporary, chic and offering an intimate community vibe, Veloute Bistro is located in the heart of the Beach. Veloute follows the terroir farm-to-table slow food movement using locally sourced ingredients. Having achieved the level of Saucier and French cuisine at the Paris Marriott Hotel Champs-Elysees, Chef Fawzi Kotb's menu is designed to inspire and challenge the most discerning palate. Sommelier Alise Matos can help you select from the extensive wine list for the perfect complement to every dish.  Alternatively, feel free to bring your own bottle.

reviews.text: My boyfriend and I have dined here multiple times due to its excellent service and atmosphere, we always return every year. Our first encounter was for...

4.5 stars 

Came here yesterday for dinner, and boy did it NOT disappoint. We decided to come here for the Summerlicious menu (which I believe majority of...
Went during summerlicous. Great menu selection! Good vibe and great food! - I had salmon to start, beautiful presentation and texture. And the seafood...

Warm goat cheese appetizer is one of the best things I ate in my entire life!!!!! Crazy good. This place is a miracle. Great food. Nice ambiance. Waiter speaks French. Easy parking. Bring your wine. Meat cooked to perfection. Already planned to go back. It’s really worth the money.
I had Christmas eve dinner here and could not even begin to tell how amazing the food, servers and chef were. Top notch all the way. I felt a little like royalty 👑

I had goat cheese and beet salad, delicious!!!
 We also had the fish of the day and the veal, both cooked to perfection! And to make the deal sweeter, the ingredients are so fresh, the herbs used are so delicious, and fresh as well... The server was fantastic!!! And the chef made the experience so personalized by coming and actually talking to all the customer. So food 10, service 10, chef 10 ; now I regret not tipping more... Definitely going to be added to my list of revisit

Veloute Bistro is with out question the best restaurant / bistro in the east end. My wife and I have had numerous meals there and enjoyed every one. In particular the wild game week is my favourite while my wife loves the Seafood Bouillabaisse and beef tartar starter.

This is our go-to restaurant when we want to go for a nice dinner.

The service is great and we always feel as if we are visiting friends for dinner when we eat here.

 Chef Fawzi is a true master. We have never had anything sent from the Kitchen that was less than perfect.

I often send clients here as a thank-you and they always love it.

Gross!!! 
There's no way you are the same as the Augusta location. Sauce, crust and quality...
I wanted to have some authentic pizza and this place was close by so we gave it a try. The entrance to the restaurant is dingy but the seating area is cute....

Amazing service! Very relaxing atmosphere. Probably the best pasta in Toronto. Chef is flexible with the menu as I am vegetarian and made a customize pasta for me. Make sure you try the house red wine. I will go here all the time for Fresh tasting PASTA!!!! Thank you

One of my absolute favourite restaurants. The staff are always very friendly. If you're looking for something light, the marinara pizza is very nice. The chili oil is a nice touch too if you want to drizzle it on. Also, the wine selection is lovely.
The pizza was delicious here, it was a rather quiet place which was a nice bonus, possibly because we may have just missed the lunch rush.

The service was excellent. We ordered pizzas which were well made and incredibly large, however I'm not sure if it was my taste buds or the pizzas I'm used to but they were quite bland. Good amount of toppings, I guess I just didn't pick the right type. I found the red sauce bland and the white pizza lacking in flavour even with Italian sausage. Don't discount this place though, their anti-pasto platter and pastas looked amazing.

An authentic Italian experience with great thin crust pizzas. The pancetta pizza is top notch and my favourite. 

Had to edit my review and remove a star after my visit here on a Monday night. The service was so poor that I'm starting to think Monday night is when they train new servers. If you're going to come here, come at lunch.

reviews.text: You should enjoy the food if you're not extremely critical. The sea food linguini was mediocre and on the greasy side. We had the skate fish, sole and...
This was my second visit here. The first was during last years Winterlicious Festival and the second was last night for a birthday dinner. Our waiter was...
Had my kids communion party here and went to a baptism here also.  There is a side for private parties, that fits about 25-30 people and space for a cake...

I'm going to start by saying that food was very good and environment was good,  the place look really good and clean. Saying that I have to say that I was disappointed with service. When there's a big part they should know that people will sometimes change places/seats and they made a bit of a  fuss about that. I have served for 10 years and you have to have a good memory. I get it that it is "easier" when people stick to their seats but in bigger parties its most likely that it will happen and you have to be prepared and not be sour about it.  The other thing that i DID not like/appreciate was not being advised that they would charge to cut the cake that was brought in. They should've advised the person that made the reservations of the charge and let the person make the choice or not. They pretty much charged $5.00 per person for them to cut the cake. So that for me was a big DEAL. You are not going to make your guest pay for birthday cake. They should give the choice instead of charging without notice. And because of that i'm only giving it a 3 star.

My review is "not fair" as I have yet to eat (and properly experience) this local restaurant, however as I (and many other likely do as well) looked through some reviews that had been left I became less (and less) interested in giving a shot (though I still may - it's just not something I'm rushing to do). 

The reason for this review is to try and help the owner - and by extension patrons / would be diners (or persons responding to other guests reviews), as while most of the reviews are encouraging, the person responding to any "lacklustre" reviews seems to take a conciliatory tone, yet (like many others, just typically not those who consider their establishment to be "fine dining") lacks a candid acknowledgement of the shortcomings some found (in their attempt to provide others with details of their experience). Instead, "excuses" are made (and poorly masked as a response). Most "fine dining" establishments that thrive or survive in the vicinity (and most big cities) pander to their customers - present, future and past, without making a point to compare with "most restaurants" (both as they feel no need and want to set themselves apart in a positive manner) or giving a lecture to customers who have a mixed experience. 

The customer is always right is a well known saying for good reason (the majority know this is far from true, though the underlying reasoning of needing to satisfy their customers - and continuing to do so is... most can fill this in). A patron is not "wrong" for not knowing certain things about a particular restaurant (or neglecting to make certain inquiries) and whether or not "other" places have similar protocols (which is a false assertion in and of itself - the majority both "want to", and "do" set themselves apart). 

I am but just "one" (well usually 2 and upwards of 20) customers - and would have made it a point to try this neighbourhood restaurant, as it looked quite good). If not for the tone taken towards other customers (including a PARTY - numerous potential repeat customers) by the person responding (presumed to be the owner or other key person involved in their operations), choosing to not only be dismissive of their stated criticism (good businesses consider this valuable "feedback"), but specifically makes a point of "what" each reviewer had done "wrong" / "should have known". A word of advice is you'd likely see more success (and ensure future success) by taking one of the following approaches - say "nothing" (no one can be put off - many don't see these reviews or are more traditional and not knowing much about the digital age) - use a "canned response" (they're pretty cheesy but many seem to get by just fine saying "Thanks for your feedback. It helps us provide even greater service!") - or if responding, be candid (which in this case seems overly candid, as that attitude is off putting) and if responding to specific criticisms either placate the customer (to retain them and have them say positive things regarding the way an issue got handled) or at minimum just acknowledge it in a "non-arrogant" manner. I might have been one of your new "best customers", though now that depends on whether or not I choose to try your fine dining some time in the future (as a lot can be taken away from "tone" and message conveyed - this is particularly for local / non franchise or big chain restaurants as it gives a preview into the manner the restaurant is run and what to expect should any issue arrive). 

Best of luck.

Don't be fooled by the "lunch specials".. There's nothing special about it, price nor the food. Asked for the BBQ chicken and potatoes with a small salad paid 28 dollars. My friend ordered the same thing and her chicken was partially raw. She brought it to their attention and didn't pay for the meal.
Beef tenderloin melts in your mouth and the sauce is so good. Black tiger shrimp also one of my favourites. Everything here is amazing if i could eat here everyday i would.

Had a wonderful experience. First time here, I had the black shrimp linguini and it was to die for. My girlfriend had the filet. We both loved our food, and an overall amazing experience. Will definitely be back soon!

reviews.text: Have been to vibo many times with my parents, and every time it has been spectacular.  If you want great service, food and environment than you have come to...
I live in the neighbourhood & have always wanted to try this place. So I popped by ladt night for dinner. The decor is a mix of old & new. They have a great...
I came here with 3 of my girlfriends because one of them lives nearby. The reviews seemed positive, so I thought it would be a pleasant experience. We had a...

Great hospitality. This place really knows how to pay attention to details. My husband and I walked in and he forgot to get coat check, the manager asked if he could take his jacket and when were were leaving his jacket was with mine on the same hanger.  Servers were fantastic. I was at the bar for a short while and contemplating between two wines and the bartender immediately brought me both to taste test prior to making my choice. Table sever has good product knowledge, made the birthday girl feel special and was attentive to my husband's water glass once he realized how much he drinks. The food was exactly what you expect from a restaurant of that quality. Portion sizes were perfect if not generous. Timing of apps to main course was very good. Would recommend and I would come back again, even though we are from out of town.
We went here for our office Christmas party and had a blast! Our server was wonderful and we all enjoyed him. I wish I got his name so I could give him a shout out.
Very slow service. Long waits for each step of ordering and getting the bill. Servers were warm and friendly and helpful but I felt they must be understaffed.
I brought my wife here for our anniversary. Honestly it was the best meal we've both ever had. Really high quality service and food.

Attended a birthday party dinner at Vibo. Nice entertainment with a live pianist. Food is reasonably priced for a special night out. Ordered the apple pecan salad and veal piccata, just enough food to fill up on. The veal was a bit salty.

lic_profile: A modern saloon, Weslodge delivers an elegant but hearty menu, artfully authentic cocktails and a sophisticated yet relaxed atmosphere featuring cutting edge décor. Executive Chef Ben Heaton has developed a variety of innovative yet approachable dishes, executed with a high level of technique. Weslodge's libations are created by a team of pure spirit mixologists led by Elan Marks. House made ingredients elevate classic cocktails to retain their original integrity.

reviews.text: There are no shortage of restaurants in Toronto, as the city offers an impressive range of international foods without needing to travel abroad. You don't...
Weslodge Saloon is a solid 4.5 star and everything down from the experience, vibe, food & service was top notch.  This restaurant is basically a can't miss...

I've been meaning try this since it opened. Having a Sunday free it seemed like the perfect opportunity to try this place.

I was pleasantly surprised at...

Last night I had the most amazing culinary experience at Weslodge. Couldn't get into another restaurant and saw an empty table in their window that had our name all over it. The 7 of went in and our server Ty and the team made sure my friend had the best birthday ever! We had several beverages - all amazing. Apps we had the baby gem salad and devil's horseback. Our shareable main was the Whole Curry Braised Lamb Shoulder which came with several sides. We also had the steak and roasted cauliflower. My greatest fear was that a plate would come out and not be as amazing as the plate before, but everything from start to finish was phenomenal. We finished it off with a Knickerbocker Glory sundae. This is my new favourite restaurant. Any food I've ever had is now substandard in comparison. Thank you for a night I will never forget.

Weslodge Saloon is a solid 4.5 star and everything down from the experience, vibe, food & service was top notch.  This restaurant is basically a can't miss because it has big yellow doors as a grand entrance.  As soon as you walk in you can tell it has a hipster vibe to it and everyone is super friendly as you walk in.  Make sure you make a reservation because it could get filled up pretty quickly in here. As soon as you walk in you''ll see how dark it is in there and how it works because you can still have good conversations even with all the noise. The interior design is very detailed and sophisticated enough to dress up here; but you could definitely come in here with a pair of nice sneakers.  From the cowboy saloon/hipster/hunter feel to this restaurant, Weslodge pulls it off. 

The service is top notch and if you get Bryce as your waiter you'll be going in and out happy.  We got the burger and fish and chips with a traditionally awesome Stella and it was cooked to perfection.  If you look at the menu you might be enticed by the share aspect of the menu which include having a whole chicken, fried chicken or duck.  We didn't get a cocktail but I know this place is very well known for their astounding cocktails so give it a try! Overall, this place is A1.

Good selection of beers and pub food. Good ambience, big bar seating area,  lean washrooms. 
Priced standard kind west prices which are generally high.

I have walked by Weslodge often and finally tonite 5 friends and I decided to check it out for dinner.  Weslodge is best experienced from the sidewalk.  The service sucked and the dinner nasty.  I rarely provide a review but in this case I need to provide a public service, do yourself a favour, just walk by...

It is 1:12 am and my stomach is still asking why did I eat those 3 mouthfuls of food.  I had the fish and chips and it was aweful.
Sat at the bar, awesome service, excellent Old Fashions. Food isn't cheap but definitely worth it.

reviews.text: I'm so glad that Wildfire was one of the options on the Summerlicious restaurant list because if it wasn't then I would've never discovered this place....
I have mixed feelings about this steakhouse. We were seated promptly without reservations, however we did ask for a bigger table as we would've ordered more...

For a summerlicious menu and portions, I'd have to give them 3 stars. With excellent service bringing it to a 4. 

I came with out law family for a meal,...

Ambiance is great, it is beautiful inside, be booths, tables and private rooms x3, bathroom are downstairs and beautiful. One handicapped washroom on main floor. Almost always someone to greet you and open the door for you which is nice. Much of the food is quite good. Pastas are always on point. Lots of drink variety. Interesting way of serving big parties, can be quite a lovely experience. Desserts are all delicious as well. Meat is always great quality.

I always enjoyed going to the Wildfire Steakhouse. The food is great, the staff are wonderful! They have an amazing wine list! Something not everyone knows is that if it's very community-oriented Steakhouse and Jody the owner help the community in many ways! Really a great spot!
Unreal steak house. Steak was cooked to perfection. The ambiance is superb, relaxing, romantic, formal. Very nice place. Pricey though. Around $75-100 a person for dining

Worst place I’ve been to in a while. Steak was overcooked, service was terrible, and even after bringing concerns to the waiter and manager nothing was done. Best part was the mandatory 18% gratuity I didn’t want to pay. Never coming back.
Love this place. Quality of the food and wine is outstanding. Service is Tops! Highly recommended.

reviews.text:
Most memorable feature: Cozy 

Loved my summerlicious experience at Wish.  The couches were very comfy and the restaurant gave a very homie feeling....
The food is truly pretty amazing. (Though limited menu, not a huge variety of healthy fare) And the staff are very sweet and have wonderful energy. But...

Such an adorable restaurant!

The atmosphere was great; very comfy and pretty decor. The food was good, but didn't have enough 'wow' factor to it. Would've...

My wife and I were there for dinner on Saturday after a show. Even though we were there at 5pm, they seemed disorganized and the service was very slow. We were in the porch area, it was very cold.  It was raining and  water was dripping on our table.  Halfway through our meal, we had to move our coats to make space for menus!  My striploin was very good with a good helping of fries. My wife had lamb gnocchi which was also very good with generous portion. However we wanted to take home the remainder which was lots, but they threw it out and couldn't offer to make it up.  Maybe we had bad luck but our experience was wanting.

Friendly service and good food but tight seating at the front. Came here for brunch and we were seated near the entrance, which felt way too crowded. There was barely enough room for people to get by so my chair was nudged every time someone walked past our table.

Nice place with good food but not the best experience. Asked for the poached eggs to be hard instead of soft and they charged 2 dollars extra for the "modification" as it slows down the kitchen. If your guest is asking for a substitute that costs more money it's understood that there would be a cost but leaving an egg in water for 30 seconds extra? That's a poor customer experience and one lazy chef...

We had a reservation for brunch. On arrival we requested for an outdoor table and were told there was no availability. Since there were at least five that we could see (they have two outdoor seating areas), we pointed those out and were told that it’s on first come, first served basis!! (you can’t specify outdoor or indoor at the time of reservation). So we were there 11 am, yet told that we couldn’t have seating of our choice for some obscure reason. Told them we would cancel the reservation, and weren’t asked not to or provided any customer courtesy!!  We walked out (and had a fantastic meal at a place not far from this one) and the one star based on really bad customer service.

The food is truly amazing. And the staff are very sweet and have wonderful energy. But it's... Very... Slow... And feels mismanaged, like no one knows whose serving which table sort of feel. After being seated we waited nearly 20 mins for a server to come see us, my table mate had to flag down the manager and ask for a server, who knows how much longer it would have been if she had not. 

Based on other reviews that seems about the typical experience. 

That being said, the food everyone ordered was amazing. Like the Nutella french toast and I had the Florentine Benedict, which comes with a parmesan fondue that beats boring old hollandaise everyday. Their cappuccino was nice, and the mimosa my friend had was strong and delicious unlike most brunch places where that is usually the weakest point. 

The decor is really so sweet and special, like your best friend's first rental, there is fairy lights, and a drafty but authentically lush and well decorated outdoor patio, a shabby modern industrial aesthetic that makes you feel cozy and cool.

Had the Sushi and Sashimi Lover with the Yuzu Roll (the one that's on fire)
Sashimi was fresh, succulent (actually viable here) and each had a well...
Came here for lunch after reading the positive reviews. I have to say that everything was great up until we started ordering. The staff seemed pretty...

The sushi was good, but overpriced. 
I could have gotten the same or similar uality for cheaper. 
The wait staff were nice, a bit lost at times though.

Good sushi. Japanese owner and chefs. The rice wasn't great which we addressed with the owner who was very apologetic. It wasn't bad, just could have been softer. The quality of the fish was good overall. We've been there twice during our 3 day visit to Toronto .

Best Japanese food I've had. I've been to Japan 3 times so I know a bit about good Japanese food. Everything was fresh and tasty!  The service was great! Our server was Jason great knowledge and a good sense of humor. He was a lot of fun. My girlfriend and I will definitely be back. Highly recommend Yuzu No Hana!          Sully (no relation to Tom Hanks)
Very nice food but just increased prices by 50%, not really any vegetarian options other than edamame. Service starts good but the waiters often avoid eye contact once food is served.
Their Omakase was wonderful!  They include their daily items plus more. It would definitely be a good choice to for special occasions.

The only reason I didn't give Yuzu 5 Star rating was due to the Manager they employ. She was so rude & condescending to all the staff & I could hear her berating them too. Why & how she is Manager of such a lovely place with such exceptional, hard working staff is beyond me? She looks like she's constantly in a bad mood & a dark cloud following her. The service was truly great, the food was excellent & the decor is simple but elegant. Very comfortable place to take family or a date too. Again, the experience was exceptional, with the exception of the Manager on duty. She does not deserve to be a Manager anywhere tbh! If she's there the next time I visit, I'm leaving & taking my business elsewhere!
